title: cheese log
directions: Soften cream cheese and Cheddar cheese until room temperature. Mix in Hidden Valley.
Shape into log and roll in parsley flakes or chopped nuts.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Cool.
When cake is cool, split layers and fill with filling mixture; frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with a little frozen coconut on top of cake. Chill overnight.

title: linzer tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend eggs, extract, flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour before rolling. Roll 1/4-inch and cut with round cutter.
Cut half again without centers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 minutes. Will look white (do not overbake).
Cool on wire rack.
Spread preserves on bottom.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and then put them together.

title: 1-2-3 tuna pie
directions: Place pie crust on wax paper in 425° oven.
Combine other ingredients and pour into pie pan.
Replace pie crust on top; slit several places.
Do not seal edges.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 425° or until crust is lightly browned and filling is bubbly.

title: lemon-lime cooler
directions: Place pudding mix in a large bowl.
Add milk; beat with an egg beater 1 or 2 minutes, until well blended.
Stir in lime juice. Pour into chilled glasses.
Garnish with fresh mint.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 1/2 cups.

title: sissy's top ramen
directions: Read instructions on the back of the bag of noodles.
After you have completed all steps, empty the water from the noodles and eat while hot.
Enjoy.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender, cool and remove bones.
Cut into bite-size pieces and place in a large casserole dish or oblong pan.
Mix soups and broth until smooth.
Pour over meat.
Take melted butter, water and dressing; mix well.
Sprinkle over meat. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie mix as directed on box without water and bake 4 to 5 minutes until sides are brown (use temperature on box).

title: sunshine dill pickles
directions: Heat water, vinegar and salt to boiling.
After ingredients are added, pour the boiling liquid into the jars.
Seal and place in sunshine for two weeks.
If they (work out) spew, don't worry. Wipe jars and place in storage.

title: clam cakes
directions: Beat eggs, milk, clam juice and chopped clams slightly with a spoon.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix until flour mixture disappears.
Drop, by spoonfuls, into hot, deep fat.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except whipped topping.
Blend well.
Add whipped topping.
Fold into ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan and place in freezer.
Remove from freezer 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: southwestern chicken
directions: Coarsely cut up tomatoes and onion.
In blender at medium speed or in food processor with knife blade attached, blend tomatoes, onion, garlic, cilantro, lime juice and soy sauce until tomatoes and onion are finely chopped.
Place chicken and sauce in a large Ziploc bag and seal, turning chicken to coat well with marinade.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Prepare outdoor grill for barbecuing.
Place chicken on grill over medium heat, reserving marinade.
Cook until golden on both sides, about 10 minutes.
Cook until fork-tender, brushing occasionally with tomato marinade.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini cooked with wheat
directions: Wash zucchini, peel if desired (good with skin).
Chop in small pieces, set aside.
Saute onion in oil, brown lightly. Add zucchini and spices.
Cover and cook,
Do not add water.
After 10 - 15 mins., zucchini will get tender and can be lightly mashed with a fork or masher.
Add tomato paste and wheat.
Cook until wheat is tender, stirring occasionally.
Ready to eat 45 - 50 mins. Good as a side dish anytime, especially on Fridays.
Extra summer zucchini are great.
Can be frozen, used later.

title: hot crunchy chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips and cheese.
Spoon into buttered baking dish.
Combine chips and cheese and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Peel, section and seed orange.
Whirl orange in blender. Prepare cake mix by package directions.
Fold 1/3 cup orange into batter and bake in 2 (8-inch) layer cake pans as directed on package.
Cool.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt. Add margarine, 1 cup water and remaining orange.
Bring to boil, stirring, and cook
2 minutes.
Cool and stir in coconut.
Split each layer and spread each layer and top with mixture.
Prepare frosting as directed on package and spread on sides of cake. Garnish top with halved maraschino cherries.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes into thin slices.
Layer them in oven proof container.
Layer potatoes, then onions, then sprinkle with cheese and salt.
Continue with the remaining potatoes and onions.
Cover with white sauce (recipe to follow). Bake at 350° approximately 1-1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: no-fail cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In an iron skillet, add 2 tablespoons oil, heat to medium to medium-high.
Mix dry ingredients; add eggs and milk.
Mix until ingredients are moistened and mixed well. Pour into hot skillet.
Bake until browned in hot oven.

title: oatmeal chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. Pour boiling water over oats and let stand 10 minutes.
Add sugar and margarine to oats.
Stir until margarine melts.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt and cocoa to oat mixture.
Add 1/2 of the chocolate chips.
Pour into pan; sprinkle the rest of the chips over the top of cake.
Bake 40 minutes or until done.

title: fresh fruit dressing
directions: Mix together and heat enough to melt sugar.
Cool and refrigerate.
Pour over fruit.
I use fresh fruit such as: grapefruit, oranges, kiwi, pineapple, bananas, grapes and strawberries.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick coating.
Mix Ricotta cheese, cottage cheese, parsley and garlic. Pour 1 cup sauce in bottom of pan.
Arrange 1/3 noodles in pan so that they touch, but do not overlap.
Spread 1/2 of the cheese mixture over noodles.
Top with 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese.
Top this with 1 cup of sauce, 1/3 of the noodles, the remainder of the cheese mixture and the rest of the Mozzarella cheese.
Add another cup of sauce, another layer of noodles and the remainder of the sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake, covered tightly with aluminum foil for 1 hour.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat butter, 3/4 cup
sugar, milk, egg and vanilla.

In another bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to butter mix, blending well after each addition. Turn into greased and floured 8 or 9-inch baking pan. Top with apples, then sprinkle with remaining sugar combined with cinnamon. Bake 40 minutes.

title: busy day meat loaf
directions: Stir together stuffing mix and milk in large mixing bowl.
Let stand about 5 minutes or until stuffing mix is softened.
Add egg, Worcestershire sauce, onion and salt.
Beat well.
Add ground beef.
Mix until combined.
Shape into loaf.
Place in greased or foil-lined shallow baking pan.
Score loaf by making several diagonal grooves across the top.
Fill with catsup.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until well browned.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Completely dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Set aside.
Mix Crisco, sugar and salt. Add boiling water. Cool slightly.
Add beaten eggs and mix.
Add flour and yeast alternating.
Mix thoroughly. Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Flatten on lightly floured board until about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Dip each piece in melted margarine and place in alternate layers in Bundt pan. Cover and let rise until double. Bake at 300° about 1 hour.

title: chilli dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Cut up cheese.
Place in crock-pot on low.
Serve with chips.

title: coconut refrigerator cookies
directions: Sift flour; add soda and salt.
Cream butter; add sugar and mix until fluffy.
Add eggs, flour mixture, rolled oats, nuts and coconut and mix thoroughly.
Divide dough into 4 rolls and refrigerate until firm.
Can also be frozen.
Take out; let thaw. Cut into 1/8-inch slices.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain for 1/2 hour.
Add 1 small can evaporated milk, butter and beat.
Cook on low heat 1 hour.
Stir often.
Pour in casserole dish; cover top with bread crumbs and butter.
Brown in oven.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix well with a mixer.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill at least 3 hours.
Top with any fruit pie filling (blueberry, cherry, strawberry, etc.).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of salted water for about 15 minutes.
Drain and coarsely chop.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: ham and tater pom poms
directions: In a saucepan, heat the water, butter, salt and pepper to boiling.
Remove from heat. Add the potato flakes and whip lightly with a fork.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop slightly rounded teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 12-15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Tip:
These can be made ahead and refrigerated.
Reheat by placing on a cookie sheet and putting them into a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
One recipe makes about 48 snack pieces.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Beat the cheese until soft and fluffy. Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Pour into crust.
Freeze 3 hours or until firm.
Drizzle with chocolate sauce before serving.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in Crisco until mixed thoroughly.
Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Work together with large spoon until all flour is moistened.
Cover bowl and place in refrigerator until ready to use (best after sets overnight).

title: beef tips and noodles
directions: Place beef tips, celery soup, mushroom soup and onion soup mix in crock-pot.
Place beef tips first.
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours or on high for 4 to 5 hours.
Pour over cooked (drained) dumpling noodles.

title: 1-2-3 stew
directions: Combine all ingredients; turn into large buttered casserole. Cover.
Bake 3 hours at 300° or 4 hours at 250°.
Serves 8.

title: cheese squares
directions: Mix shredded cheeses together.
Mix milk, eggs, flour and chilies together.
Combine and put in 9 x 13 pan.
Top with pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with ice ring made in Jell-O mold.
Add some of the cherries for festive appearance.

title: virginia's hamburger soup
directions: Saute onions in the oil. Add meat and garlic; cook until brown. Add rest of ingredients except okra. Bring to a boil and simmer 1 to 1 1/4 hours until potatoes and carrots are tender. Let frozen okra set out on counter while soup is cooking so it will be thawed. Add okra and cook just until it is done.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine first eight ingredients in large bowl.
Take 12 four tortillas, place about 1/2 to 3/4 teaspoon of filling in each tortilla.
Fold as for burrito, bottom fold up then fold sides in then roll.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with soup and milk, mixed.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and put into baking dish.

title: cream cheese pound cake(billy carter's favorite)
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese, blending in sugar with electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time and continue to blend. Add flavoring and beat until smooth and light.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake is golden and tests done.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.

title: savory chili
directions: Brown beef and onions together;
drain off excess fat.
Stir in beans, tomatoes, and salt, pepper, and chili powder to taste. Simmer for several hours.

title: myrtle taylor's old fashion sugar cookie - 1940's(family favorite)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg together; set aside.
Add lemon rind or extract to butter and cream together; add 1 cup sugar gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and cream; beat thoroughly.
Gradually add flour mixture and blend.
Chill until firm enough to roll, 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut with 3 1/2-inch floured cutter or other shapes.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: creamed crabmeat on toasted buns or english muffins
directions: Mix in bowl and put on toasted bun.
Put under broiler for 5 to 6 minutes until toasted around edges.
Serve with congealed salad and iced tea for a nice lunch.
Makes 4 servings.

title: turkey croquettes
directions: Melt the butter in a medium saucepan; then stir in the flour until well blended.
Slowly stir in milk and cook until the mixture thickens, about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove the sauce from heat and pour into large mixing bowl.
Add parsley, scallions, turkey, lemon juice, sage and thyme and blend well.
Cover the bowl and chill until firm about 30 minutes.
Shape mixture into 10 squat cones, roll in bread crumbs, dip into the beaten eggs, and roll in bread crumbs again.
Place on a platter and allow to dry about 10 minutes at room temperature.
Fry in hot fat about 375° for about 5 minutes.
Drain and serve immediately.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Beat in the eggs, salt, baking powder and flour.
Stir in the cereal, coconut, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet and bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: mama's banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in heavy saucepan.
Add milk, stirring over heat, then add eggs, butter and vanilla while beating with electric beater over medium heat.
Pudding done when mixture bubbles up and has become thick.
Let cool, then add bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and 7-Up alternately mixing well each time.
Add flavoring.
Cook in cold oven at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: apple crisp with orange juice
directions: Mound apples in buttered pie plate and pour orange juice over them.
In separate bowl, combine sugar, flour, spices and salt; cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, or until apples are tender and topping is crisp.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: yum yum chicken
directions: Season chicken as desired; boil until tender. Cool and skim off fat. Bone chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.

Arrange in 9 x 11-inch pan. Mix soups and sour cream; spoon over chicken. Top with stuffing mix. Melt margarine in heated chicken broth; pour evenly over all. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Can be served over rice.

title: spaghetti sauce(canning)
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except the tomato paste, and cook 1 hour. Add the tomato paste and cook for 1 more hour. Cook slowly and stir often. Put in hot jars and seal. Can be canned or frozen.

title: coconut, sour cream, dream cake
directions: Mix water, cake mix, eggs, and oil. Stir in 1 c. coconut. Pour into two round cake pans. Bake at 350 until done.

Mix sour cream and sugar together. Add 1 1/4 c. coconut, 3/4 c. toasted coconut and 1 1/2 c. pecans, chill. Spread part of mixture between layers. To remaining mixture add whipped topping. Spread on sides and top of cake. Garnish top of cake with 1/4 c. pecans and 1 c. toasted coconut. Store in sealed container in refrigerator.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Wash and drain all vegetables.
Begin with lettuce, in bottom of container that can be sealed tightly.
Layer peas on top of lettuce.
Rest of vegetables may be layered as desired.
End with another layer of lettuce.
Sprinkle lemon juice all over salad. Seal top of salad with mayonnaise to airtight.
Garnish with cheese and real bacon bits.
Seal container with lid.
Refrigerate overnight or 8 hours.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain well the spinach. Pat extra moisture out on paper towels. Stir in cream cheese, sour cream and dried onion soup mix. Blend well. Pour into ungreased 8 1/2 x 11-inch or 9 x 12-inch casserole. Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cover for 1/2 the baking time, then uncover until cheese melts.

title: apple cranberry crisp
directions: Combine apples and cranberries.
Toss with 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Place in greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish.
Combine flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and salt and rolled oats.
Sprinkle over apple mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes until top is crisp and brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot cross muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt in medium bowl.
Make well in center.
Beat egg, oil and 2/3 cup milk.
Pour into well.
Stir with wooden spoon until flour is moistened.
Stir in raisins.
Spoon into buttered muffin tins filling 2/3 full. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Remove from tins and cool.

title: special turkey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roast in 350° oven.
Turkey will be done when popcorn blows the tail off the turkey.

title: tallerene
directions: Cook noodles.
Sear meat and chopped onion until grainy.
Add half the catsup, half the cheese and all the other ingredients. Put in a 3-quart casserole dish and top with remaining catsup and cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: unleavened bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl together, using a fork to stir first.
Then, use hands to combine ingredients into stiff dough.
Dough will be sticky at first, but continue working dough until smooth and elastic.
Pinch dough into 1-inch balls and flatten to about a 3-inch round.
Bake in an oven or electric skillet at 400° until slightly browned.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together, then add eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour mixture and sour cream alternately. Add vanilla.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° or until cake stays in place when touched lightly with finger.
Cake will pull away from pan slightly.

title: tomato soup
directions: Brown onion in margarine.
Stir in
flour,
salt, sugar and pepper.
Cook until smooth and
bubbly, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in 2
cups tomato juice or canned tomatoes.
Bring to a boil,	stirring constantly and boil for 1 minute.
Add 2 cups cold whole milk,	all
at once. Heat rapidly
to
serving temperature,
stirring
constantly. Serve at once.

title: southern chili for four
directions: In saucepan, combine beef and water; simmer about 15 minutes or until meat loses its red color.
Separate meat from liquid and chill both.
Remove any congealed fat.
Set aside 3/4 cup of beef broth.
In saucepan, combine peppers, onion, jalapeno, celery and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, seasoning and reserved 3/4 cup of beef broth.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: delicatessen pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in a gallon jar.
Add garlic, pickling spices, red pepper and fresh dill as desired.
Combine vinegar, salt and water, bringing to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Cool.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Let stand for 5 or 6 weeks before using. Delicious.

title: banana boat dessert
directions: Prepare mix as package directs for pudding.
Fold in whipped topping (Cool Whip) and marshmallows.
Line bottom and sides of baking dish with wafers.
Pour in half of pudding mixture.
Cover with banana slices.
Top with remaining pudding.
Fix an anchor on top of pudding out of marshmallows.
Chill.

title: cabbage delight
directions: Grind cabbage and apples until fine.
Mix well and add salad dressing and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and let set one hour.
Toss and serve.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Coat bread with butter.
Arrange cucumber slices on bread and sprinkle with dill.

title: easy thousand island dressing
directions: Very good on lettuce hearts or served with fish.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Pour oil in wok and preheat on high for 3 minutes.
Place meat in hot oil.
Stir-fry.
Turn meat occasionally.
Add celery.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add onion.
Cook 2 minutes.
(When pan gets dry, add vegetable broth as needed.)
Add mushrooms and green peppers.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add remaining vegetable broth and soy sauce.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain, but do not rinse.
While pasta is hot, toss with vegetables.
Cover for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: crepes (french pancakes)
directions: Sift flour.
Resift with salt, baking powder and powdered sugar.
Beat 2 eggs.
Add milk, water and vanilla.

title: roman apple cake
directions: Combine in mixing bowl sugar, flour, salt, baking powder, soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Beat in shortening, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add 3 cups raw apples, pared and chopped.
Mix well. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble together melted margarine, cinnamon, brown sugar, flour and oats.
Place on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix following directions on box.
Bake in a 1 layer (9 x 12-inch) pan.
After cake is done, poke holes in it all over (but not to edge) using a fork.
Pour condensed milk all over cake into holes, using entire can.
Refrigerate cake for 2 hours.
Remove from fridge and spoon 3/4 can crushed pineapple on top of cake; smooth it out with a spoon.
Frost with Cool Whip. Sprinkle remaining pineapple over all.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Great cool dessert!

title: shrimp  bisque
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp, stirring to make a smooth paste.
Heat slowly until thick.
Add shrimp and cook briefly until tender.
Serve as a one dish meal with corn bread.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine milk and lime juice by hand and gently stir in Cool Whip.
Pile in crust and chill.

title: old fashioned butter pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cold water.
Add boiling water and flavoring.	Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Slice butter over pie filling.
Bake
in	a
350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with egg white meringue when cool.

title: pork chops creole
directions: Brown chops in butter until an even light brown.
Arrange in baking dish.
Brown onion and pepper in same pan chops were cooked in. Add soup and seasonings. Cook 5 minutes.
Pour over chops. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve and enjoy.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Saute onion and pepper in 3 tablespoons oil in skillet; do not brown.
Combine enchilada sauce and sour cream in saucepan. Simmer for 1 minute.
Spread a small amount of sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan. Soften tortillas 1 at a time in 1/4 cup hot oil for several seconds; drain on a paper towel.
Add onion, pepper and Monterey Jack to tortillas; roll to enclose filling.
Place seam side down in prepared pan.
Pour enchilada sauce over top. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut filling
directions: Cook all ingredients, except coconut and nuts, until mixture thickens (about 12 minutes).
Add nuts and coconut; beat until thick.
Spread on cake layers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
well.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake at	350°
for approximately 45 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup bread crumbs over top, if desired.

title: jellied salad
directions: Dissolve jello with hot water.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into a large mold or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.

title: reva's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well in bowl; mold into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut butter brownie cups
directions: Mix brownie batter according to package directions.
Fill paper-lined or foil lined muffin cups two-thirds full.
Remove wrappers from peanut butter cups.
Set one in each muffin cup and press down until batter meets the top edge of the candy.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Combine flour, margarine and sugar until well blended.
Best done with fork or fingers.
Dough will be sticky.
Pack into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 18 minutes, just until edges start to brown.
Cool.

title: aunt beatrice's dumplings
directions: Mix flour and eggs with enough milk to make a stiff dough. Knead a few times and roll dough very thin.
Cut into strips and break into small pieces when dropping into broth.
Cook until tender.

title: carrot cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Then add eggs. Mix and add flour.
Mix, then add carrots and nuts, then mix again.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan; glaze with orange icing.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Toss macaroni with butter or margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a lightly greased crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high 2 to 3 hours, stirring once or twice.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Mix together in crock pot:
pork and beans, kidney, butter beans, brown sugar, ketchup and liquid smoke.
Fry bacon and onions.
Drain.
Add hamburger and bacon to crock pot.
Cook on high 1 hour.

title: fresh lemonade
directions: Stir together water, lemon juice and sugar.
Pour over ice. Makes 10 (3/4-cup) servings.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apple, celery and nuts.
Blend in mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: favorite deviled eggs
directions: Mix in a bowl together first 7 ingredients until creamy.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in cheese.
Cover and refrigerate. Yields 25 appetizers.

title: raspberry-chocolate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, pecans, butter and egg; stir until crumbly.
Set aside 1 1/2 cups of this pecan mixture.
Press the remaining mixture into the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread the raspberry jam over all.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips, then top with the remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack; cut into bars.
Yield: 3 dozen bars.

title: sausage lasagna wraps
directions: Cook and drain lasagna noodles.
Divide 1 pound sausage into 6 pieces.
Split sausage lengthwise and place 1/2 slice Mozzarella cheese on top.
Wrap each piece in a cooked noodle.
Place layer of spaghetti sauce in baking dish.
Place lasagna wrap on sauce. Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with grated Romano cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: one-dish microwave sausage stew
directions: In a 3-quart microwavable baking dish or bowl, combine water, milk and cheese sauce packet from potato mix.
Stir in sausage, frozen vegetables and dehydrated potato slices.
Cover and microwave on High (100%) power, stirring every 5 to 7 minutes, for 32 to 35 minutes, or until potatoes are tender (will be extremely hot; good idea to let stand for a few minutes).
Serve with your favorite bread, toast or crackers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: quick noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out like pie crust.
Cover with flour.
Double over half again.
Press with rolling pin.
Cover top with flour.
Start at one end and roll dough into a roll. Slice diagonally from end of roll into thin slices.
Drop into boiling broth.
Don't stir; just push apart.
Boil 5 minutes. Don't cover.

title: butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Add milk; stir in flour mixture until blended.
Refrigerate dough for 1 hour.
Roll out dough; cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes on greased sheet until golden brown.
Yield:
25 cookies. Carbohydrate 11 g, protein 1 g, fat 3 g, calories per cookie 75. Four cookies = 1 fruit exchange, 1/2 fat exchange.

title: reception salad
directions: Dissolve jello in pineapple juice heated to boiling point. Add salt.
Cool.
When mixture begins to set, pour remaining ingredients; fold in whipping cream last.
Serves 14.

title: mccurley's meatballs
directions: Knead ingredients into meat, then roll into balls.
Put in frypan on high with an inch of water.
Boil until brown.
Put in spaghetti or eat by themselves.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Heat meat in skillet until redness is gone.
Add mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Place in a baking dish and cover with Tater Tots.
Bake until golden brown.

title: minute cookies
directions: Mix all together. Drop on greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: dolly beck's overnight lettuce salad
directions: Use a straight sided bowl large enough to hold all ingredients.
Layer vegetables in order given, starting with lettuce.
Save some lettuce to make a thin top layer.
Top with the mayonnaise, sealing the edges.
Sprinkle with the sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly; refrigerate overnight.
The sugar causes the onions to weep, which makes this salad a success.
Do not stir.
Serve carefully to get some of all layers.
This salad keeps several days if kept refrigerated.
Lettuce stays crisp if you sealed the edges well with the mayonnaise.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil in saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and cereal.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and cool.

title: never fail egg white meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch and cold water.
Add boiling water.
Cook until thick and clear.
Let it get cold and then add to egg whites.

title: cherries "n" chocolate fudge
directions: Line square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch) with foil.
In medium microwave-proof bowl, combine sweetened milk and chocolate chips. Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in almond extract, almonds and cherries.
Spread evenly in pan.
Cover and chill until firm. Store in refrigerator covered.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces.
Fry some of the grease out and put onion in to cook some.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: cucumbers and onions
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions into bowl.
Bring vinegar, sugar and celery seed to a boil in saucepan.
Let cool slightly.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook small beets until tender. Cool in cold water. Slip off skins. Make syrup. Cover beets and simmer 15 minutes. Seal in hot jars.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and add to meat, drain.
Add tomato soup, ketchup, worcestershire sauce and vinegar.
Stir well and let simmer for a few minutes spoon onto buns or toast.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water (must not be hot).
Sift flour, salt and sugar into mixing bowl.
Add Crisco and whole egg. Mix together with yeast water.
Cover and put into refrigerator overnight.
Roll dough out about 1-inch thick.
Cut rolls and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let rise 3 hours.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes or until nice and brown.
This dough can also be used for cinnamon rolls.
Serves 12.

title: unfried salmon patties(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Spray lite vegetable cooking oil spray over cookie sheet.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour, then stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes for a chewy cookie, 10 to 11 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet. Remove to wire rack.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: holiday ham and cheese ball
directions: In small bowl, combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, deviled ham, onion and chilies, chopped fine.
Mix well, shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill in refrigerator.
Take out to soften slightly before using.
Serve with your favorite cookies.
Makes 1 (2-cup) cheese ball.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well.
Serve by adding 2 teaspoons to each cup of boiling water.
Store in tightly sealed container.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, gelatin, salt, egg yolks, cinnamon and milk; cook until it boils.
It will just start to thicken.
After this is completely cooled, fold in pumpkin, sugar and egg whites.
Pour into shell.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Mix and blend the first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Pour over the cabbage and mix well.
Refrigerate approximately 3 hours. Remove from refrigerator; stir well and sprinkle with paprika and Praise the Lord!

title: dot's fried rice
directions: In large skillet, add cooking oil (make sure to cover the entire bottom of skillet).
Scramble eggs and set aside.
In same skillet, add scallions.
Stir, then add rice and stir.
Add soy sauce to rice and scallions; stir until the rice turns brown from the sauce.
Add shrimp; cover and cook for about 1 minute, then add sprouts, eggs, chicken and carrots (if you desire chicken and carrots).
Heat through and serve.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake; cool.
Take 1/2 of the cake and crumble in bottom of punch bowl, then layer 1/2 can of pineapple, 1 box of pudding, 1/2 can cherry pie filling and 1 banana (sliced thin and covering the pie filling).
Start layers all over, beginning with the cake. Top with Cool Whip.
Keep cold.

title: fly-off-the-plate rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Pour hot water over the sugar, butter and salt; add 2 cups flour. Beat as hard as possible. Let cool to lukewarm. Add the yeast mixture and remainder of flour. Knead well and let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours. Shape into rolls or 2 loaves of bread.
Let rise again. Bake 20 minutes (rolls) or 50 minutes (loaves) in a 375° oven.

title: trifle dessert(an old english recipe)
directions: Slice cake to cover bottom of Pyrex baking dish.
Cover with strawberry jam.
Sprinkle with brandy.
Make up Jell-O in usual way and when Jell-O is cooled, pour over cake.
Put in refrigerator until set.
Add fresh fruit.
Return to refrigerator until served with whipped cream.

title: corn chowder
directions: Brown bacon until almost crisp.
Add onion and saute.
Add cut-up potatoes and carrots.
Add milk.
Cover and cook until vegetables are done.
Add creamed corn, salt and pepper to taste.

title: dumplins
directions: Sift flar* , salt and bakin* powders together.
Add ag* , lard and water til it turns to workable dough.
Pinch off and drop in biling* chicken or matos* .
Cook until done or they git* hard.

title: vegetables with linguine
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions. While linguine is cooking, saute garlic and mushrooms in 1/4 cup oil in a large skillet.
Add broccoli, salt, basil and remaining 1/4 cup oil. Saute until vegetables are crisp-tender. Toss with cooked linguine and serve.

title: pie crust dough
directions: Combine salt and flour in mixing bowl.
Cut in Crisco with pastry blender until mixture is fairly coarse.
Sprinkle with water, a tablespoon at a time, tossing with a fork.
Work dough into a firm ball.
Roll into desired shape on a lightly floured surface.
Place in pie plate; fill as desired.
Bake as needed. Yields double crust for 8 or 9-inch pie plate.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown burger and onions.
Drain.
Add soup. milk, bouillon, cooked vegetables and cooked rice.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Pour into 9 X 13 pan.
Lay cheese on top.
Place baked tater tots on top of cheese.
If it is still warm, microwave about 10 minutes.
If not, microwave about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: patty's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add the eggs.
Sift and add the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, and ginger.
Add the vanilla, oatmeal and raisins.
Shape balls by hand and press with sugar on glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Toss together and spread on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a 300° to 325° oven for 10 minutes.

title: stuffed bell peppers for two
directions: Cut off top of each pepper; remove seeds.
Cook 5 minutes in boiling salted water; drain.
Set aside.
Combine ground beef, rice, 1/4 cup tomato sauce and remaining ingredients.
Stuff peppers with mixture and place in small baking pan.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over stuffed peppers and bake at 350° for an hour or until meat is done.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Melt Velveeta and mix with soup and 1 can of water.
Brown hamburger meat.
Warm tortillas in microwave for about 15 seconds. Fill with spoonfuls of meat and grated Cheddar cheese.
Roll up and place in casserole dish.
Pour cheese and soup mixture over enchiladas and cook in a 350° oven until heated through and through.

title: spoon bread(a family favorite)
directions: Recorded while observing a spoon bread expert at work!!!

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in berries.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
(The batter will be lumpy.
Do not overmix.)
Spoon into 12 (2 1/2-inch) greased muffin tins.
Bake 25 minutes or until done at 400°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar together and set aside. Prepare pudding as directed on package and chill.
Mix Cool Whip, pudding mixture and cream cheese mixture together. Layer in a 2-quart deep bowl beginning and ending with cookie crumbs.
A cute idea is to use a plastic hanging basket flowerpot.
Cover the holes in the bottom of the pot with the top of the Cool Whip container to avoid leaking and use a trowel to dip.
Can be put in freezer about 2 to 3 hours before serving so it will not be too soft.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Put meat in pan.
Cover with all ingredients.
Cover pan with lid and bake at 325° for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir sauce halfway through cooking time.

title: butterfinger ice cream dessert
directions: In a square or rectangular pan, place a layer of
ice cream sandwiches until they cover entire bottom of pan (you may have to cut a few to make them fit).
Cover sandwiches with chocolate fudge, then layer in Cool Whip.
Finally, sprinkle Butterfinger crumbs over top.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: zucchini custard
directions: Cook zucchini, covered in salted boiling water until tender. Drain well.
Put in shallow baking dish.
Beat together egg, sour cream, salt, pepper and half of cheese.
Pour over zucchini.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until set.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheddar puffs
directions: Grate cheese and cut butter into bits.
Add all other ingredients and stir the mixture with a wooden spatula until it forms a ball.
Knead the dough lightly to distribute the fat evenly and reform it into a ball.
Dust with flour, then chill for 1 hour (wrapped in waxed paper).
Roll out between two sheets of waxed paper into 1/4 inch rectangle and cut out rounds with a 1-inch fluted cutter.
Arrange these 1 inch apart on baking sheets.
Brush with 1 large egg beaten with a pinch of salt.
Sprinkle rounds with poppy seed and bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes, until puffed and golden.
Let cool for 5 minutes, then transfer to rack to cool completely.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cake:
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sift together flour, cinnamon and baking soda.
In another bowl cream together sugar and corn oil.
Combine ingredients and add the eggs and grated carrots.
Fold and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken breast.
Mix egg and seasonings.
Beat well and soak chicken for 2 to 3 hours in refrigerator.
Drain and roll chicken in flour and fry in hot grease.
Makes a crispy, delicious fried chicken.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Mix milk, pumpkin, sugar and seasonings.
Cook until well heated.
Add beaten egg yolks into mix.
Cook until thick.
Soften gelatin in cold water; stir into pumpkin until dissolved.
Set in refrigerator to thicken.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in; whip the cream and fold in.
Put in a 9 to 10-inch baked pie shell. Top with toasted coconut and refrigerate.

title: buttermilk corn muffins(great with cheese dishes and soups)
directions: Combine dry ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in buttermilk, egg substitute and fat-free mayonnaise until well blended.
Spray muffin pans with cooking spray; spoon batter into muffin pans, filling two-thirds full.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 12 muffins; 0 grams fat per muffin.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Warm bowl and flat beater with hot water and dry.
Place potatoes in bowl and break apart with fork.
Attach bowl and flat beater.
Gradually turn to speed 4 and beat 1 minute, until smooth.
Add milk, butter, salt and pepper on speed 4.
Beat until milk is absorbed.
Increase to speed 6 until fluffy, about 1 minute.
Exchange flat beater to wire whip on speed 10 for 2 to 3 minutes.
Yields 3 cups of potatoes.

title: easy cheese straws
directions: Combine pastry mix, cheese and cayenne pepper in a bowl.
Add 2 tablespoons cold water.
Mix well with a fork. Roll 1/4-inch thick on floured surface. Cut into 2-inch strips.
Place on baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown. Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and milk.
Melt butter and pour into mix. Pour mix over bread that you have lined in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put pineapple on top.
Bake at 350° until brown, 30 to 40 minutes. Good with baked ham.

title: broccoli, cauliflower or mushroom soup
directions: Steam or cook vegetable in very little water, drain, and coarsely chop.
Set aside.
In 2 quart saucepan, saute onions (mushrooms) in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and salt, cook over medium heat until bubbly.
To saucepan, gradually add milk, bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cooked vegetable, stirring constantly until thick.
Sprinkle with parsley or chives on top of each serving.
Add shredded cheese and diced tomatoes for added garnish as desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, soup and Veg-All together.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour in a casserole dish and layer with canned biscuits on top of the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Heat half and half, cheese and margarine over low heat until smooth.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with onion salt and top with grated cheese.
Do not stir.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: roasted chicken
directions: In small bowl, thoroughly combine salt, paprika, cayenne pepper, onion powder, thyme, white pepper, garlic powder and black pepper.
Rub mixture into chicken, inside and out, patting mixture into skin to make sure it is evenly distributed and down deep into skin.

Place in sealable plastic bag, seal and refrigerate overnight. When ready to roast chicken, stuff cavity with onions. Roast, uncovered, at 250° about 5 hours, basting occasionally with pan juice and until chicken is golden brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat
together
butter,
eggs, sugars and vanilla until light and
fluffy.
Add
dry ingredients, blend well.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Drop
from teaspoon onto ungreased sheets, 2 inches apart. Bake
at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except green beans.
Then combine mixture with green beans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: amish chicken and noodles
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove chicken pieces. Bone when cooled.
Chop into small pieces.
Bring liquid back to full boil.
Add noodles and bouillon cubes.
Reduce heat; stir frequently.
When done (15 minutes), add chicken.
Stir well but gently and serve.
Add hot water if too thick.

title: squash relish
directions: Boil for 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Blend all ingredients except spareribs to make sauce.
Pour over ribs and marinate for several hours, or overnight.
Bake at 300°
until meat is tender.
Baste with sauce several times while baking.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir after 15 minutes.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; set aside.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of drippings in skillet.
Cook onion in reserved drippings until tender.
Add pork and beans, Worcestershire, brown sugar, ketchup and mustard.
Turn into 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Stir.
Crumble bacon.
Top beans with bacon.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat strawberries and jello until jello dissolves.
Layer vanilla wafers in bottom of large pan or bowl.
Mix 1 box pudding, half of sour cream, 1 cup Cool Whip and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over wafers just before pudding sets.
Pour half of strawberry mixture over it and swirl slightly.
Repeat procedure and top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Mix cornbread mix, buttermilk, eggs, flour and corn together and set aside.
Brown meat, onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Pour 1/2 of corn bread mix into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spread evenly.
Top with meat mixture; spread evenly.
Top with cheese. Pour remaining corn bread mix over top.
Bake at 350°
for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until tender, approximately 20 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator; peel and chop.
Add all other ingredients that have been prepared; toss together and garnish with paprika.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese. Pour 1/2 of mixture into large heavy greased skillet. Spread cheese over this. Top with balance of mixture. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken bake
directions: Combine 1 cup cheese and remaining ingredients except bread crumbs.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Cover; bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Stir; top with bread crumbs and remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients except powdered sugar.
Roll in small balls.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Roll in a bowl of powdered sugar, very gently, until evenly coated.
Store in airtight container when cooled.

title: onion crescent rolls
directions: Combine onion and water; let stand a few minutes until onion absorbs water.
Add butter.
Open tube of rolls as directed in package.
Spread onion butter on triangles of dough before rolling into crescents.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: In a large bowl combine ingredients.
Serve with gingersnaps, graham crackers, cinnamon graham crackers and/or snickerdoodles.

title: aunt helen's oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend together first 6 ingredients with mixer. Add rest of ingredients to mixture and mix well by hand. Drop on greased cookie sheet by tablespoon. Bake at 300° for 13 to 15 minutes. Cool 2 to 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: eggless chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 inch pan or two- 9 inch layer cake pans. Stir all together and bake for 35 - 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cake
directions: Line your cake pan with waxed paper and bake in a 325° oven for 2 hours.
Let stand 24 hours.
Remove from pan and then wrap in aluminum foil.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with milk, lemon juice and food coloring, if desired.
Pour into pastry shell; bake 30 minutes.
Top with meringue and brown or Cool Whip. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Prep time:
10 minutes.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Mix everything EXCEPT oil and heat to dissolve sugar.
Let cool - add oil and broccoli.
Let set overnight.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, beat the butter, peanut butter, white and brown sugars and the eggs together until the mixture is light and fluffy.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Beat sugar, milk and egg yolks together.
Add lemon juice; beat and pour into pie crust made with vanilla wafers.
Put meringue on top made from egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar. Brown top at 450°.

title: rueben casserole
directions: Spray a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish with Pam.
Break up corned beef and ut in bottom.
Put a dressing over it.
Put drained sauerkraut over corned beef.
Sprinkle bread cubes over top.
Pour remaining dressing over bread cubes and cover with Swiss Cheese.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of the warm water.
Add remaining 1 cup water, sugar and instant potatoes.
Leave mixture out of the refrigerator for 8 to 12 hours, then refrigerate for 3 days.

title: tarragon carrots
directions: Steam carrots in small amount of water until tender.
Add butter.
Sprinkle with fresh tarragon.

title: light and luscious citrus mousse
directions: In medium saucepan, whisk together pudding, milk and egg. Over medium-high heat, bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in rind and juice.
Transfer to medium bowl.
Place plastic wrap directly over surface and refrigerate until cool (about 1 hour).
Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into serving bowls or use a pastry bag to fill hollowed out citrus "shells." Chill thoroughly before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake in greased and floured pan.
(May be baked in a tube pan or three 1 pound coffee cans or in a loaf pan.)
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add the eggs and pulp and mix well.
Add all other ingredients that have been sifted together.

title: rich's magnolia room fruit salad
directions: Place cream cheese in a mixer bowl.
Add confectioners sugar. Blend in mayonnaise.
Add vanilla.
Fold in fruit and marshmallows, gently.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into large paper-lined muffin tins; freeze.
Before serving, take out of freezer about 10 to 15 minutes, but do not allow to become soft. Remove paper liners before serving.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine the zucchini, onions and salt and allow to stand overnight.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Drain again.
Use a large kettle and add the vegetable mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Ladle into jars.
Water bath 5 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place cubed bread in bottom of baking dish. Top with cheese. Brown sausage and drain. Spread over top.
Beat eggs, milk and dry mustard.
Pour over. Refrigerate overnight. Next morning, dilute can of soup with 1/2 can of milk and pour over. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: meat or vegetable filled bread
directions: Mix water and yeast with electric mixer.
When yeast is dissolved, add egg, margarine, salt, sugar and 2 cups flour.
Mix until well blended.
Keep adding flour until you have soft dough. Knead for 6 to 8 minutes on well-floured surface.

title: peanut butter sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan, stir in flour, 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with fork until smooth.
Stir in peanut butter. Spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup brown sugar.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes. Spoon onto dessert plates or cut into squares.
Top with ice cream and spoon sauce over each serving.
Serves 9.

title: pig pickling cake
directions: Mix and beat 2 minutes. Pour into 4 (8-inch) or 3 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans. Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool.

title: mandarin orange fluff dessert
directions: Use no water.
Mix in 2-quart bowl all the ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours before serving or overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Mash and add butter, egg, 1/2 cup cheese, 1/2 of the cracker crumbs and stuffing mix.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cracker crumbs, stuffing mix and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese browns lightly, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Separate eggs.
In boiler, put 2 egg yolks.
Stir in condensed milk and lemon juice until well blended.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar and eggs for 10 minutes.
Add sifted flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add oil slowly and beat. Add vanilla, apples and nuts and mix well by hand (mixture will be thick).
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake cake for about 1 hour or until cake is done.
After cake is finished baking, top with sifted powdered sugar.

title: "frozen pea and bacon salad"
directions: Toss peas, onions and bacon together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add sufficient sour cream to hold together.
This salad is best made one day ahead and kept in refrigerator.
Stir occasionally to mix flavors.

title: french-fry bake
directions: In large saucepan, cook peppers and celery in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add all the milk.
Cook, stirring until bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Add half the cheese, the carrots and pimiento, stirring until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine. Add cheese and soups. Heat over low heat just enough to mix.
Layer rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer broccoli over rice.
Pour cheese sauce over broccoli and heat in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with unrolled crescents.
Spoon sausage and potatoes on top.
Layer Cheddar on top.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper and pour over.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger corn pone pie
directions: Brown meat and onion together; add other ingredients and heat. Make corn bread batter and spread over meat mixture.
Bake at 400° until corn bread is done.

title: luncheon biscuits
directions: Preheat
oven
Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once
and
stir
until dough follows fork around bowl. Place dough on
lightly floured surface, patting out dough to 3/4-inch thick. Use
either
small
biscuit
cutter
(I use a snuff box) or a knife when unique shapes are desired.
Bake at 425° for
to 12	minutes
on
an
ungreased cookie sheet. Yield: 10 tiny biscuits.

title: debbie's ham roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese in
a
small
bowl.
Add
to
cream cheese chopped green
onions, including part of stalks, garlic salt and Season-all.
Mix
together
and spread cheese mixture thin and even over slice
of ham, lengthwise.
Roll up ham and insert 6 to 8 toothpicks.
Slice in between toothpicks.
Makes approximately 80 bite size roll ups.

title: cranberry applesauce
directions: Combine water and sugar in large heavy saucepan and place over high heat.
Cook, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Add apples. Cover and cook, stirring frequently, 5 minutes.
Add cranberries. Cover and cook until apples are very soft and cranberries are popped, 15 to 20 minutes.
Use potato masher or wooden spoon and mash mixture until chunky.
Stir in ginger, cinnamon and lemon zest.
Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Cool, cover and refrigerate.

title: deer burgers
directions: Mix meat with salt and pepper and spread out in a 9-inch pie pan.
Cover with tomatoes and sprinkle on remaining ingredients. Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 20 minutes.
Cut in wedges like pie to serve.
Enough for 2.

title: rainbow salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice, dissolve lemon Jell-O, then add cream cheese.
Blend in blender and chill this.
Mix strawberry and lime Jell-O separately according to directions on box.
Pour in separate 10 x 7-inch pans and chill until thick.
Cut into 1/2-inch squares and mix with cream cheese and lemon Jell-O mixture.
Stir in small amount at a time, stirring after each addition.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion according to package.
Beat egg, soup, margarine and cheese together.
Mix with cooked broccoli and onion.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan, sprayed lightly with Pam.

title: glorified chicken
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Stir in soup.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until done.
Stir often. Makes 4 servings.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Cook potatoes in water for 20 minutes.
Melt margarine in medium saucepan and add flour.
Add onion powder, then pour in milk to make a smooth sauce.
Add cooked potatoes to sauce, water included.
Add salt and cheese.
You may thin the soup with hot water, if desired.

title: burger tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onions.
Drain well.
Put meat in casserole dish, add Tater Tots, soup and milk.
Stir together. Top with grated cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until Tater Tots are done.

title: pauline's pecan pie
directions: If you like pecan pie . . . this is a great recipe!
Cream butter, add sugar and continue to beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, syrup and chopped nuts.
Mix. Pour in pie shell.
Put whole pieces on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cereal delight
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and peanut butter in a large boiler.
Cook until melted and mixed well.
Remove from heat and add the cereal. Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Put the 4 cups plain flour in a large mixing bowl.
Make a hole in the middle by pressing the flour to the side.
Add sugar, eggs, buttermilk with baking soda dissolved in it and shortening. Work with hands until the dough is stiff enough to handle.
Roll to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut and sprinkle with nutmeg, coconut or anything desired.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes about 60 tea cakes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Beat in blender the sugar and evaporated milk.
Add the vinegar, celery seed and salt. Fold in the mayonnaise.
This will keep several weeks if you have more than needed.

title: butterscotch yams
directions: Arrange yams in single layers in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake in 325° oven for 15 minutes.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan combine remaining ingredients, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 5 minutes.
Pour over yams.
Bake, basting frequently 15 minutes longer or until glazed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sue's blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In an 8-inch square baking dish, melt butter. Into a bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg and stir in sugar until well combined. Add milk and whisk batter until it is just combined. Pour batter into melted butter, but do not stir. Pour berries into center of batter, but do not stir. Bake cobbler in middle of oven 40 minutes, or until cake portion is golden and berries exude juice.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix as listed, let set for 1 hour in refrigerator, covered. Bake as needed.
Spoon into greased muffin tin.
Will keep in refrigerator for a week.
I mix mine up at night if I want them for breakfast.

title: hello dolly squares
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Pour condensed milk over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: golden glow pickles
directions: Pour salt over all and let stand 2 hours; drain.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Melt caramels with Pet milk and oleo in a double boiler.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Chill.
Melt Hershey bar and paraffin over low heat in double boiler.
When it has melted dip candy into it.
Place on waxed paper.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Brown sausage in separate pan; drain grease.
Cut tops of peppers off and clean seeds.
When rice is done, add sausage, tomatoes and cheese. Replace tops of peppers, wrap individually with foil and bake until peppers are tender at 450°.

title: colonade frosting
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup and cook to soft boil stage.
Set aside, beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Slowly add hot syrup to beaten egg whites, beating constantly until frosting is creamy.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla and beat to spreading consistency.

title: toffee almond sandies
directions: In mixing bowl cream butter and sugars.
Add oil, eggs and extract.
Mix well.
Combine flours, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and toffee bits.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields about 12 dozen.

title: spanish rice
directions: Peel, wash and dice onion on a chopping board.
Wash, remove the core of seeds, and then dice green peppers on a chopping board.
Measure water in a liquid measuring cup and place the water in a medium saucepan.
Set the saucepan of water on the stovetop, and set the temperature dial to boil.
Measure rice and place the rice in the saucepan of boiling water with salt.
Cover the saucepan with a lid, set the temperature dial to a medium heat, and set the timer for 15 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked crust. Cook at 350° until done.

title: angel bars
directions: Put into a bowl, cut up cherries.
Stir by hand until well blended.
Grease bottom only of a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Pour batter into a pan.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven, or until top begins to brown.
Cool.
Cut into bars or use as a dessert. Serve with cream.

title: pepperidge farm chicken
directions: Mix Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix and Parmesan cheese.
Melt butter.
Roll chicken pieces in butter and then in the mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: tofu loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put 1/4 cup oil in loaf pan, then press mixture into pan.
Bake for about 1 hour.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes before trying to remove from pan.
Garnish with ketchup and parsley.
Also good sliced and fried for sandwiches the next day.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Combine 1/3 cup softened butter,1/4 tsp. garlic powder, 1 tsp. parsley flakes and 1/4 tsp. thyme leaves.
Cut a loaf of Italian bread into 3/4 inch thick slices.
Spread one side of each slice with butter mixture.
Place on baking sheet and broil 5 inches from heat for four minutes or until bread is nicely browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut and boil broccoli.
Mix eggs, soups, onion and cheese together.
Blend in broccoli.
Spread crumbled crackers over top and pour
melted butter over all.
Bake about 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
This is very good!!!

title: marble squares
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Add flour sifted with soda and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread batter kind of thin.
Sprinkle chocolate bits over top.
Put in preheated oven at 350° for 2 minutes.
Remove and use spoon to marbleize bits into batter.
Continue baking for an additional 12 to 14 minutes.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and egg. Mix gradually.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: lemon salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve the gelatin in boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Stir in milk, pineapple with juice, mayonnaise, cottage cheese, nuts and horseradish sauce.
Mix well.
Chill for 6 hours or overnight.
Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: beef marinade
directions: Combine liquids and seasonings.
Pour over beef.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Cook steaks, London broil or roast on grill using marinade as a basting sauce.

title: coconut pie
directions: Blend coconut with milk and let stand.
Cream butter with sugar.
Add 3 slightly beaten eggs, then add coconut and milk. Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Can be served warm or cool topped with whipped cream, Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: those amazing noodles(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Boil water for cup of noodles.
Pour water over noodles.
Let sit until done.
Drain water from tuna fish.
Put into large bowl. Dice the green pepper and onion into fairly small pieces.
Put into bowl.
Before putting in noodles, drain water from them.
Put them into the bowl.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons mayonnaise.
Stir until mixed well.
Add Old Bay; stir.

title: surprise cake
directions: Mix 2 cups flour and 2 cups sugar in mixing bowl; set aside. Cook together 1 stick margarine and shortening, 1 cup water and cocoa.
Let come to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture. Mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, salt, vanilla and soda.
Mix well and pour into cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients together according to instant tea recipe and serve.

title: veg soup from ham bone
directions: Simmer vegetable broth and ham bone at least 4 hours.
Remove meat from bone and add back into broth.
Cool soup overnight in refrigerator and in the morning, remove cooled fat on top.
Reheat soup until hot and add your choice of noodles.
I like Kluski noodles.
Enjoy!

title: delightfully cherry
directions: Dissolve 1 package of gelatin in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup ice cubes and stir until gelatin starts to thicken (2 to 3 minutes).
Remove unmelted ice and stir in cherries.
Pour into 5-cup mold and chill.

title: chocolate angel strata
directions: Beat together egg whites, vinegar, salt and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon until soft mounds form.
Add 1/2 cup sugar gradually, beating until meringue stands in stiff, glossy peaks.
Spread on bottom and sides of pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool.
In bowl, combine egg yolks with water and melted chocolate.
Spread 3 tablespoons over cooled meringue.
Chill the remainder.

title: mona's best ever brownies
directions: In medium saucepan, melt margarine and chocolate.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar.
Cool slightly.
Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan (greased).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with a butter icing and cut into squares.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until creamy.
Add oil and vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients, sifted.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients. Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves or 1 loaf and 16 cupcakes.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Mix oleo and sugar.
Add vanilla and flour.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: delicious cornbread
directions: Mix together.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch open casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour or until slightly brown on top.

title: parmesan pepper rolls
directions: Mix 1 1/4 cups flour, the sugar, cheese, salt, pepper and yeast in large bowl.
Beat in water, egg whites and oil until smooth. Stir in remaining flour until smooth.
Scrape batter from side of bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place about 30 minutes or until double.
Spray 12 medium muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inches, with nonstick cooking spray.
Stir down batter, beating about 25 strokes.
Divide among muffin cups.
Let rise, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes or until batter rounds over tops of cups.
Heat oven to 400° and bake 15 minute to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 12 rolls.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, peanut butter, coconut, crumbs, vanilla and nuts.
Pinch off and roll into a ball and dip in chocolate.
Place on wax paper to harden.

title: ham casserole
directions: Wipe ham with damp cloth.
Cut ham into 1-inch squares. Peel, slice and wash potatoes.
Alternate a layer
of
ham and potatoes. Sprinkle each layer with onion, green pepper, white pepper
and cheese; dot with butter.
Mix
water
and
tomato sauce; pour over layers.
Cover and cook at	375°
for
1/2 hours.
Top with cheese last few minutes of cooking time.

title: shrimp melange
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen.
Cook artichokes according to package directions; drain.
Set aside.
For cheese sauce, in medium saucepan combine cornstarch, 1/2 tsp. paprika, 1/2 tsp. salt, and dash pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in wine; heat through.
Stir Swiss cheese into sauce till melted.
Set aside.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar, let stand overnight.
The next day: Boil rhubarb and sugar mixture 10 minutes. Remove from heat and add jello, stir until dissolved. Put into jars and refrigerate. Can be frozen.

title: noodle burger casserole
directions: Brown onion in bacon drippings.
Add ground beef and brown. Add tomato soup, water, uncooked noodles, salt and pepper.
Cook until noodles are tender.
Add corn.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix and cook in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with cheese, if desired. Brown in oven.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Add eggs and salt to flour and mix thoroughly with your hands. Add water 1 teaspoon at a time until dough forms a ball.
Knead on a floured board or counter until smooth (10 minutes).
Cover and let stand for 10 minutes.
Divide in 4 parts.
Roll dough one part at a time (keep others covered) on a floured board to desired thickness.
Cut noodles to desired width.
Let dry on a towel, about 2 hours.
When dry, break into smaller pieces.
Cook as desired until tender (12 to 15 minutes).

title: creamy cucumbers
directions: Mix all seasoning ingredients with sour cream.
Pour over sliced cucumbers and chill until ready to serve.

title: tomato-cheese salad
directions: Arrange 3 tomato slices on each of 6 salad plates.
Drizzle with dressing.
Sprinkle with cheese and onions.

title: skinny fruit dip
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender or food processor fitted with a steel blade.
Process until smooth and creamy.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Yield: About 1 1/3 cups of dip.

title: patriotic cake(easy, delicious and pretty)
directions: Use your favorite white cake recipe or use 1 white cake mix and bake according to instructions in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Poke holes in the cake with a toothpick, fork tines, etc.

title: comfort molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until smooth.
Add egg and molasses. Mix until smooth.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cut in half for 2 people.

title: squash corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: she crab soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, stirring constantly until bubbly. Stir for one minute after bubbly.
Stir in half and half. Continue stirring until thick and bubbly.
Add vegetable bouillon cubes, celery leaves, pepper and Tabasco.
Fold in crabmeat.
Thin with milk if necessary.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage until done, stirring to crumble well; drain and set aside.
Butter each slice of bread; cut into cubes.
Place cubes in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sausage.
Top with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat well and pour over mixture in baking pan.
Chill at least 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 generously.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt 1/2 cup sugar in iron skillet, stirring constantly.
Beat egg slightly.
To egg, add balance of sugar, butter and milk. Cook slowly until reaches boiling point.
Add browned sugar while mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; let cool and beat until right consistency to spread.
Makes enough for filling and icing for two layer cake.

title: summer special
directions: Shake well with ice.
Serve with slice of orange and piece of mint.
Serves 1.

title: salted nut squares
directions: Place 1/2 of peanuts, which have been divided, in an ungreased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, melt butter and peanut butter chips over low heat.
Add milk and marshmallows. Cook and stir until melted.
Pour over peanuts.
Sprinkle the remaining peanuts over top.
Cover and refrigerate.
Cut into bars.

title: gumbo
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove chicken from broth to cool. Continue cooking broth.
Add next 8 ingredients in order as you prepare them.
Dice and add chicken.
Add frozen okra.
Cook on low for approximately 1 hour.

title: squash casserole with potatoes
directions: Cook squash, potatoes, onion and margarine in thick skillet until done.
Cook slowly until done.
Butter baking dish. Sprinkle lightly with Ritz cracker crumbs in bottom of dish, another layer of Ritz cracker crumbs, then layer of cheese slices on top.
Put squash casserole into oven to melt cheese.

title: tabbouleh(middle eastern salad)
directions: Wash burghul.
Drain and place in a large bowl.
Squeeze out moisture by cupping your hands and squeezing.
Add all chopped vegetables and mix well.
Add oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper. (It's a long process, but chop the vegetables as fine as possible for the more true Tabbouleh.)
Allow burghul to soak and absorb the juice (about 1 hour).
Serve over fresh green lettuce.
Eat with lettuce leaves, tender grape leaves or with a fork.
Makes a refreshing appetizer or a picnic salad.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Stir together the whole egg, egg yolk, sugar, mustard and cornstarch.
In saucepan, bring to boil the water, salt and vinegar.
Stir in the egg mixture.
Cook for 1 minute until thickened.
Remove from heat, add butter and mayonnaise.
Chill for 1 hour.
Then add to the broccoli-cauliflower mixture.

title: pepper steak
directions: Melt oleo; sprinkle beef with garlic powder and saute; stir until brown.
Remove meat and add onion and green peppers.
Saute 2 minutes.
Return meat to skillet along with tomatoes and beef cubes and simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Blend together cornstarch, sugar, soy sauce and water.
Add to meat mixture and cook
until thick.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Mix in oatmeal, cocoa, coconut and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper while still hot.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Put in crock pot and add V-8 juice, tomatoes, okra, mixed vegetables, salt, and pepper. Add a dash of Tabasco and cook all day on low.
Add macaroni 30 minutes before serving.

title: pork chops with pepper slice rings(electric skillet meal)
directions: Heat fat to 360°.
Brown chops on both sides.
Place onion and pepper rings on each chop.
Fill rings with uncooked rice.
Pour tomatoes around chops.
Add celery and seasoning.
Reduce temperature to 240°.
Cook, covered, for 50 minutes.
Keep hot on warm.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together very well with mixer.
Pour into Bundt pan that is well-greased.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour in oven.
Check with toothpick for doneness. Freezes very well.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in milk on a double boiler. Add nuts and cherries and fold in whipped cream. Freeze until mushy, then beat well. Freeze again until firm. Serves 6 to 8.

title: big mikes chili
directions: Cook beef and onions together in 3-qt saucepan until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain grease.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Heat to a boil.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over bowl.
Enjoy!

title: roquefort cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses together with mixer, then add other ingredients except pecans. Mix well. Shape into two small or one large ball. Roll in finely chopped pecans. Chill and serve.

title: cheese blintzes
directions: Mix sugar, cream cheese and egg yolks until creamy.
Cut crusts off bread and roll until flat.
Spread cream cheese mixture on each slice of bread and roll up.
Melt butter.
Roll each blintz in butter and then in sugar-cinnamon mix.
Place on cookie sheet and put in freezer for 1 hour.
Bake 15 minutes in 400° oven.
These can be stored in freezer and baked as needed.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bake as directed on box.
Combine tomatoes, onion, sweet pickle relish and bacon.
Begin with a layer of veggies, then a layer of crumbled corn bread.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Mix mayonnaise, dill pickle and juice. Pour over salad before serving.
Makes a large bowl of salad.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, flour, salt and spices. Next add pumpkin, Karo, milk, butter and coconut. Pour into unbaked pie shell (9-inch). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. This makes 2 pies.

title: cabbage roll casserole(fast and easy!)
directions: Put cabbage in bottom of large casserole to cover bottom; can also use a roast pan.
Put a layer of ground meat to cover cabbage.
Top with onion.
Season to taste.
Pour rice over meat evenly.
Pour tomato soup (or sauce) over rice, covering rice completely.
Pour can of water around edges.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be doubled and tripled for large crowds.

title: watergate salad
directions: Cool about 1 hour before serving.

title: shauna's knock 'em dead
directions: Place 1/2 of wafers on bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cream together butter and powdered sugar.
Add egg and beat until light and creamy.
Spread over crumbs.
Whip whipping cream and then add nuts, pineapple and cherries.
Spread over crust.
Add remaining crumbs to top and let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
This may be doubled and a 9 x 13-inch pan used.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and cut off stems and chop.
Saute chopped stems and onions in margarine for about 10 minutes.
In the blender, 2 slices bread, garlic salt and oregano.
In a bowl, add mushroom mix to bread crumbs.
Add enough bouillon to moisten mixture.
Add salt and pepper.
Fill mushroom caps in baking dish. Top with cheese and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: beef and mushrooms
directions: Cut sirloin steak into strips.
Brown strips in oil.
Add onion and garlic powder and cook until onion is tender.
Add soy sauce, beef bouillon, mushrooms and 2 cups of water.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender (approximately 40 minutes).
Combine remaining water and cornstarch.
Add to meat mixture and stir until thickened.
