Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook ground beef until done; drain.
Put meat in bottom of baking dish.
Layer vegetables over meat mixture.
Spoon mashed potatoes over meat and vegetables.
Mix part of the cheese into potatoes.
Sprinkle the rest on top.
Bake at 350° until browned on top.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put the pineapple with juice in bowl.
Stir in pudding until well mixed.
Stir in whipped topping, nuts, marshmallows and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon christmas cake
directions: Separate egg yolk from white.
Cream butter, egg yolks and sugar; add 2 cups flour.
Beat well.
Add lemon flavor in another large bowl.
Add cherries, pineapple and nuts; mix well.
Beat egg whites.
Fold in the remaining 2 cups flour.
Then combine all together.
Put in 325° oven for 1 hour, then turn oven to 250° for another hour or until cake is golden brown.
Cook in a tube pan.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together all ingredients except nuts.
Mix well until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In
a
quart glass bowl, stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook for 8 minutes on High; stir after 4 minutes. Stir
in butter and vanilla extract.
Cook on High for 2 minutes. Add soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto lightly
greased
cookie
sheet.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli as package indicates, omitting salt. Drain well.
Place broccoli in oblong dish.
Heat soup and shredded cheese.
Gradually add milk, mayonnaise and beaten egg to soup mixture, stirring until well blended.
Pour over broccoli. Combine bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle over mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tomato coleslaw
directions: Trim and core cabbage; shred.
Combine in a large bowl with carrots, peppers and onion.
Dice 2 tomatoes; add to cabbage. Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, celery seed, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Blend well.
Pour over cabbage; toss, cover and refrigerate several hours.
Slice 2 tomatoes and put on top.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In 9 or 10-inch skillet heat margarine and oil together until margarine is bubbly and mixture is hot; add chicken and saute, stirring frequently, until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.

Add peppers, onion, mushrooms and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 5 minutes. In blender container combine pineapple, ketchup, sugar, vinegar and broth mix and process until pureed, scraping down sides of container as necessary.

Pour pureed mixture over chicken and vegetables in skillet and stir to combine; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; add tomato and scallions, stir to combine, and cook until flavors blend, about 5 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Cook and stir onion in butter in 2-quart saucepan until onion is tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in half and half and 1 1/2 cups of the cheese. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute. Place potatoes in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Pour cheese sauce on potatoes. Bake, uncovered, until top is brown and bubbly, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti in boiling water following directions on box. Drain.

title: chocolate custard
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs, milk and cocoa.
Cook in top of double boiler over hot water until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool. Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shells.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine cornbread mix and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs, milk and oil, mixing well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: eggnog bread
directions: Mix egg, eggnog and butter.
Sift in dry ingredients; stir in pecans and fruit.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham chowder
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil and cook 10 minutes. Do not drain. In a small saucepan, melt butter and add flour; stir until smooth. Add milk and heat thoroughly. Combine this mixture with potato mixture and stir well. Add cheese and ham. Slowly simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: leroy's slaw
directions: Add sauce immediately before serving slaw.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs; stir in applesauce and water. Stir in dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 35 minutes or until tested done. Can be iced with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer cooked fryer pieces in pan.
Layer boiled eggs over chicken and salt and pepper.
Mix chicken broth and pour over chicken.
Mix flour, margarine and milk.
Pour over chicken and first mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: fruity rice salad
directions: If using navel orange, peel and section it, then cut sections into bite-sized pieces.
Combine rice, fruit, peppers and almonds. In small bowl, whisk together salad oil, seasoned rice vinegar, cinnamon, lime juice and honey; pour over rice mixture and gently stir.
Chill.
Serve with honey-mustard dressing.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Add topping.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening, 1 cup sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat hard.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Make into small balls about the size of a walnut; roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: summer sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small deep bowl.
Cover and leave at room temperature until ready to use.
Cook your favorite pasta (either spaghetti, linguini or angel hair) al dente.
Drain and pour some sauce on the bottom of a serving dish; place pasta over that.
Sprinkle with Romano cheese and top with more sauce.

title: potato candy(peanut butter swirls)
directions: Boil several small potato cubes in pan until tender.
In small mixing bowl, put a cup of confectioners sugar and a piece of potato to the side.
Slowly mashing and stirring, mix the potato with a little of the sugar at a time.
The potato should "melt" into a liquid which mixes well with confectioners sugar.
Keep adding little pieces of potato until all is mixed into a ball. Knead the ball with confectioners sugar on your hands.
On wax paper, roll out dough with rolling pin until as long and flat as it gets.
Spread thin layer of peanut butter all over rolled out dough.
Roll into a tube-like shape.
Cut and keep refrigerated.

title: melba-cheese snack
directions: Spread an equal amount of cheese on each Melba round.
Top each with pimento strip or a caper.
Yields 2 servings.

title: brown's mulligan
directions: Boil okra until soft, drain, rinse with cold water.
Combine onions and oil and saute until brown, drain onions.
Combine onions, okra, tomato juice in same skillet.
Cook for 10 minutes to thicken.

title: easy fudge
directions: Butter square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Heat milk, chips and square of chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir nuts in and vanilla.
Spread in pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes 64 squares.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in top half of double boiler.
Cool slightly.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Form into log roll.
Put on wax paper and chill.
Cut into slices.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Put in a greased 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish or pan. Cook approximately 30 minutes in 400° preheated oven.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 2 round pans.
Cool. Using a 6-quart punch bowl, place 1 cake layer (broken) in bowl. Add 1/2 of each of the other ingredients in this order:
pudding, bananas, pie filling, fruit cocktail, pineapple, nuts, coconut and Cool Whip.
Repeat layers; chill.
Decorate with maraschino cherries and nuts, if desired.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Butter sides and bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Melt oleo in medium size saucepan. Blend in flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens slightly.

title: creamy tomato aspic
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Heat tomato sauce to boiling. Dissolve softened gelatin in it.
Stir in all remaining ingredients, except celery.
Chill until mixture thickens.
Fold in celery.
Turn into individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crab cakes
directions: Break bread in small pieces and moisten with a little milk. Mix together and shape into cakes.
Fry quickly, until brown.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Spread pineapple in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over top of pineapple.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: golden potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on.
Peel after potatoes have cooled, then grate them.
Melt butter, pour over grated potatoes.
Add sour cream, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix all well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: light oriental ginger dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar with tight-fitting lid.
Cover and shake vigorously until combined.
Chill and shake again before serving.
Serve over green salad, chicken salad or pasta salad. Makes 4 servings.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package and drain.
Melt 1 1/2 Tbsp. butter in a heavy saucepan.
Blend in flour, stir in milk slowly, and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Add seasonings and cheese, stirring until cheese is melted.
Add macaroni and transfer to a buttered 1 qt. casserole or individual casseroles.
Combined bread crumbs and 1 Tbsp. melted butter. Sprinkle over macaroni.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Prepare a pie shell of crescent rolls.
Spread with mustard. In a skillet over moderate heat, cook the zucchini and onion in margarine for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture into the pie shell and bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes, or until center is set.
Cover crust with foil during the last 10 minutes of baking.
Allow to stand for 20 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine vanilla, margarine, milk and cocoa.
Add confectioners sugar until creamy.

title: so easy sugar cookies
directions: Dissolve baking soda in warm water.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: fajitas
directions: Grate 1 tablespoon orange peel and 2 teaspoons lemon peel.
Set aside.
Squeeze orange to get 1/4 cup juice and lemons to get 1/4 cup juice.
In shallow pan, place orange and lemon peel, orange and lemon juice, pineapple juice, wine, water, soy sauce, garlic, black pepper, chilies and butter.
Stir well.
Place skirt steaks in marinade; turn to coat.
Cover with plastic wrap and let stand at room temperature for 2 hours (no longer).
Grill steaks 3 inches above coals for 5 to 6 minutes on each side.
Cut crosswise in finger length strips.
Serve with hot flour tortillas.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Fry chicken in oil until brown. Add lemon pepper, soy sauce, and white vinegar. Simmer for 5 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: macaroni tuna salad
directions: Boil macaroni as directed.
Drain and cool.
Add tuna and onion.
Mix in salad dressing and salt.
Mix thoroughly.

title: nut brown buttermilk bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg; add sugar and mix well.
Stir in buttermilk and butter.
Blend in dry ingredients quickly, just until moistened.
Add nuts.
Pour batter into a buttered loaf pan 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 3/4-inches.
Bake in a preheated oven to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done in the center.
Remove from pan and cool on cake rack.
Makes one loaf.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Mix the flour, Crisco and milk together to form dough.
Mix with hands and divide into 4 parts.
Roll 2 parts out to fit 2 cookie sheets.
Cover dough with half of the pineapple mixture.
Roll remaining dough out for top crusts.
Prick with fork all over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light brown.
Cool and frost.

title: chop suey
directions: Make stock with water, soy sauce and bouillon cubes. Add stock to browned meat. Simmer for at least 1/2 hour.
Add chop suey vegetables. Serve over rice. Basic chop suey recipe freezes well.

title: date and nut bars
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add gradually 1/2 cup sugar, beating well.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
After adding dry ingredients, add dates and nuts; beat well.
Spread evenly in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut into 2 1/2 x 1-inch bars.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: Bring the sugar, milk, cocoa and vanilla to a boil in a heavy saucepan. Boil for 1 minute.
Pour hot mixture over oatmeal and chopped nuts.
Stir until well blended. Drop from the teaspoonful into powdered sugar and roll while still hot.
Place on wax paper until cookies harden.

title: cheesy garlic biscuits
directions: Mix together the dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add cheese.
Make a well in the center; add milk.
Stir just until dough clings together.
Knead gently on a lightly floured surface for 10 to 12 strokes.
Roll or pat into 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into biscuits and transfer to an ungreased baking sheet.
Top with mixture of 3 tablespoons melted butter, 1/4 cup of Parmesan cheese and 1 teaspoon powdered garlic.
Brush over tops of biscuits and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Melt margarine. Saute onions and peppers in margarine. Take out and set aside. Brown meat in skillet. Add onion and pepper. Salt and pepper to taste. Pour over shredded cabbage in casserole dish. Spoon tomato soup over top. Cover and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: luncheon salad
directions: Heat soup, add gelatine softened in cold water.
Cool.
Add cheese that has been mashed up with fork.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Chill until firm.
Good with Ritz crackers.

title: simple sangria
directions: Combine both juices.
Add red wine if desired.
Place one slice of orange, lemon and lime in each glass.
Add two cherries to each glass and fill with cracked ice.
Pour juice mixture over cracked ice.
Serve immediately.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Moisten oats with milk before adding.
Turn
into
loaf
pan
sprayed
with
nonstick coating and lay the bacon
slices on top.
Bake 1 3/4 hours in a moderate oven (350°).

title: pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour melted margarine in 11 x 7 x 2-inch or 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Toss spaghetti in margarine.
Cover spaghetti with 1 can tomato sauce.
Add in order given: 1/2 Swiss cheese, 1/2 pepperoni, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and all of mushrooms (optional), then sprinkle with oregano and basil.
Top with remaining Swiss cheese, pepperoni, 1 can tomato sauce and finally Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set overnight.

title: white a la king
directions: Saute chopped green pepper in margarine.
Add Fri Chik, mushroom soup, pimentos, peas and add milk.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over biscuits or croissants.

title: lemon herb beef pot roast
directions: Combine garlic, lemon pepper and 1 teaspoon basil; press evenly into surface of beef.
In Dutch oven, heat oil over medium-high heat until hot.
Brown beef evenly.
Pour off drippings.
Add 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil;
reduce heat to low.
Cover tightly; simmer 2 hours.
Add vegetables; cover and continue cooking 40 to 45 minutes or until beef and vegetables are tender.
Remove beef and vegetables.
Skim fat from cooking liquid.
Stir in cornstarch mixture and 1/2 teaspoon basil.
Bring to a boil;
cook and stir until thickened.
Serve with pot roast and vegetables.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, making two 9-inch layers.
When completely cool, split both layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Blend well.
Chill.
Reserve 1 cup mixture.
Spread between layers of cake.
Combine reserved mixture with Cool Whip and blend until smooth.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Seal in airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days before serving.
Will keep many more days, if it has the chance!

title: sour cream dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Refrigerate overnight to blend. Serve with veggies.

title: pork chop-potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops.
Put potatoes in square baking pan.
Put pork chops on top of potatoes.
Mix together soup, water and sour cream.
Pour over pork chops.
Cover and seal with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together salt, soda, baking powder and flour and add to the sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla mixture.
Add oats and chocolate chips. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Bake desired amount of chicken breasts for about 20 minutes. Top with cheese, onions and tomatoes.
Bake until cheese is melted.
Serve with rice and steamed veggies.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine and refrigerate until chilled.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in salted water.
Mash and add butter, milk and eggs.
Fold in cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dip for corn chips
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with corn chips.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and spread in 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Mix flour, butter and sugar as for pie crust.
Put on top and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: martin's gazpacho
directions: In a large blender, combine tomato, 1/2 cucumber, 1/2 onion, 1/4 green bell pepper and 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Puree.

title: layered chicken salad
directions: Layer chicken, celery, onions, almonds and eggs.
Mix mayonnaise, soups and seasonings in greased casserole pan.
Cover with potato chips.
Bake at 350° until bubbling and browned.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Twenty-four hours before serving, remove crust from bread; cube bread (older bread is better).
In a mixing bowl, mix all other ingredients.
In a buttered casserole dish (9 x 13-inch), layer bread, meat and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator.
Bring to room temperature. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Test for completion.

title: doughnut drops
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook for 1/2 minute.
Drain.
Sugar or glaze.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook to a soft-ball stage. Remove from heat and add 1/3 cup creamy peanut butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Beat with mixer until thick. Pour into 8-inch buttered pan. Let cool; serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and set aside.
Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper together.
Drain off grease.
Add tomatoes and catsup; simmer for 15 minutes.
Put a layer of macaroni, layer of ground beef, then layer with cheese.
Put in oven at 350° long enough to melt cheese, about 15 minutes.

title: bavarian kielbasa with noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook kielbasa and onion until browned, stirring often.
Spoon off fat.
Add soup; stir until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Add beans and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook 5 minutes or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir cooked noodles into skillet.
Heat 2 minutes, stirring often. Serve with mustard, if desired (spicy brown mustard or French mustard).
Makes 4 servings.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: creamy braised veal shank
directions: Curry and vinegar are the surprise ingredients in this otherwise classic dish.
The browned strips of liver are served on sauteed onion rings and topped with bacon and parsley.

title: emily's butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla, flour, dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake in 8 inch greased square pan
at 325 degrees for 25-30 minutes.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Combine mushroom and chicken soups, tomatoes and cheese in microwave-safe bowl. Microwave the mixture until the cheese has melted. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer cooked noodles, chicken and cheese mixture. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream apple chicken
directions: In a large skillet, cook chicken in oil over medium heat until browned and no longer pink inside.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Add apples, juice, onion, basil and salt to the skillet; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until apples are tender.
Combine sour cream and flour; add to skillet.
Stir and cook until sauce is warm (do not boil).
Arrange noodles on a serving platter.
Top with chicken.
Spoon apple sauce over all. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef, onions, garlic and oregano.
Add soup, water and vinegar.
Simmer 30 minutes.
In a 12 x 8-inch casserole, layer cooked macaroni, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Repeat.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Place stewed tomatoes in casserole-type dish.
Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons sugar; mix together.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes. Remove and place bread, torn into 1-inch pieces, on top.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 teaspoons sugar and dot with butter.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: slush
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes, then cool.
Add juices and gin or bourbon, then freeze.
When ready to serve, fill glass half full with slush, then fill up with 7-Up or Squirt.

title: fruit slush
directions: Over heat, dissolve sugar with 1 cup water.
Combine everything and freeze.
Serve slushy.
Can be refrozen.

title: lemon pie
directions: Bake in pie crust 8 minutes at 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread on pie and brown in oven.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar in a large bowl.
Blend in 1 egg at a time until well blended.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix and add to chocolate mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Roll into balls and then roll in confectioners sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: best ever caramel corn
directions: Spray one large paper bag with Pam.
Put popcorn in bag.
In bowl, mix margarine, syrup and sugar.
Heat 4 minutes on High in microwave.
Add vanilla and soda; beat with whisk until it turns light and foamy.
Pour over popcorn and shake.
Poke holes in bag with fork and fold top of bag over and close tightly.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and shake.
Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes again; remove and shake.
Microwave for 30 seconds; remove and shake.
Microwave for 30 seconds; remove and shake.
Bag will be hot!
Pour out onto waxed paper and cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell. Bake for about 1 hour.
Test for doneness by shaking pie plate. (Middle should shake a little.)
Don't overbake.

title: carrot slaw
directions: Add small amount of oil to grated carrots.
Stir; add raspberry vinegar and small amount of pepper.
Chill and serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Smooth refried beans across bottom of baking dish.
Follow by mayonnaise and sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over top. Cover with scallions, olives and tomatoes.
May serve as is or bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Serve with nachos.

title: shrimp scampi(makes 4 servings)
directions: In skillet, combine butter, garlic and parsley.
Melt butter and set aside.
Cook linguine.
As linguine is cooking, prepare shrimp.
Bring 3 quarts of water to a boil.
Add unpeeled shrimp. Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Drain and peel.
Saute shrimp in hot skillet for 2 to 3 minutes. Serve over linguine.

title: fish soup
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Stir in tomato juice, water, bouillon cubes and oregano.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add lobster, crab and shrimp.
(Serves 6-8.)

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Save 1 cup of the flour to dust the fruit.
Cream the butter or margarine and sugar.
Add 1 teaspoon lemon.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour gradually, then the fruit and nuts. Pour into cake or bread pans, well-greased.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature.
Mix chili peppers in and spread on flour tortillas and roll.
Place in plastic container and refrigerate until ready to serve.
(They can be made several days ahead.)
Slice and serve with salsa for dipping.

title: coconut sour cream layer cake(3 day cake)
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
When layers are completely cooled, split both of them and make four layers. Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut, blending well; chill. Reserve 1 cup of sour cream mixture for frosting.
Spread remaining between layers.
Combine the one cup of sour cream with whipped topping, blending smoothly.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Seal cake in airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add unbeaten egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well after each one is added.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add to mixture, alternating with the milk. Add vanilla.
Last, fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a slow oven at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil noodles and set aside.
Cut up Velveeta cheese into small pieces.
Cut up margarine.
Pour milk over cheese and margarine. Microwave on High until melted (about 4 minutes).
Pour noodles into baking dish, then melted cheese.
Add salt to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken fingers
directions: Cut each chicken breast into 3 to 4 fingers.
In large bowl, combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt, pepper and parsley.
Saute garlic in butter.
Remove from heat.
Add chicken fingers.
Allow to set 3 minutes.
Dip chicken in bread crumbs and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top chicken with remaining bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and cover loosely with foil.
Serve hot or cold.

title: pineapple-cherry dump cake
directions: Pour undrained pineapple into a buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Pour cherry pie filling over this and sprinkle cake mix over top. Sprinkle nuts and coconut over this.
Cut margarine into thin patties and arrange on top.
Bake at 350° in oven for 35 minutes or until done.
(Check cake at 35 minutes; if not done, continue to 45 minutes.)
This recipe will serve 10 people.

title: homemade sausage recipe
directions: Mix and package or freeze.

title: fat-free pineapple dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch microwave dish.
Mix 1/2 box of cake mix into the crushed pineapple.
Microwave on High for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove, sprinkle ground cinnamon on top.
Serve warm with fat-free ice cream or serve cold.

title: rumaki appetizer
directions: Wash chicken livers and cut in half.
In a large bowl, put the chicken livers and teriyaki to soak overnight.
Cover bowl.
Set bacon out to become room temperature before cooking.
Take 1 strip of bacon, put a chicken liver and water chestnut on top and wrap, securing it with a toothpick, then roll it in brown sugar.
Place in a baking pan.
Set oven on broil, 400°.
Cook until bacon is crisp, about 10 minutes.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add taco seasoning and beans.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup together; set aside.
Line bottom of pan with tortillas.
Put half of sour cream mixture next; add meat. Cover with tortillas, then put rest of sour cream mixture over tortillas.
Put cheese on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and sauce.

title: creamy citrus mayonnaise
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours. Yields 7/8 cup.

title: easy homemade soup
directions: Slice steak into bite sized pieces.
(Note:
Whole steak is much cheaper than buying stew beef already cut.) Combine ingredients in pressure cooker.
Cook under pressure for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with corn cakes.

title: salmon macaroni salad
directions: Mix all together and chill before serving.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown beef; pour off excess fat.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Chop onions (tops and all).
Mix with cream cheese and sour cream.
Cook noodles and drain.
Layer noodles in Pyrex dish.
Add layer of meat sauce, then layer of cheese mixture until all is used.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine in saucepan; bring to boil. Cook 2 minutes, then remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Drop onto waxed paper.

title: orange julius
directions: Using blender, mix all of the ingredients and then add some ice in the blender to crush up and serve immediately.

title: round steak-potato casserole
directions: Cut steak into small bite size.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Dredge in flour.
Brown in fat. Alternate layers of steak, potatoes and onion in a covered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange cream cheese frosting
directions: Put cream cheese and margarine into a medium size mixing bowl. Cream together until they are soft and fluffy by rubbing them against the side of the bowl with back of a spoon.
Beat in the confectioners sugar until well blended.
Beat in vanilla and orange rind.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Stir together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easter braid
directions: Soften active dry yeast in warm water, compressed yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine milk, sugar, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in about 2 cups of flour; add eggs and mix well. Stir in softened yeast.
Add lemon peel, mace, the raisins and remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Let rest 10 minutes. Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Place in lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add egg and beat until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and orange peel.
Mix well.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring
ingredients to a boil; pour over popcorn.
Bake in oven at 250° for 1/2 hour.

title: baked beans-n-bacon
directions: Cook onions and pepper in bacon fat until tender.
Add and stir remaining ingredients.
Put into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cocoa pie
directions: Separate eggs; use whites for meringue.
Mix all ingredients and cook for 5 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add taco and dressing mixes.
Add remaining ingredients and heat.
Serve over corn chips and cheese.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put beans in ovenproof dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Pour mushroom soup on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Top with onion rings; bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: fruit avocado dressing
directions: Put all ingredients, except oil, in blender and beat on low for 1 minute.
Gradually add oil until thickened.
This is delicious over a tender lettuce like Boston, grapefruit sections and avocado.

title: best frosting ever
directions: Mix all together and beat well.
Will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well and blend flour and sugar; add all other ingredients
and
blend into eggs.	Pour into a buttered Pyrex dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: banana-nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2 inches. Beat sugar, bananas, oil and eggs in large bowl. Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt. Stir in nuts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer 1/2 the stuffing in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place the chicken on top.
Pour the celery soup over the chicken.
Pour the chicken soup over the celery soup.
Pour the milk over the chicken soup.
Cover with the other half of the stuffing.
Pour 2 cups of the chicken broth on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix zucchini, oil, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder, eggs, vanilla, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Add flour and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over pork chops and bake for 2 hours at 375°.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut meat in 1-inch squares.
Cut all vegetables in good size pieces.
Place all vegetables and meat in roasting pan.
Mix tapioca with tomato juice and pour over ingredients.
Cook in a 250° oven for 5 hours.

title: mom's bread or rolls
directions: Combine yeast and water.
Let stand until yeast is dissolved. Add sugar, salt and shortening and blend.
Stir in flour and mix. Make into a round ball and put in greased large pan or bowl.
Let raise three times, kneading each time.
Divide dough; shape into rolls or loaves.
Let rise double, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake bread at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Bake rolls at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheddar parmesan potatoes
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine over low heat.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk; cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Remove from the heat.
Add the salt, Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Add potatoes; stir gently to mix.
Place in a greased 2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: easy recipe white bread
directions: Mix thoroughly 3 cups of flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Add the butter.
Gradually add the water.
Beat 2 minutes with a mixer on medium speed.
Add 1/2 cup of flour and beat 2 minutes on high. Stir in enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn onto a floured board and knead 10 to 12 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Cover with plastic wrap and a towel and let set for 20 minutes.
Divide in half and shape into loaves.
Put into buttered loaf pans.
Brush tops of the loaves with oil.
Cover with plastic wrap and a towel and refrigerate 2 to 12 hours (rises in the refrigerator).
Remove from the refrigerator and let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until it sounds hollow when tapped.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Pour sugars, milk and syrup in pan; stir until it starts to boil.
Turn down on medium heat.
Cover and let cook three minutes.
Take off stove, cool.
Stir in butter and vanilla.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Stir asparagus, boiled eggs, soup and milk together and put in casserole dish.
Place cracker crumbs on top.
Pour oleo over crumbs.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box but use milk instead of water.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bring to a boil, the crushed pineapple and sugar.
When cake is done, punch holes in it and pour pineapple mixture over hot cake.
Let set until almost cool. Mix pudding according to package instructions, mix in mixer with cream cheese and spread over cake.
Next, slice bananas on cake then spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans, cherries and coconut.

title: ann's easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13 pan; mix flour, sugar, milk, baking powder and dash of salt.
Pour into pan and spoon fruit and juice over batter.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: dalena's shorty annie
directions: Brown hamburger, pepper and onion.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with cornbread or crackers. Parmesan cheese added on top of individual bowls is good also.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Place an apple in each crescent roll and sprinkle with cinnamon and roll up. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over rolls. Sprinkle cinnamon over top and bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: In a large bowl combine the cornmeal, flour, garlic powder and cayenne together. Pour the buttermilk into a separate bowl and season with salt and pepper. Dip the tomatoes in the buttermilk and then dredge them in the cornmeal mixture, coating both sides.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Toss together bread crumbs and pineapple chunks and place in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be made up and refrigerated overnight.
Good with ham.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Cut cake in slices to cover bottom of pan.
Add fruits on top.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil; cool and drizzle over.

title: asian salad
directions: Over low heat, brown noodles, almonds, and sesame seeds with butter.
Once browned take off heat to cool.
In a small saucepan bring vegetable oil, sugar, and vinegar to boil for 1 minute. Cool.
Add soy sauce.
In large bowl, combine cabbage & green onions.
Add noodle mixture and soy sauce mixture.
Toss to coat.

title: turkey-italian style
directions: Place turkey in casserole dish.
Cover with cheese and top with Italian tomato soup from can.
Garnish as desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Grind each vegetable, one at a time, in blender or food processor.
Drain well.
Mix vegetables with sour cream and lemon juice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Makes about 60 small sandwiches.

title: fudge icing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil; boil at medium for 3 minutes.
Add 1 box powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Ice cake that is still warm.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Crush graham crackers with rolling pin or use blender.
Mix all together and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.
Garnish or top with whipped cream.

title: olive - cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese with butter. Stir in flour, salt and paprika. Mix well. Wrap 1 teaspoon dough around each olive, completely covering olive.
Place on cookie sheet, cover with foil or clear wrap and freeze until firm. Remove and store in plastic bag in freezer.

title: seafood pasta(serves 4)
directions: Heat oil in large frypan.
Saute onion and pepper.
Add garlic, white wine and cleaned and shelled raw shrimp.
Simmer until shrimp are almost cooked.
Add tomato sauce, heavy cream and steamed vegetables.
Bring back to a simmer.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place hot cooked pasta in a large bowl.
Top with shrimp mixture and mix thoroughly.
Top with grated cheese and chopped parsley.

title: hot olive cheese balls
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Wrap each piece around an olive. Roll ball in cheese.
Bake at 450° for 6 to 8 minutes until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 40 balls.

title: split pea hummus
directions: Boil peas for 30 minutes or until soft.
Combine all ingredients in blender and process until smooth and creamy.
Add water, if necessary, for consistency.
Use as dip with chips or veggies.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Prick sausage links several times with fork.
In skillet, brown sausage well.
Drain and reserve 3 tablespoons drippings.
Slice sausage.
Set aside.
In the drippings, cook the peppers and onions.
Cover for 5 minutes.
Uncover and cook until the vegetables are tender but not brown.
Season to taste with salt. Add the sausage and wine; heat through.

title: blue ribbon pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening until mixture is corn meal texture.
In a measuring cup, beat together vinegar and egg, then fill to one cup level with cold tap water. Mix together flour and vinegar mixture.
Dough will be soft and sticky.
Working on well floured board, roll out a piece of the dough to approximately 1/8-inch thick and 2 to 3-inches wider than pie pan.
Put in lightly floured pie pans.
Roll out equal sized circles for top crusts.

title: butterscotch yumme
directions: Mix the flour, oleo and salt and press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until done; drain.
In casserole dish, combine noodles, chicken, celery, peppers, mayonnaise and salt.
Blend celery soup and milk; heat through.
Add cheese; heat and stir until cheese is melted, then add to noodle mixture.
Bake at 425° about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: woodland nut cake
directions: Sift 2 3/4 cups flour.
Add sugar and salt and baking powder. Sift thoroughly.
Drop in Crisco.
Add milk and extracts and 2 eggs.
Beat for 2 minutes at low speed.
Add remaining 2 eggs. Beat 2 minutes more at low speed.
Add chopped nuts and blend. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Very good topped with a cream cheese frosting.

title: easy chicken casserole(serves 6)
directions: Mix everything together and pour into greased baking dish. Bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven and sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top if you like.
Return to oven for about 10 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
This is very good left over.

title: mint tease
directions: In a saucepan, bring water and mint to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Remove tea bags and mint.
Stir in sugar.
Chill.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a loaf pan with nonstick vegetable spray.
Mix all ingredients except butter and pour into pan.
Bake for 30 minutes, remove from oven.
Pour melted butter over top and return to oven for 15 to 20 more minutes.

title: cherry puff magic
directions: Makes 8 large puffs.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Place half in greased baking pan. Mix chicken, onion, celery and mayonnaise.
Spread over cornbread mixture.
Beat eggs, milk and broth; add salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Pour over chicken.
Pour remaining cornbread over chicken.
Spoon soup over dressing, sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at least 45 minutes or until brown at 375°.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened (do not beat).
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup nuts and 2 cups bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and cool completely before frosting.

title: breasted potatoes
directions: Wash and dry the Potatoes.
Mix Oil into pan with melted Butter; add Garlic Powder, Salt and Thyme Leaves mixing thoroughly. Quarter the dried Potatoes and drop a few at a time into the mixture; coating completely.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Continue until all Potato pieces have been covered and added to the baking dish.
Bake at 325 for 1 hour; turning halfway through the time.
Quantity depends on the serving sizes for the eaters.

title: rainbow pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Rinse with cold water. Finely chop and dice all vegetables.
Stir vegetables into pasta. Toss with Dijon Basil Vinaigrette.

title: cocoa-licious cereal treats
directions: Microwave margarine in 4-quart microwavable bowl on High for 45 seconds or until melted.
Add marshmallows.
Mix to coat. Microwave 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, or until marshmallows are smooth when stirred, stirring after 45 seconds.
Add cereal.
Mix to coat well.
Press firmly into lightly greased foil lined 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Turn onto cutting surface.
Peel off foil.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add marshmallows.
Chop apricots and add juice; add pineapple.
Mix and stir good.
Let chill in refrigerator.

title: crabmeat in toast cups
directions: Cut crust from bread.
Cut into rounds with 2 1/2 inch cutter. Brush both sides with melted butter.
Press into tiny muffin tins.
Bake cups in 450° oven for 5 minutes or until brown.
Melt the 3 tablespoons of margarine in a medium saucepan.
Stir in flour and cook until bubbly (about 1 minute).
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add milk and crabmeat.
Fill each toast cup with mixture and bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Yields about 100 cups.

title: apple-nut muffins
directions: Grease 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups. In a bowl, beat egg with juice, oil and vanilla. Stir in flour, sugar, baking powder and salt just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Stir in nuts and apple.
Fill prepared muffin cups; sprinkle with Sugar 'N Cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions, omitting chilling.
Place 1/3 crumbled brownie mix in bottom of a 3-quart trifle dish (glass bowl on stem).
Top with 1/3 pudding, 1/3 whipping topping and 1/3 crushed candy bars.
Repeat layers twice with remaining ingredients, ending with crushed candy bars.
Chill 8 hours.
Yields 16 to 18 servings.

title: herbed biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl. Cut in shortening and butter with pastry cutter or fingertips until mixture forms coarse crumbs.
Add milk and herbs and stir until mixture forms ball.
Gently knead dough on lightly floured surface, making 8 turns.
Roll out dough on lightly floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness.
Using a 3-inch round cutter, cut out biscuits.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Gather scraps; repeat rolling and cutting.
Bake until biscuits are golden, about 14 minutes.
Transfer to rack; cool 5 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix ingredients with wooden spoon.
Make a well and add buttermilk.
Mix moderately; soft moist dough. Shape into a heavily greased 9-inch cake pan or skillet. Bake in a
350° oven for 60 minutes.

title: fast and easy foil dinner
directions: For each person to be served, rip a sizeable piece of foil. Then cut potatoes and carrots.
Make a hamburger patty for each dinner.
Surround the hamburger patty with the potatoes and carrots.
Add 2 teaspoons butter on top of hamburger and a nice slice of onion.
Salt and pepper everything for your own taste. Then wrap up each dinner and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot. A tossed salad or jello salad goes nicely on the side.

title: snicker salad
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Fold in apples and candy.
Chill; serve in a crystal bowl.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook 1/2 cup water and white syrup on low heat until it comes to a boil; stir often.
Mix the cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water and add it to the mixture.
Let it boil on higher heat for about 5 minutes, then remove from heat.
Add the flavoring and the food coloring.
Let the mixture get real cool before you pour it over the berries.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Blend remaining ingredients and broccoli.
Place in buttered casserole.
Top with buttered Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: gnocchi
directions: Boil potatoes until completely done.
Peel and run through ricer.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Slowly add flour until firm manageable dough develops.
Let dough rest 10 minutes under covered dish.
Take slice of dough and roll with hands into long 2 to 3-foot "snake".
Repeat until dough is gone.
Cut each roll into 1/2-inch long pieces.
Place Gnocchi pieces on cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Do not be afraid to use extra flour to prevent sticking.
Place in freezer.
When frozen, put in plastic bags for storage.
This recipe may be doubled or tripled.

title: caramel squares
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda, salt and butter in bowl; mix well.
Reserve half of the oat mixture.
Press the remaining mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans. Drizzle with mixture of ice cream topping and 6 tablespoons of flour.
Sprinkle with reserved oat mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares.

title: chinese noodle candy
directions: Melt morsels and oil in double boiler until smooth.
Add nuts and noodles and drop on waxed paper to harden.
Store in closed container.

title: mandarin pork roast
directions: Trim excess fat from roast.
Sprinkle roast with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Spread mustard over roast and place in large Dutch oven.
Cover and bake at 325° until meat thermometer registers 170°.
Drain mandarin oranges, reserving liquid. Combine liquid and next 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened. Remove from heat and stir in onion, green pepper and oranges. Spoon sauce over roast.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: broccoli, cauliflower, pea salad
directions: Clean broccoli and cauliflower and cut into small bite size pieces; add frozen peas.
Pour Hidden Valley Ranch dressing over top of vegetables.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: patty's tea room salad
directions: Mix together and freeze overnight; cut into squares.
Use 9 x 13-inch Pyrex cake pan.

title: chocolate caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup milk over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Set aside.
Melt margarine.
Add to 1/3 cup of milk and cake mix.
Press half the cake mix into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle 1 cup of pecans and chocolate chips over cake.
Pour caramel mixture over top.
Drop the rest of cake mix (teaspoon size) and press into caramel mix. Sprinkle rest of nuts on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: great deer roast
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients
and rub on thawed meat.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Place meat in roasting pan lined with aluminum
foil. Put
sliced onions and uncooked bacon on top.
Add Worcestershire and
wine
to
top.
Add
2 cups chicken broth around
roast. Bring
foil loosely over meat, do not use lid. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes per pound.
Midway of baking time, pull
foil away from top and continue baking.
Can add carrots and
potatoes
at
this time.
Retain liquid for gravy.

title: mom's goulash
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add soup, beans, onion and pepper. Simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Best with tossed salad and apple pie.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Make a paste of the cocoa and food coloring.
Cream the shortening with the sugar.
Add eggs.
Combine flour with salt. Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Fold in baking soda and vinegar with spoon.
Use a round tube pan for Ding Dong Cake recipe or use three 8-inch cake pans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: calizza
directions: Brown meat and set aside.
Season with garlic salt and Italian spices.
Pour in tomato sauce and cheese.
With well-buttered hands, shape bread dough into squares.
Place a spoonful of meat and cheese mixture in the middle of the dough.
Fold sides of dough over meat sauce and seal the edges.
Place on a well oiled cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 325°
for about 20 minutes.
When cooked, brush with butter.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk and egg.
While stirring add chopped onions last.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot oil, frying only a few minutes until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and rolls. Press 2 crescent rolls together to form a rectangle. Put 1 heaping tablespoonful of mixture in center of roll and fold over. Pinch edge to stay together. Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. They puff up quickly. Watch closely.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Run tomatoes, peppers, onions and celery through food chopper. Add salt and drain overnight.
In the morning, add mustard seed, vinegar and sugar.
Pack in jars, no need to seal.
Baby food jars are nice.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Boil rice and drain.
Fry ground beef and onion.
Combine all ingredients; pour into 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Salt pork chops to taste.
Put pork chops in oblong pan; put sliced onions on top and pepper.
Pour rice over this and then pour mushroom soup and water over this.
Place in a 350° oven and bake 1 hour or until done.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine squash, onion and green pepper in a saucepan with a small amount of water.
Cook over medium heat until tender.
Drain and add next 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoonful into hot oil; cook until brown.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Cream the cream cheese and add powdered sugar.
Prepare whipped topping mix as per package and fold into cheese mix.
Fold in mini marshmallows with topping and cheese.
Spread over the baked layer.
Dissolve strawberry jello in boiling water.
Stir in frozen strawberries, thawed.
May chop strawberries some.
Chill to slightly thickened.
Spread over sour cream layer and chill. Serves 16 to 20.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini halfway (not too soft).
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Cut cucumbers in slices, then in four (cube).
Dice tomatoes.
Add cucumber and tomatoes to linguini, mix well then add dressing and half a jar of Salad Supreme.
Mix all together. Chill 2 hours and serve.

title: snow salad
directions: Stir well 1/4 cup cold water and unflavored gelatin.
Boil 1 cup water and add sugar.
Add it to the first mixture.
Let cool, but not set.
Mix in vanilla and sour cream.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour in jello ring mold and let set.
When serving, fruit pie filling in the cherry.
You can also use fresh sliced strawberries mixed with strawberry glaze.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix ingredients; put small balls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on a paper towel.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: coconut cream jello salad
directions: Mix crackers and margarine.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding with milk.
Add ice cream.
Pour over crumbs.
Sprinkle with crushed nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: cocoa with marshmallows and chocolate chips(makes about 14 cups mix)
directions: Stir together the dry milk powder, confectioners sugar, cocoa powder, nondairy creamer, marshmallows and chocolate chips in a large bowl

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 11 x 7 x 7 or 8 x 8 x 2 baking pan with 1 tablespoon butter.
Mix in medium bowl the corn, milk, cornstarch, salt, Tabasco, sugar, eggs and milk.
Pour corn mixture into preheated pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes or until pudding is set.
Delicious!!

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into tube pan; bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes until done.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Can fix crust and sausage the night before; add other ingredients in the morning.

title: tomato vinaigrette
directions: Dice tomatoes, add ingredients, toss and cover for 3 hours.

title: allie's peach pudding
directions: Filling:
Combine sugar, salt, flour and beaten egg yolks.
Add milk-syrup mixture.
Cook on low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and flavor; beat until smooth.
Alternate cookies and thin slices of peaches with pudding.

title: my favorite dinner
directions: Go to the garden and get the vegetables.
Start with 1 cup chopped and add 1/2 cup more for each person.
Get the bamboo shoots and water chestnuts from the store.
Use last 4 ingredients for each 4 persons.
Put sesame seed oil (substitute other kinds if you wish with a less flavorful result) in a large hot skillet. Slice onion into it.
Cover and stir until translucent.
Add 1/2 cup water if too dry.
Cover immediately after water addition to give steam.
Cook vegetables in microwave without water.
Carrots and celery take the longest.
Cook the others together only until warmed.
Add vegetables to onion.
Add grated ginger and teriyaki sauce.
If a sauce is desired, add 1 cup water with 2 tablespoons cornstarch dissolved in it.
Cook until jelled.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Using half of the cake, break into small portions.
Place in the bottom of punch bowl. Mix the vanilla pudding mix with the milk.
Pour half of this over cake in bowl.
Spoon 1 can of cherry pie filling and 1 can of the drained pineapple.
Next, slice 2 bananas, then sprinkle 1/2 of the chopped nuts.
Spread 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Repeat the layers again.
Decorate the top with cherries and nuts, if so desired. Serves 25 people.
Let refrigerate overnight or several hours.

title: steamed pudding
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add raisins, molasses, sour milk and egg.
Line steamer pan with waxed paper; steam for 3 hours.
Serve warm with sweetened White Sauce.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream until smooth. Spread in a 9 x 13 cake pan.
Pour bottle of taco sauce over this. Next put chilies on, then lettuce (cut fine), cheese, black olives and tomatoes.

title: caramel corn
directions: If using microwave popcorn, use 1 1/2 to 2 bags of popped corn.
Remove unpopped kernels.

title: two-step chicken pecan salad
directions: In large bowl, place chicken, celery, parsley, salt, pepper, tarragon and oil; stir together until well mixed.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight, stirring once or twice to blend ingredients.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a double boiler and cook until it coats the spoon.

title: ma-ma's gingerbread
directions: Sift flour, soda, ginger, cinnamon and salt onto waxed paper. Cream shortening with sugar until fluffy in a large bowl.
Beat in molasses and egg.
Stir in flour mixture, half at a time, just until blended.
Beat in hot water until smooth.
Pour into a well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched.
Leave in pan on rack to cool 10 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: rhubarb delight
directions: Mix the ingredients together and press into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: In mixing bowl, whisk together egg and milk.
Sift in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir to make a soft dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead lightly.
Roll and cut in 6 equal squares. Place 4 apple quarters in center of each square, bringing up corners of dough to enclose apple.
Pinch and seal.
Place dumplings in a large pan, not touching.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer.
Test by pricking with toothpick.
If apples are tender, they are done.
Sprinkle with a little cinnamon-sugar.

title: squash puppies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with enough flour to make a stiff dough. Drop by spoonfuls into a hot greased skillet and brown to your liking.
You may use more meal and deep fry like hush puppies.

title: grandma's corn soup
directions: Cook all together until it boils.
Pack in jars.
Put on cold mason inserts.
Screw lid rings on tightly.
Place in canner and cook in hot water for 3 hours.
Lids should seal in canner.
Take out of canner and set aside.
Do not touch for at least 24 hours. Lids should have made a popping noise within that time period.
Any that hasn't sealed, refrigerate immediately and use before spoiling.

title: bean salad
directions: Place chickpeas and green and yellow beans in mixing bowl. Season well.
Place shallots, mustard, garlic, vinegar and oil in small bowl.
Season and, using a wire whisk, mix well until thick. Pour dressing over beans.
Mix well.
Add parsley and tarragon; mix well.
Let sit 15 to 30 minutes at room temperature.

title: meat 'n bean bake
directions: Cook meats and onion until crumbly.
Add the other ingredients.
Mix and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix and form into meatballs. Brown lightly; add tomato sauce. Stir to coat and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: honey roasted apples
directions: Pare top 1/3 of the apples and remove core, leaving 1/2-inch of core on bottom.
Place apples in oiled baking dish. Combine honey, orange juice, lemon juice, orange peel and ginger.
Mix well.
Spoon over apples, allowing mixture to fill centers and coat entire surface.
Pour water into baking dish. Bake, covered, at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes longer or until apples are glazed and tender.
Baste with liquid from baking dish every 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rachel pafford's dirty rice
directions: Cook rice per directions.
Brown sausage, chopping while you brown.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
Put sausage back into pan and add rice, onion, soy sauce, water and sage.
Turn down to medium heat and simmer until rice is almost dry.
Serves 10 people.

title: ten day slaw
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, oil and salt to boil.
Pour over cabbage, pimentos, onion and pepper.
Refrigerate.
Will keep ten days or more.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli and sauce.
Top with crumbled Ritz.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dessert pumpkin
directions: Combine pumpkin, salt, cinnamon, ginger, cloves, sugar, eggs and milk; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with package of yellow cake mix.
Pour melted margarine over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Heat margarine in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Cook bell pepper and mushrooms in margarine until soft, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir constantly until bubbly and remove from heat.
Stir in milk and broth.
Heat to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and pimento.
Heat until hot.
Serve over rice or toasted bread triangles.

title: white confetti fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt 1 1/2 pounds white chocolate with 1 can Eagle Brand milk.
Remove from heat.
Stir in salt, vanilla and chopped cherries.
Spread evenly into wax paper lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board.
Peel off paper.
Cut into squares.
Store loosely, covered, at room temperature.
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: mustard potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in cubes.
Cook in enough water to cover until tender.
Drain and cool until warm.
Mix Miracle Whip, mustard, salt and celery seed.
Add remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Add potatoes and mustard mixture.
Mix lightly or until well blended.
Do not overmix or potatoes will mash.

title: marvelous pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in pie shells and chill 1 hour.

title: cooked grits(servings:  8)
directions: Pour into casserole serving dish and bake at 250° for 1 hour. Top with Cheddar cheese and paprika 20 minutes before it comes out of the oven.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Bake on greased cookie sheet at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini squash cakes
directions: Mix Bisquick and cheese.
Stir in eggs and butter or oleo. Fold in zucchini.
Fry in butter or oleo.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side.

title: mother's chocolate pie *
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, flour and cocoa.
Add egg yolks mixed with a little milk, stir well.
Add remaining milk, cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Beat in margarine and add vanilla.
Pour into a baked pie shell.

title: chicken breast on rice
directions: Blend mushroom soup and milk; set aside 1/2 cup.
Combine one portion of the soup mixture with rice, mushrooms and onion soup mix.
Pour into baking dish.
Arrange chicken breasts on top, (skin side up) and pour the rest of the soup mixture over them and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer to brown.

title: banana oatmeal chewies
directions: Cream flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Add egg and mix well. Mix flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Add alternately with mashed bananas.
Add oatmeal and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes into small pieces and cover with water; boil until the potatoes are tender.
Add the oleo, salt and pepper to taste. Chop the green pepper and add to the potatoes.
Cook 6 to 8 pieces of bacon
until crisp.
Cut bacon into small pieces.
Add bacon and small amount of bacon grease to potatoes.
When pepper is tender, add 1 can Milnot.
Thicken with small amount of cornstarch and water.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cut into small pieces.
Mix soups (undiluted) and tomatoes in pot and simmer until warm.
Spread small amount of mixture in bottom of 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Put small amount of chicken and tablespoon of mixture in tortilla, roll up and place in pan.
Repeat until pan is full.
Pour remaining mixture over top of enchiladas.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Add the next 4 ingredients in order listed:
crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips and nuts.
Next, pour condensed milk over all.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Boil syrup and sugar, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter; mix well.
Add Krispies and mix well. spread into buttered 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Cool.
Melt chips together and spread on bars.
Cool and cut.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Cook carrot strips covered in small amount of water, boiling for 5 minutes or until tender-crisp; drain.
Put into shallow casserole.
Mix the mayonnaise, horseradish sauce, onion, salt and pepper and spread on carrots.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter and sprinkle over mayonnaise mix.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°. Yields 6 servings.
Double for potlucks.

title: fudge muffins
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in pan.
Beat in sugar, salt and flour.
Then add eggs, one at a time, stirring in.
Add vanilla and walnuts.
Pour in greased 24-cup muffin pan and bake 25 minutes in 325° oven.

title: concert punch
directions: Combine nectar, pineapple juice, limeade concentrate and water.
Stir well and chill.
Just before serving, pour into punch bowl.
Add soda and stir well.
Serve immediately.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in the molasses.
Put 1 teaspoon soda in sour milk and add the rest of the soda to the flour.
(This makes a soft dough and will puff up beautifully.)
Drop by small spoonfuls into well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: seafood and spinach soup
directions: Bring herbs, broth and potatoes to a boil.
Simmer about 20 minutes. Add shrimp, fish, tomatoes and half the spinach.
Simmer 5 more minutes. Garnish with the rest of the spinach. Serves 6.

title: frosty strawberry salad
directions: Cream the mayonnaise and cheese.
Blend in strawberries and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream.
Freeze.
Cut into squares. Serve on lettuce leaf and garnish with fresh, whole strawberries.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients using enough salad dressing to blend. Serve as a salad with ham.

title: weeknight fajitas
directions: In a large bowl, pour dressing over the chicken strips, pepper, onion, garlic and oregano.
Toss lightly.
Cover and refrigerate at least 10 minutes, but preferably overnight.
Drain.
Stir-fry chicken mixture until chicken is browned and no longer pink.
Stir in tomatoes.
Fill tortillas with chicken mixture.
Serve with salsa, sour cream, shredded cheese, refried beans and/or guacamole. Serves 4.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. In large bowl, combine sugar, raisins, nuts, zucchini, oil, vanilla and eggs; blend well by hand.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder, nutmeg and cloves; mix well by hand.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool before frosting.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix eggs, oil and vanilla with dry ingredients.
Mix in apples and stir well.
Grease and flour pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; reserve broth and cool.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix dressing according to package directions and spread in pan.
Remove chicken from bones and spread in chunks over dressing.
In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add flour and seasoning and cooled broth.
Stir over heat until mixture boils and thickens.
Slowly stir in beaten eggs and pour over chicken. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix in order and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
After baking, top with mixture of honey and catsup (equal parts).

title: cream cheese caramel apple dip
directions: Mix well together; add nuts, if desired.
Cut up 6 apples into wedges and dip!

title: orange dreamsicle cake
directions: Blend all ingredients and pour into two 9-inch greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool and split layers.

title: butter rings coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, 2 tablespoons sugar and salt.
Work oleo and raisins into the mixture.
Mix together the yeast, 1/4 cup warm milk and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Add this to 1 cup milk into which 3 egg yolks have been added.
Combine this mixture with the flour mixture; refrigerate overnight.

title: no water jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle 1 small package of jello over mixture and stir.

title: stain glass windows(marshmallow rolls)
directions: Mix all together and add one package of colored small marshmallows.
Place in a large bowl.
Place some coconut in a large piece of foil.
Roll mixture into a large log, approximately 1 to 1 1/2 inches round.
Should make 4 logs, then roll into the coconut.
May be kept frozen for later use.

title: hamburger and gravy
directions: Fry hamburger light brown on both sides.
Make gravy.
Put in slow cooker.
Put hamburger in slow cooker.
Let cook 1 hour or more.
Serve with cream potatoes.

title: quick and easy mexican dip
directions: Spread refried beans over an entire dinner plate.
Mix Durkee taco seasoning and sour cream together.
Spread over refried beans.
Spread cheese over sour cream mixture.
Top with sliced tomatoes and chopped green onions.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with chips.

title: butterscotch-peanut fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine butterscotch pieces, milk and marshmallows. Stir over medium heat until marshmallows melt. Remove from heat; beat in peanut butter, vanilla and a dash of salt. Stir in nuts. Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Chill; cut into squares. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except pie shell and blend well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 5 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 45 minutes.

title: swedish pot roast
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and ginger.
Dredge meat in seasoned flour.
Brown pot roast in oil.
Pour off excess drippings.
Add cinnamon stick and water.
Arrange dried fruit on pot roast.
Cover and cook slowly for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender.
Add orange juice and cook slow for 15 minutes. Discard the cinnamon stick.
Remove meat to heated platter. Thicken fruit and liquid mixture with cornstarch for gravy.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten eggs, 1 at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Add almond flavoring.

title: sombrero salad
directions: Season cheese with salt and chili powder; add enough pineapple juice to moisten.
Mold into cones about 2-inches in diameter; place cone on each slice pineapple at base, arrange strips of green pepper for "hatband" and pimento for the "bow".
Serve on crisp lettuce with whipped cream mayonnaise.

title: fluffy rice and chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix mushroom soup and milk.
Reserve 1/2 cup of mixture.
Mix remaining soup mixture, rice, mushrooms (with liquid) and half of the onion soup mix.
Pour into ungreased baking dish.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Pour reserved soup mixture over chicken; sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 1 hour, uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: hot fudge
directions: Boil 10 minutes.
Add more sugar if not thick enough.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together, make into small balls and bake about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: brunch dish
directions: The day before, place cubed bread in an 8-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Cover with sausage, which has been cut into small pieces and cooked.
Top with remaining other 1 cup cheese.
In a small bowl, beat eggs and 2 1/4 cups milk together. Pour over sausage mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
The next day, dilute mushroom soup with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over refrigerated mixture.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown
beef
and
drain,
add other ingredients. (Do not drain beans.) Simmer on medium low until onions and garlic are tender and juice is thickened.

title: raisin-oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in the oats.
Combine egg whites, brown sugar, oil, milk, vanilla and raisins; add to flour mixture.
Mix well. Drop batter, a teaspoon at a time, onto an oiled cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes, depending on texture desired.
Shorter baking time results in a chewy soft cookie, the longer time in a crisp one.
Yield:
3 dozen.
One cookie contains 70 calories, 1.6 gm fiber, low cholesterol and for sodium control, omit salt.

title: syrup tea cakes
directions: Mix well.
Chill dough.
Pinch off small pieces and flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake on greased cookie pan for 8 minutes at 350°. Will keep in refrigerator.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: In a small saucepan, heat the water to boiling.
Add the chocolate and stir until melted.
Cool.
Combine crumbs and butter and press into the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, cream (at medium speed) the cheese until light and fluffy.
Add the sugar and eggs and continue beating until well blended.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
This should take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire about 4 weeks at 456°.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more are expected, two rabbits may be added, but only if necessary since most people do not like to find a hare in their stew.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Saute onions in oleo.
Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Use up to 1/2 cup broth to keep from being dry.
Put in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Place bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw, rinse and drain spinach.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, dressing and spinach.
Chill mixture several hours or overnight. Remove center from loaf of bread and fill with dip.
Cut center section into squares for dipping.

title: no-fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into sifted flour with sugar and salt already added. Add 1 egg, well beaten.
Mix cold water and vinegar together.
Add to flour mixture, a little at a time, until all have been added.
Mix well.
Place on floured board and knead until ready to roll out for pie crust.
This will make about 5 pie crusts.
Keep stored in refrigerator until all have been used.
It will roll out better if stored in refrigerator overnight. This will keep well for 2 weeks.

title: white chocolate almond balls
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Spread nuts on baking sheet and toast in oven until golden brown.
Cool and chop.
With electric mixer set at medium speed, beat butter, sugar, salt and almond extract until creamy.
On low speed, beat in flour until mixture just comes together.
Stir in nuts.
Chill until firm.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Put on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake until golden brown on bottom, 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool completely on wire racks.
Chop chocolate, put in a small bowl and melt in a 250° oven.
Put coconut in a bowl.
Drop cookies, one at a time, into chocolate. Coat and remove with fork, letting excess drip off.
Drop cookies in coconut.
Lightly press coconut onto cookies.
Set on rack to dry.

title: ten-ten rolls
directions: Grease pan (Bundt is best) very well.
Place frozen rolls in pan on top of chopped nuts.
Sprinkle with pudding mix.
Melt butter with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cover with towel.
Let set overnight (10 to 12 hours).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes for 30 minutes.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Blend together sugar, butter, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Roll out and cut in shapes.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 2 loaf pans. Cream the shortening and sugar thoroughly. Add eggs, pumpkin and water. Blend in dry ingredients except nuts and raisins.
Stir in nuts and raisins. Bake in prepared pans 65 to 75 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: simple baked beans
directions: Drain beans well.
Combine brown sugar, ketchup, liquid smoke, mustard and onion.
Mix well.
Stir in beans.
Cook on top of range at medium heat until begins to boil.
Reduce to simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water, drain well.
In a buttered 2-quart baking pan, put layers of macaroni and layer of cheese until both are used.
Beat eggs, milk and salt.
Pour eggs and milk mixture over macaroni and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar-free tiny applesauce cupcakes
directions: Cream margarine until fluffy.
Beat egg and sweetener until thick and lemon colored; add to margarine and mix well.
Sift all dry ingredients together; add to margarine mixture alternately with applesauce; blend well.
Add vanilla, raisins and nuts.
Pour into tiny tart tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 30.

title: waikiki meatballs
