directions: Mix thoroughly beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk. Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls.
Melt shortening in large skillet; brown and cook meatballs.
Remove from pan; keep warm.
Pour fat from skillet.
Mix cornstarch and sugar; stir in pineapple syrup, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth.
Pour into skillet; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils and thickens.
Boil and stir one minute.
Add meatballs, pineapple and green peppers.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted butter, then in crumb mixture.
Arrange in shallow pan, uncovered.
Dot with 2 tablespoons oleo.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours, or until tender.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Mix mincemeat, salt, shortening, sugar, water and cinnamon; boil 1 minute.
Add soda to mix and let cool, then pour over flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour at 300°.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Cover chicken with water to have enough broth. When cooked, take chicken out of broth; bone and use in dumplings (if desired). Make dough with cup of broth. Make it real stiff, where you can roll your dumplings out and they don't tear up when layered into boiling broth. Put a lot of black pepper on each layer. Let each layer get done before putting others in boiling broth. Layer until all of your dough is used. Leave plenty of broth where dumplings won't be dried out.

title: swiss cream steak
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons margarine in large skillet.
Saute onions; remove from skillet.
Pound steak strips and dredge in flour seasoned with salt, pepper and paprika.
Melt remaining margarine in skillet and add meat.
Brown well on both sides.
Mix in prepared onions, water and sour cream until blended.
Cover and cook over medium heat until meat is tender, 30 to 45 minutes. Uncover and cook until sauce thickens, about 10 minutes.
Serve over hot, cooked rice or noodles.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour in unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cream dip for fruit
directions: Beat ingredients until smooth.
Serve with any fresh fruit, such as bananas, grapes, apples, etc.

title: muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients except last three.
Put in greased muffin tin and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Pop out and dip in margarine, sugar and cinnamon mix.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix; put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle Ritz cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: gratin of sweet potatoes and bourbon
directions: Peel potatoes, cut into 1/2 inch slices.
Place in 1 1/2 qt. buttered baking dish.
Season with salt.
In a small saucepan over medium heat, reduce cream by 1/3.
Add bourbon, whisk well.
Pour over potatoes, dust with nutmeg.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salad
directions: Dissolve jello in pineapple.
Fold in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Keep in refrigerator and it keeps a long time.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, shortening and beaten egg. Mix well. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, well-greased.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Spray an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish with nonstick spray.
In medium bowl stir cream cheese, cottage cheese, eggs and sugar until well blended.
Stir in raisins, margarine, vanilla and cinnamon.
Add egg noodles.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 20 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Blend dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add butter to bowl and mix well.
Spread oatmeal; mix on top of apples and press lightly in greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Double for 9 x 13.

title: yellow squash relish
directions: Place
first
4 ingredients in large pan.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in a pan.
Bring this mixture to a boil and then strain.
Pour
vinegar
mixture
over squash mixture and mix. Bring
to a boil for about 2 minutes then put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: roast beef
directions: Sprinkle dry ingredients over roast.
Spread mushroom over all and wrap securely in foil.
Cook 3 to 4 hours at 350°.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Put oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla in a bowl.
Put margarine, sugar, milk and cocoa in a pan.
Bring to a boil and boil for exactly 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over the contents of the bowl.
Mix well.
While still hot, drop cookies by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Chill until hard.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Line a 9 inch pie plate with foil. Microwave chocolate and butter in a large bowl on high 2 minutes or until butter is melted. Stir until chocolate is completely melted. Stir in nuts. Press mixture onto bottom and sides of prepared pie plate (to form the crust). Refrigerate until firm, approximately one hour. While crust is chilling you can make the Filling.

title: seafood stew
directions: Assemble ingredients night before.
Heat over double boiler when ready to serve.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Place chicken breast in baking dish.
Spoon pineapple over chicken.
Pour slightly thickened juice over chicken breast and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until tender.
Baste chicken occasionally.
Serves 1.
Contains 190 calories, 22 g protein, 2.8 g fat, 60 mg chol. and 55 mg sodium.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed by hand.
Pour into greased spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, leave in oven with door open for 1 hour to cool.
Remove from oven and cool for additional 2 hours, then refrigerate.

title: homemade pepperoni
directions: Mix by hand.
Form into rolls.
Refrigerate, uncovered, for 24 hours.
Bake on wire rack (so juices drip through) at 300° for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage until browned; drain off excess fat.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan, with points toward the center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust; seal perforations. Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar and Swiss cheeses.
In a bowl, beat together the eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: swiss ham ring-around
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
In a large mixing bowl, combine parsley, onion, mustard, margarine and lemon juice; blend well. Add cheese, ham and broccoli; mix lightly.
Set aside.

title: chambord raspberry trifle
directions: Cut angel cake into small pieces.
Make pudding according to directions on package.
Using a large trifle bowl, layer bottom with cake.
Drizzle liqueur over it, followed by pudding, whipped topping and raspberry preserves.
Keep layering and put strawberries on last.

title: green tomato chow-chow
directions: Grind tomatoes and let stand overnight.
Drain off juice. Add peppers and onions.
Mix well.
Add sugar, salt and spice bag. Let cook about 20 to 25 minutes.
Place in hot sterilized jars.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Use large, over-ripe cucumbers.
Peel and scoop out the seeds. cut into 2 to 3-inch pieces and place in a large cooking pot. Salt the cucumbers liberally and let stand overnight to draw out some of the water.
The next day, pour off the accumulated water and rinse off the cucumbers and leave draining in colander.
Heat vinegar in a large kettle.
Add spices and bring to boiling point. Add the sugar, then add the cucumbers to the liquid and heat thoroughly.
I cooked the cukes until they were just tender enough to remain together when picked up with a fork.
This took practice.
Put in sterilized jars at once and seal.

title: turkey pasta salad
directions: Combine pasta with cooked vegetables.
Chill in refrigerator. Vegetables should not be overcooked!
Add cabbage, turkey, carrot and spices.
Toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: puppy chow
directions: Pour cereals into large bowl; set aside.
In a 1-quart microwave safe bowl, combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth.
Stir after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereals, until pieces are coated.
Pour cereal into plastic bag with powdered sugar.
Shake until all coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and add taco seasoning, water and olives.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup crushed chips onto pie crust followed by meat mixture.
Top with 1 cup sour cream, 1 cup shredded cheese and top with 1/2 cup crushed chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with shredded lettuce, tomatoes and taco sauce.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil sugar and water and pour over jello.
Mix well.
Then add cranberries, apples and pecans.
At last, add the crushed pineapple.
Very good for the holidays with turkey and dressing.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in 1 1/2 or 2-quart glass bowl.
Microwave 4 minutes on High.
Stir.
Microwave another 3 minutes on High.
Add butter.
Microwave 2 minutes on High.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Stir until foamy.
Spread on greased cookie sheet, spreading to 1/4-inch thick.
Set until cool.

title: homemade pizza crust
directions: Mix flour, warm water, yeast and salt into a ball (may need a little extra flour if it seems too sticky).
Divide into 3 or 4 balls; let rise in warm place for 1 hour.
Spread in greased pizza or cookie sheet pans.

title: louisiana baked flounder with bacon
directions: Place fish fillets over 2 slices bacon in greased baking dish. Cover with remaining bacon and lemon slices.
Combine tomato soup and water.
Add bay leaves, salt and pepper to taste.
Place sliced onion on top of fish and pour sauce over fish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place on heated serving platter.
Strain sauce over fish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry nut muffins
directions: Grease and line 12 muffin tins.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and soda.
Blend.
In a separate bowl, blend orange juice, egg, melted butter and orange zest.
Add orange juice mix to dry ingredients and mix with a wooden spoon until batter is moist but lumpy.
Add cranberries and walnuts.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemon and garlic shrimp
directions: Mince
the
garlic and chop scallion.
Squeeze 2 tablespoons juice
from the lemon.
Heat butter and oil in a large frying
pan over
medium heat.
Add shrimp, garlic and 1 teaspoon
of salt. Saute, stirring, until shrimp turn pink, 3 or 4
minutes.
Stir in the lemon juice and scallions.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Place celery, carrots and onion in large Dutch oven and cover with water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer.
Add potatoes, margarine, evaporated milk and enough water to cover vegetables.
Fry bacon pieces, drain and add to soup.
When vegetables are tender (about 30 minutes), stir in cheese until melted.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream and add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pressed chicken
directions: Place chicken and pork roast in a large kettle.
Add salt and pepper.
Put gelatin in 1 cup cold water.
Add to chicken mixture. Place in 3 glass loaf pans.
You may have to press down the meat to drain off some of the juice.

title: festive dip
directions: Put in crock-pot and cook slowly until ready to serve with chips.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Mix rice, corn, 1 can

tomato sauce, salt and pepper, onion, 1/2 c. water, and ground beef. Place in a baking dish and cover meat with bacon strips. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Mix 1 can of tomato sauce and 1/4 c. water and pour over meat and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Add mixture of flour, baking powder and sugar to egg and milk mixture.
Cut bread slices into half pieces.
Dip bread in batter and deep fry until golden brown. Serve hot with syrup.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Serve with celery, carrots, cucumbers, green peppers, mushrooms, green onions, radishes, etc.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, butter and corn syrup in heavy saucepan, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Immediately stir in condensed milk and simmer, stirring until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water.
This cooks quickly; be careful not to scorch.

title: cotton picking good cake
directions: Beat cake mix, eggs, oil and juice of mandarin oranges.
Fold in diced mandarin oranges and pecans.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: thelma's hot dog chili
directions: Brown meat in skillet (drain off grease).
Add all other ingredients; stir well.
Simmer 2 hours or longer, stirring occasionally.

title: roasted peppers and onions
directions: Cut peppers in half and onions in wedges. Place in 375° oven. Turn over when well browned to toast other side. Remove from oven and place peppers in a brown paper bag. Let stand in bag for 10 minutes. Peel and cut into strips. Arrange on platter with onions and marinate with sauce. Great with salads, appetizers, or alone with bread.

title: surprise pasta
directions: Put acini de pepe, salt and oil in boiling water.
Cook until tender, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Rinse and drain pasta.
Cool to room temperature.
Add pineapple, sugar, marshmallows and cherries to the pasta.
Sprinkle pudding mix over this and mix lightly. Add coconut, pecans and Cool Whip; fold in lightly.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: caramel corn
directions: Divide popped corn between 2 to 4-quart bowls.
Mix brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt in 2 1/4-quart casserole. Microwave, uncovered, 2 1/2 minutes; stir.
Microwave, uncovered, to boiling, 30 seconds.
Boil 3 minutes.
Stir in baking soda. Pour syrup over popped corn, stirring until mixed.
Microwave on High 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes, stirring every minute.
Cool, stirring occasionally.

title: potato soup(potetsuppe)
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Peel and chop onion fine.
Put potatoes, onion and salt in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add water to cover.
Boil 15 to 20 minutes or until a fork pierces potatoes easily.
Mash potatoes and onion in pan without draining liquid. Slowly add milk, stirring well as you do so.
Allow soup to simmer while you add butter, pepper and parsley.
Stir over medium heat until smooth and hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well and use.

title: super simple italian chicken pasta
directions: Cut chicken into cubes; shake with salt, pepper and flour. Brown in skillet with oil.
Stir in Hunt's.
Heat through and serve over your favorite pasta.
Makes 4 servings.

title: diabetic fruit cake
directions: Combine all fruit in a small bowl; set aside.
Cream the margarine and vanilla.
Stir in flour, soda, baking powder and spices.
Pour in fruit mixture; beat until blended.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool; store in an airtight container for 3 days.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs in mixing bowl, then add fruit cocktail.
Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add these to the mixture.
Mix well with a spoon (not mixer).
Pour into a greased baking pan. Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corned beef sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Melt butter, add to cheese.
Chop corned beef and mix with butter and cheese; add mustard.
Spread on thin fresh sliced bread.
Roll sandwiches corner to corner and roll in wax paper.
Twist ends to secure roll.
Store in refrigerator overnight or freeze.
Toast for 30 minutes or until brown.
Yield: 25 or 30. For fancy sandwiches, trim bread ends. For hearty man-pleasers, leave crust on.

title: pebble top chocolate bars
directions: Combine coconut, melted butter, 2 tablespoons sugar and graham cracker crumbs in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix well and spread in bottom of pan.
Combine remaining ingredients (except chocolate chips and pecans) and blend at medium speed with mixer until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Spread over graham cracker layer. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Mix together and place in a casserole.
Cover.
Bake slowly one hour.

title: aunt gerri's salad dressing
directions: Mix together and toss over salad just before ready to serve. "Doesn't come any easier than this!"

title: chew cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Cook in greased 8 x 11-inch casserole dish until done.

title: easy chili
directions: Saute hamburger, onions and peppers; drain well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Season to taste.
Simmer 30 minutes and serve hot.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Combine potatoes, salt, butter, pineapple and juice.
Place half of mixture in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with half the marshmallows.
Add remaining half of the potato mixture.
Arrange pecans on top.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover the last 10 minutes before serving and add the rest of the marshmallows.

title: two hour surprise
directions: In a pan or casserole, put dry onion soup, mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and cup of rice into the water.
Mix well.
Put chicken on top.
Cover with foil or lid.
Put in oven for 2 hours at 325°.
When time is up, your supper is done.

title: garlic cheese bread
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch slices.
Heat garlic powder and butter slowly until butter is melted.
Brush each slice of bread on both sides with garlic butter and place on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake in 425° oven 10 minutes or until cheese melts. Serve hot.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water until jello is dissolved.
Add all the rest and place in jello mold or Bundt pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: parmesan potato slices
directions: Combine onion, celery and butter in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until vegetables are just about tender.
Thinly slice potatoes into baking dish; mix lightly.
Cover and microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender; stir once. Add garlic salt, pepper, cheese and seasonings; mix lightly. Sprinkle with paprika.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes, uncovered.

title: potato balls
directions: Cook potatoes, peel and mash adding first 3 ingredients.
Make up a batter with the rest of the ingredients.
Heat oil about 2 inches deep and form walnut-size balls of the mashed potato mix; dip in batter and fry.
Drain and serve with catsup or chutney.

title: reese's pieces peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together and set aside.
Cream shortening, butter, peanut butter and sugars together.
Add egg and gradually mix in flour mixture.
Then add candies.
Roll into small balls.
Place balls onto ungreased cookie sheet and press with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not hard.

title: hot cider
directions: Place whole cloves 1/2-inch apart in an orange.
Place in a baking dish with 1/4 cup water and bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 2 cups of hot water.
Add milk and mix well.
Add pineapple with juice and the cottage cheese.
May add nuts, if desired.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Spread in greased pie plate.
In medium bowl, beat eggs, milk and baking mix until smooth.
Pour over meat mixture. Bake at 400° until knife inserted comes out clean. Top with cheese and let melt.

title: easy mexican lasagne
directions: Saute meat with onion; drain.
Add soups and Ro-Tel.
Simmer. In large flat, greased Pyrex dish, spread a little of the meat mixture.
Then layer flour tortillas, meat mixture and cheese, repeating layers to fill dish.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: lemon lush
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
Mix butter, flour and nuts together. Spread with a fork in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in oven for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: greek salad
directions: In a jar, combine oil, vinegar, bay leaf, garlic and oregano. Shake well and chill several hours.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Before serving, remove bay leaf and garlic from dressing.
Shake well and pour over salad.
Serves 6.

title: chop suey
directions: Use barbecue sauce and a can of cola or any carbonated drink. Bake at 275° for 1 hour per pound of meat in 9 x 13-inch pan; cover with foil.

title: slimming chicken cacciatore
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients, plus dash of pepper in pan.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove chicken, sprinkle with paprika.
Combine cornstarch and water.
Stir in skillet.
Cook and stir to thicken.
Cook 1 minute more.
Spoon sauce over chicken. Yields 4 servings, 139 calories per serving.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Put bread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and sausage.
Beat eggs with 2 1/4 cups milk and pour over top.
Mix soup with rest of milk and pour over mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Fry hamburger and drain grease.
Put all ingredients into a slow cooker and cook 3 to 4 hours on medium.
Great for cookouts!!

title: *fruit cheese salad
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish, place a layer of each of the following in the bottom:
miniature marshmallows, crushed pineapple, sliced bananas and apricots.
Prepare lemon jello as directed on the back of package and pour over the layered fruit. Let congeal.
Can be made a day ahead and refrigerated overnight to congeal.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8-inch square baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.

title: crab dip
directions: Spread cream cheese about 1 inch thick in serving dish, spread crab meat over cheese and pour cocktail sauce over meat. Delicious with Ritz crackers.
Can use more cream cheese or crab meat according to taste.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spread chopped pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and spread on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
No icing is needed.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Pat out rolls on a cookie sheet; pinch perforations together. Bake crust 10 to 15 minutes, then cool.
Mix room temperature cream cheese, mayo and dry dressing mix together.
Spread on crust.
Chop raw veggies into small pieces and place on cheese mixture. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Pat down, cover with foil and place in refrigerator.
I use broccoli, green peppers, radishes, carrots and onions to make a colorful pizza.

title: lasagne
directions: Put tomatoes, paste and spices in blender.
Add to drained, cooked meats.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes, or until mixture is consistency of spaghetti sauce.
Stir together cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Heat oven to 350°.
In ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, alternate layers, starting with noodles, then cottage cheese mixture, sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
End with noodles and Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses on top.
Bake for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: caramel candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and butter over low heat for 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add milk.
Return to low heat and stir constantly until reaches 237° to 238° on candy thermometer or soft ball stage (takes about 15 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat 10 minutes or until quite stiff.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Put into refrigerator until cool.
When cool, cut into squares or roll pecans to make pecan rolls.
Cut into strips and eat.

title: beef-eggplant bake
directions: Prepare eggplant by paring and cutting to 1/4-inch slices. Beat 3 egg whites until well stiff; add yolks.
Dip eggplant and fry in oil until brown.
Place in layers in a 9 x 13-inch pan, alternating eggplant, tomato, onion and cheese.
Repeat 2 to 3 times.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: bran cereal muffins
directions: Stir bran cereal and milk together; let stand 1 to 2 minutes. Add egg, oil and honey.
Beat well.
Stir remaining ingredients together in separate bowl.
Add to liquid mixture and stir only until mixed.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: miss finney's apple cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and cinnamon onto wax paper.
Combine sugar, eggs, oil, vanilla and orange juice in a large bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until well blended.
Stir in flour mixture until well mixed.
Fold in apples, nuts, and coconut.
Spoon into a well greased and floured 10 x 4-inch angel cake tube pan.
Bake in slow oven 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until top springs back when lightly pressed with fingertips.
Cool in pan or on wire rack 15 minutes.
Remove cake from pan to serving plate with a raised edge. Puncture top of cake all over with wooden pick or skewer.
Spoon hot Buttermilk Sauce over warm cake several times until cake absorbs most of it.
Let stand about an hour before serving.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Combine cheese, soup and dip, onion and peppers and mix well.
Fold into hash browns.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in 9/13 pan.
Top with 1/2 sausage.
Spread rest of mixture on top ending with sausage.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Serves 12-14.

title: vegie pizza
directions: Pat 1 1/2 to 2 packages of crescent rolls in bottom of cookie sheet.
Bake according to package directions and cool.

title: rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into a 13 x 9 inch glass dish. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spoon bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, scald cornmeal with boiling water. Add eggs, salt, sugar and margarine.
Mix well.
Add milk.
If mixture is not as thin as water, add more milk.
Finally add baking powder and blend.
Pour into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with pats of margarine.

title: corn chowder
directions: In heavy saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Add all other ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields about 2 quarts or 6 to 8 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Drain.
Put into a large casserole dish.
Add celery soup.
Mix well.
Sprinkle dry soup mix on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix cracker crumbs with melted margarine.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to
40 minutes.

title: rachel's bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let rise, punch down twice and let rise double in bulk.
Grease loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on package.
Add the crushed pineapple (drained).
Place in container and let thicken in refrigerator.
Fold in last 4 ingredients and chill until firm.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Combine Oreo crumbs and margarine. Mix well. Reserve 1/2 cup mixture. Press in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread ice cream over crust. Drizzle with chocolate syrup. Spread Cool Whip over top. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs. Garnish with almonds. Freeze for at least 12 hours before serving.

title: fruit fantasy
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream until smooth and fluffy; set aside.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in cream cheese mixture until well blended.
Drain fruit, reserving juice to make 1 1/2 cups combined.
Reserve a few peaches for garnish.
Stir juice and soda into jello mixture.
Refrigerate until thick.
Cut peaches into bite size.
Fold fruit and marshmallows into thick jello mix. Pour into 7 cup mold.
Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with mint and reserved peach slices.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Mix well.
Place in ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Best for dipping with any kind of chips.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add 1 beaten egg and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch pan. When cool, frost with 1 pint whipped cream with a little powdered sugar added.

title: annie's green hot sauce
directions: Dice all vegetables; add to the rest of the ingredients.
Place in pan; cook on medium-high until tender.
Spoon into a blender and chop.
Place in covered container; store in refrigerator.
This can be put in canning jars and canned.
Cook for 30 minutes on medium-high heat (in your canner) after water starts to boil.
This is good on a cool day in chili, on tacos, in hot dog sauce or even as a chip dip.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; set aside. Measure cereal and milk into mixing bowl and stir to combine.
Let stand 1 to 2 minutes or until cereal is softened.
Add egg and oil to cereal mixture.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Stir in raisins.
Portion batter evenly into 12 greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until muffins are golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: gazpacho
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill 24 to 48 hours to blend flavors. Add a dollop of sour cream to each bowl, if desired.

title: mushroom ball
directions: Mix above ingredients together and chill.
After chilled a few hours, form into a ball.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine the ingredients in an appropriate container and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground round as you would make your meatballs.
Shape into small meatballs.
Mix currant jelly and ketchup together; heat. Brown meatballs in oven.
Pour jelly and ketchup mixture over meatballs and stir.

title: rice and nut vegetable loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put in oiled baking dish and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Remove from oven and immediately turn out onto platter.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spray baking dish with pan spray and place mixture in dish.
Bake 60 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: french muffins
directions: Combine shortening, half of the sugar, and egg; mix thoroughly.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, and nutmeg. Stir into egg mixture alternately with milk.
Beat well after each addition.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately roll in melted butter and then in mixture of remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Serve hot.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Add spices, salt, molasses and vinegar; stir well.
Add soda and flour and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In a large pan, brown the bacon and cook onion, celery, garlic and basil until tender.
Stir in soups, water, tomatoes, macaroni and salt.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cabbage and zucchini.
Cook 10 minutes or until done.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Beat in eggs and food coloring.
Sift together cocoa, flour and salt.
Add dry ingredients.
Alternate with buttermilk.
Mix vinegar, vanilla and baking powder; add to the batter.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat; drain grease.
In a 5-quart pan, combine all ingredients; mix together well.
Add chili powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring just to a boil and then turn heat to simmer. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with cheese and crackers.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in water; set aside.
In mixing bowl, combine cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda and egg.
Mix until blended.
Stir in softened yeast.
Gradually add flour to form stiff dough.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place for about 1 hour.
Stir down dough.

title: snappy green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Cook onion in reserved fat until tender.
Add vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour over hot cooked, drained beans.
Crumble bacon atop.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop onion, dried beef and green pepper fine.
Add to softened cream cheese and olives.
Mix thoroughly and chill for 2 hours or more.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk together.
Grease rectangular pan with stick of butter.
Pour in sugar, flour and milk mixture.
Add blackberry pie filling.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Boil water, vinegar, sugar and salt for 1 minute.
Let cool. Pour over other ingredients and let stand overnight and it's ready to eat.

title: four flavored pound cake
directions: Spray tube or Bundt pan with vegetable (oil) spray; dust with flour and set aside. Combine flour plus next 3 ingredients in large bowl. Add oil and milk. Beat at medium speed until smooth. Add lemon rind and next 4 ingredients.
Fold in 1/3 egg whites. Gently fold in remaining egg whites. Pour batter into pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan. Cool on rack.
Serve 3/4 cup fresh strawberries with each slice. Makes 16 servings. Contains 183 calories per 1/2 inch slice.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix and drop by spoonfuls in hot oil (375°) and fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain and serve.

title: brussels sprouts medley(makes 4 servings)
directions: Trim stem ends and any discolored leaves from Brussels sprouts.
Cut an "X" into stem of each.
Cook in about 1-inch boiling salted water, uncovered 4 to 5 minutes, then covered until just tender, 3 to 5 minutes longer (or steam over boiling water until just tender, 8 to 10 minutes).

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll and put in refrigerator.
Cut into thin slices.
Bake at 350° until done.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: aunt leona's orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water. Mix well.
Add sherbet and juice from mandarin oranges.
Beat with electric mixer until foamy.
Let set until partly set.
Stir in mandarin oranges.
Pour into mold or other dish.
Refrigerate.

title: southern crab cakes
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Shape mixture into 8 small cakes.
Chill for several hours.
Combine egg with 2 tablespoons water in bowl.
Coat crab cakes with flour. Dip into egg mixture.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Saute over high heat in Parkay in skillet until golden brown.

title: baked pumpkin custard
directions: Spray a 1 1/2-quart casserole with nonstick cooking spray. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; stir well until blended. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce oven to 350° for 45 minutes or until inserted knife in center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.
Garnish with whipped topping, if desired.

title: ginger sparkles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and molasses.
Mix flour, ginger, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Mix thoroughly.
Form into small balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place on greased baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove to a rack to cool.
Store in airtight container or freeze.
Yields about 5 dozen cookies.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender. Remove from heat and take meat off bone. Reserve chicken broth to mix with ingredients. Tear bread into small pieces. In large bowl, add chicken, celery and onion. Mix well. Add chicken broth, cream of chicken soup and sage (to taste). Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: baked squash ritz
directions: Cook squash and onion; drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients and put in greased casserole.
Top with 1/4 cup additional crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sausage and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until light brown.

title: graham puffs
directions: Combine crumbs and flour.
Set aside.
In saucepan over high heat, heat water, margarine and salt until margarine melts and mixture boils. Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in crumb mixture, beating vigorously with wooden spoon until mixture leaves sides of pan in a ball. Add eggs, one at a time, beating until thoroughly blended.
Chill pan in ice water until completely cooled. Drop batter on cookie sheet in 6 mounds, swirling top of each.
Bake in preheated "hot" oven (400°) about 40 minutes.
Turn off oven. With sharp knife, make a small slit in side of each puff.
Leave puffs in oven with door closed 30 minutes longer. Cool.
Cut off top of puffs carefully with sharp knife. Fill with your favorite creamy pudding filling.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple slices
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and Crisco.
Separate egg (save the white).
To the yolk, add enough milk to make 2/3 cup.
Add to flour mixture.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll out to fit a cookie sheet (pliable dough).
Put on bottom of cookie sheet.

title: sugar jumbles
directions: Mix well together the butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Then sift together the remaining ingredients and add to the first mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in 375°
oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cookies should still be soft.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of pan. Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread over crust.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and then add remaining and blend. Pour into medium muffin tins which have been lined with paper cups.
Freeze until firm.
Remove papers to serve.
Will fill 10 muffin cups.

title: cobia in sour cream sauce
directions: Cut steaks into serving size portions and roll in flour, seasoned with salt, paprika and pepper.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Remove onion from the pan and save.
Place fish in a pan.
Fry at moderate heat.
When fish is brown on one side, turn carefully and brown the other side.
Cooking time is approximately 10 minutes, depending on the thickness of the fish. Cover with the onion, sweet basil and sour cream.
Cover and simmer for five minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves six.

title: fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl combine apples and bananas; add fruit cocktail and nuts.
Mix ingredients with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Add vanilla.
Chill.
For added flavor, add a small box of flavored jello to Cool Whip before mixing with fruit.

title: strawberry triumph pie
directions: Divide 1 quart of strawberries in half.
Crush half of berries and add cornstarch, sugar and lemon juice.
Stir over medium heat until thick and clear.
Cool.
Add last half of berries to cooled mixture.
Pour into baked pie crust.
When chilled, cover with whipped topping.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in eggs.
Add combined dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with milk and juice, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: nut ball cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts. Chill thoroughly.
Roll in balls and bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Immediately roll in powdered sugar three times.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients; pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: low-fat boiled custard
directions: Heat milk to scalding.
Beat egg yolks; add 3 to 4 tablespoons hot milk to yolks.
Stir. Stir back into custard.
After this has thickened, add 1/4 cup water to 2 tablespoons cornstarch and stir into yolks.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Stiffly beat egg whites and add to mixture.
Do not boil the boiled custard as it will cause it to curdle.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° on a cookie sheet with sides for 25 minutes.
Cut.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Bake cake in a jelly roll pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix the milk with the 2 pudding mixes.
Add all the other ingredients; blend well.
Cover the cooled cake with this mixture.

title: nomie's green salad
directions: Make Jell-O with 1/2 amount of boiling water.
Let it set until soft jelly stage.
Combine Jell-O and cream cheese in blender; blend until milky.
Fold in celery, pineapple and nuts (more nuts may be used if you like).
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or into a mold.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers thinly, take skins off, put in bowl and sprinkle with salt.
Let sit 15 minutes.
Pour off excess liquid. Mix together other ingredients; pour on cucumbers.
Let sit 20 minutes.
Put in jar with liquid; store in refrigerator.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add pineapple (20 ounce) and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until fluffy and fold into pineapple mix.
Pour into 2 small or 1 large unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until pie shell is done.
The top will be golden brown.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Let ice cream soften, then in a large container, put ice cream and Cool Whip and mix together.
In a bag, break up Oreos into pieces.
Add to ice cream and mix well.
Spoon into cake pan and smooth out.
Cover and put into freezer until firm.

title: congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling point.
Add gelatin and soften cream cheese to pineapple mixture and heat until cream cheese is mixed well and then take off burner.
Place gelatin mixture into bowl and add nuts and fold in whipped cream.
Place dish into the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef across grain into 1/4-inch slices.
Cut slices to make 2 x 1-inch pieces.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Sear meat in 2 tablespoons hot oil over medium-high heat, until browned; remove beef.
Saute onion until tender.
Add mushrooms; continue cooking until tender.
Add broth and tomato paste; stir until smooth. Blend in sour cream.
Add beef, along with any juices in bowl and parsley.
Bring sauce to a simmer; cook 5 minutes or until meat is heated through and sauce thickens.
Serve with noodles.

title: fettucine with chicken in parmesan cream
directions: Spray 10-inch skillet with cooking oil.
Heat for 1 minute. Add chicken and cook 3 minutes, then remove.
Melt margarine.
Add garlic and cook 1 minute.
Add flour and cook, stirring constantly with whisk, for 1 minute.
Slowly add milk and cook until bubbly and thick.
Add cheese, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add pasta, broccoli and chicken.
Ready to serve.
(Weight Watchers.)

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Add 1 teaspoon of oil to cooking water.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Set aside. Mix last 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Add spaghetti and toss to coat well.
Chill at least 6 hours or overnight.
Stir 2 or 3 times while chilling.

title: mint julep
directions: Bring sugar and water to a rolling boil.
Cool and refrigerate in a jar with a lid.
Take a sprig of mint; place in bottom of the julep cup.
Add crushed ice to the top of the glass and bruise mint leaves.
Pour in simple syrup, leaving room to add 1 or more ounces of bourbon.
Garnish with a sprig of mint and a straw.

title: honey's sweet potato pie
directions: Bake sweet potatoes until soft.
Mash and blend with sugar, flour and margarine.
Add beaten eggs and blend.
Add raisins, nutmeg, cinnamon and flavoring.
Add milk gradually and blend well.

title: coney island spread
directions: Grind together with food chopper and mix thoroughly.
Makes a large amount for sandwiches.

title: hot pizza dish
directions: Brown ground beef and mix all ingredients but the Mozzarella cheese together and bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Add the Mozzarella cheese on top and bake 5 more minutes.

title: pork chops 'n stuffing
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in oven-proof skillet and pour off drippings.
Lightly mix bread cubes, onion, butter, 1/4 cup water, poultry seasoning and pinch of sage.
Place a mound of stuffing on each chop.
Blend mushroom soup with 1/3 cup water; pour over.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Stir often until brown.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake corn bread mix according to directions, cool and crumble. Combine all ingredients.

title: holiday cranberry sauce
directions: Cranberries become sweeter the more they are thawed and refrozen.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, maple syrup, milk, nutmeg, butter, nuts and salt.
Add eggs and pour into buttered shallow pan.
Bake in a moderately hot oven (375°) for 50 to 60 minutes. Serves 6.

title: everyday cake
directions: In 8-inch layer cake or square pan, stir all ingredients with rubber spatula until well blended.
Scrape down sides of pan. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan on rack.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan thoroughly with Pam or Mazola oil spray.
Put 8 slices of bread in pan.
Top with ham and cheese. Put the remaining 8 slices on top.
Beat eggs; add milk and mustard.
Pour over bread slices.
Let set overnight in refrigerator, covered.
Before baking, melt 1/2 cup oleo and 3 cups finely crushed cornflakes and put on top.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven (325° for Pyrex).
Use only glass, enamel or Baker's Secret pans.
Do not use aluminum or badly scratched pans.

title: ellie's potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft (not brown).
Add potatoes and milk.
Cook a few minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook and stir.

title: chocolate candy cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar; mix well and set aside.
Combine water, butter and cocoa in heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in flour mixture.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
While warm, prick surface and spread with Chocolate Candy Frosting.

title: veg-chilli
directions: Saute chopped vegetables in oil.
Add ingredients; mix and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Season with chili powder to taste.

title: orange chiffon
directions: Mix gelatin and hot water until dissolved.
Stir in cold water. Refrigerate until it starts to thicken to a jello consistency. Fold in oranges and pineapple, then fold in Cool Whip until well blended.
Pour into four cup molds or serving bowls.
Refrigerate until set, about 4 hours.

title: granny stephens tea cakes
directions: Mix salt, sugar, flour, soda and baking powder together first, then add milk, vanilla and butter.
Beat eggs.
Add to mixture. Put into freezer until you set oven and grease cookie sheet.
Roll into small balls and pat flat.
Bake at 350°.

title: orange chicken with broccoli
directions: Combine chicken and soy sauce in plastic bag. Seal and chill 15 minutes. Cook broccoli in boiling water 3 minutes. Stop cooking process in ice water. Drain and set aside. Drain chicken, reserving soy sauce. Dredge chicken in cornstarch. Brown chicken in oil over medium heat until done. Remove chicken and keep warm. Reserve drippings in skillet. Add soy sauce, onion and next 5 ingredients to skillet and saute until vegetables are tender. Add chicken broth and marmalade, stirring until marmalade is melted. Return chicken to skillet. Bring to a boil. Stir in broccoli and orange sections. Serve immediately.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken into large, bite size pieces; season with ginger, garlic and pepper.
Stir-fry in hot wok or skillet in 1 tablespoon oil until brown and cooked through (do not overcook).
Place torn romaine in bowl.
Put the chicken on the lettuce in the center; sprinkle chow mein noodles around the edge.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients over the chicken.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small pan and heat to blend flavors.
Great for any barbecue.
If onion soup mix is not used, add 1/2 teaspoon salt to the recipe.

title: yellow squash pickles
directions: In a large pot, let mixture of all ingredients, except squash, come to a boil.
Add squash and boil 5 minutes.
Seal in jars. Boil in hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: low-fat curry dip
directions: Separate squash from its shell and place in a 9 x 12-inch greased baking dish.
Mix in carrots, margarine and seasonings. Top with Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and dish is heated through.
Makes 6 to 8 (1/2 cup) portions.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt
margarine in a saucepan.
Add sugar and cocoa and stir well.
Add eggs and stir mixture, do not beat.
Add milk and vanilla
and pour in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for
minutes,
then reduce heat to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or
until
crust
is brown.
This is delicious topped with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Combine sugar, water and spices in deep saucepan or deep-fat fryer. Simmer 10 minutes; strain. Add orange juice, grapefruit juice and cider. Reheat. Garnish with orange slices with candied cherry in center of each slice.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In an 8 x 10-inch pan, pick a head of lettuce in pieces to make one layer.
Then add chopped onions, green pepper and celery. Sprinkle cooked peas.
Spread Hellmann's mayonnaise over layers. Sprinkle with sugar.
Put grated Cheddar cheese and crumbled bacon on top.
Cover tightly with foil and refrigerate.

title: carrots in cinnamon sauce
directions: Clean carrots; place in saucepan.
Sprinkle other ingredients over carrots.
Cover with water.
Simmer for 7 to 8 minutes. Remove carrots.
Boil sauce for 2 minutes (or until it thickens). Pour over carrots.

title: eggplant saute
directions: Dice and saute onion and green pepper in a little olive oil and the garlic.
Dice eggplant and add.
Simmer for about 1/2 hour or until very tender.
Add stewed tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Preparation time:
1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: escalloped carrots(freda adams - bethel, ohio)
directions: Cook sliced carrots until just tender.
Save drained liquid for soup.
Saute onion in butter 2 or 3 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard, pepper and celery salt.
Blend in milk and cook. Stir until smooth.
Alternate layers of carrots and cheese.
Pour sauce over and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: grape wine
directions: Put in gallon container, first filling with water. Stretch balloon over top of jug. Let set for 3 weeks, then enjoy it.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Measure sifted flour.
Add baking powder and salt.
Sift together.
Cream the butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar gradually and beat until smooth and creamy.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour alternately with the milk, beating after each addition until smooth.
Fold in coconut.
Pour batter into a 10-inch tube pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted into cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes, then remove.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Core, pare and slice the apples.
Line a deep pie pan with pastry.
Spread a layer of apples over the bottom; sprinkle with mixture of sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Repeat layers until all apples and mixture are used.
Spread the sour cream over the top. Moisten the rim of the pastry; add the top sheet of dough, making 2 to 3 slits in the top to allow steam to escape.
Press the top to the bottom crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then lower temperature to 375° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes more or until the apples are tender and the crust is golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add eggs to all ingredients except pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Decorate with pecans, being careful pecans do not sink to bottom of pie.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pie will seem uncooked when hot, but will thicken as it cools.

title: pecan pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each.
Beat in flour until smooth.
Add vanilla and chopped pecans.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted margarine.
Add beaten eggs and pecans to syrup mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake in a 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: aunt dixie's company best pickles
directions: Cover whole cucumbers with boiling water; let stand overnight. Drain.
Repeat the procedure 4 more days.
On the fifth day, drain and slice in 1/2-inch pieces.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice as thin as possible.
Chop onions and sweet peppers.
Combine with cucumbers and salt; let stand 3 hours in ice and drain.

title: carrot salad
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook in salt water and drain.
Mix all remaining ingredients.
Mix carrots with ingredients and marinate.
Serve warm or cold.

title: basic best salmon loaf
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Slightly beat eggs.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Bake in an 8 x 4-inch loaf tin.
If using less of the liquid, make into patties and brown in frying pan.
Bake loaf at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix preceding ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.
Bake at 450° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken crescent roll-ups
directions: Stew chicken until tender.
Let cool.
Cut off bone and chop. Heat soup, milk and cheese in saucepan.
Unroll crescent rolls and place chicken at large end; roll up.
Put in casserole dish and pour sauce over rolls.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until rolls are brown.

title: jalapeno pepper dip
directions: Grind cheese, onions and pepper together.
Mix mayonnaise with salt and 6 tablespoons pepper juice.
Mix all together and let set for a while before serving.

title: hummer pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in freezer for 4 hours, uncovered.
Cover and will keep up to 2 weeks in freezer.
This recipe will fill 2 ready-made pie crusts.

title: crunchy salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add cashews just before serving. Refrigerate.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix eggs, milk, oil and corn. Add cheese and chilies.
Mix dry and liquid together.
Bake in square cake pan at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: italian beef
directions: *Can use mild banana peppers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cajun potatoes a la scott
directions: Heat Dutch oven and fry bacon.
Remove bacon and drain. When cool,
crumble
bacon.
You can reserve some bacon fat or use some oil
or
butter
to
cook
the potatoes.
In the same Dutch
oven, heat
and
cook
the
cubed
potatoes,
stirring constantly. When
potatoes
are
almost tender, add onion and continue cooking until potatoes are tender.
Add green beans, bacon and Creole seasoning.
Mix well and when green beans are warm, serve.

title: pudding torte
directions: Mix softened butter, flour and 3 tablespoons powdered sugar together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Cool completely.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Combine first five ingredients and mix until blended.
Sift flour, soda and salt in a separate bowl.
Add rhubarb and nuts to liquid ingredients and add flour mixture.
Do not overmix.
Pour batter into 2 large or 4 small loaf pans, which have been greased and floured.
Before baking, sprinkle top with cinnamon-sugar. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate lover's delight - trifle
directions: Bake chocolate cake mix as directed and prepare instant pudding as directed.
Break cake into pieces when cool.
Crunch up chocolate bars.
Put ingredients in layers in a large glass bowl: cake pieces, pudding, Cool Whip, Skor Bars.
Repeat layers.
Can make a day ahead.

title: 4-layer chocolate delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix together the flour, oleo and pecans.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° until brown.
Let cool.

title: garden vegetables casserole
directions: Place all sliced vegetables in casserole dish and mix all other ingredients.
Toss lightly.
Cover and microwave on high for 8-10 minutes.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and set aside to cool.
In large bowl, pour Wesson oil over the cake mix and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Add Jell-O water.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: famous company casserole
directions: Pan-fry beef in large skillet.
Cook until browned thoroughly. Pour off excess fat.
Add salt, onion and tomato sauce.
Cook about 1 minute and remove from heat.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Drain.
Mix together the cheeses, sour cream, pepper and onion.
Add to the cooked noodles; blend.
Pour into 3-quart casserole and top with the meat mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: jello salad
directions: Add 2 cups boiling water to Jell-O.
Dissolve.
Add pineapple and strawberry filling in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill.

title: holiday cheese tree
directions: Combine cheeses, mixing until well blended.
Mix well with the rest of the ingredients except parsley and nuts.
Drop mixture into tree shape.
Top with parsley, tree base with nuts.
Use remaining pimentos as decorations.
Spread on crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: butterscotch sweet rolls(serves 14)
directions: Thaw frozen bread for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cut the long way and then cut each half into 7 pieces.
Grease Bundt pan. Sprinkle pan with 1/3 cup chopped nuts.
Put in the bread pieces. Sprinkle the top with a little cinnamon, 1/2 box of butterscotch pudding mix, 1/2 cup white sugar and 1 tablespoon brown sugar. Melt 3/4 cup of margarine and pour over all.
Sprinkle remaining 1/3 cup chopped nuts on top.
Cover with a towel overnight.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: uncooked fundoughs #2
directions: When our kids get together they talk about how they remember breakfast first and foremost.
Karen used no special recipes in the preparation, the memorability stemmed more from the materials used and the timing.
Pancakes, juice or fruit, cereal and of course homemade syrup as it contained less or no sugar.
(There was a long period when Karen used no sugar in food preparation!)
The following is a description of the timing as best as I can recall it:

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients or beat well. Bake in 3 layers at 350° until done.

title: basic alfredo sauce
directions: Saute onion in the vegetable oil until tender.
Stir in the flour and garlic until smooth.
Slowly stir in the evaporated skim milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and begins to thicken, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese, basil and black pepper.
Serve on hot pasta. Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: choco-peanut butter sauce
directions: In a 4-cup glass measure, heat chocolate with milk on High in microwave for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is melted. Stir, then stir in sugar.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until mixture boils. Add peanut butter and vanilla. Stir until blended. Serve hot or cold over ice cream, pound cake or sliced bananas.
Makes 1 cup.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saut onions and celery in butter until tender.
Mix all ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: deviled ham ball
directions: Thoroughly mix deviled ham and cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Shape in ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: black magic cake
directions: Mix together well the flour, sugar, soda, baking powder, salt and cocoa. Add coffee, buttermilk, eggs, oil and vanilla. Beat well. Batter will be thin. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Dip pork chops in ranch dressing, then roll in bread crumb/parmesan cheese mixture. Bake uncovered in 375 degree oven in 13 X 9 pan for 30 minutes or longer.

title: corn soup in bread bowls(for 2)
directions: Cut lid in bread and hollow out.
Saute onion in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Stir in corn, potato, bell pepper, half and half, chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes. Ladle soup into bread "bowls" and garnish with parsley.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Separate onion slices into rings.
Combine all ingredients, except mushrooms, in small pan.
Bring to boil.
Meanwhile, wash and boil mushrooms.
Add to mixture in saucepan after drained. Simmer 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool and chill in a covered bowl for several hours.

title: louisiana oyster stew
directions: Heat milk to boiling in saucepan, stirring constantly.
Add celery and potatoes and cook for 5 minutes.
Add oysters and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Bring to boil again and let simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour into soup plate.
Place 1 pat of butter on each serving and sprinkle with paprika.

title: marinade for older fowl or animal
directions: Optional:
One can cranberry juice will hasten marinating process and enhance flavor.

title: company applesauce
directions: Saute the nuts in butter until golden brown over low heat. Add brown sugar and crushed crackers.
Mix well.
Place crumb mixture over bottom of loaf pan (save 1/2 cup for top).
Pour applesauce over crumbs. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with reserved crumbs. Can be used as salad or dessert.

title: continal chicken
directions: Season chicken with all seasoning.
Slice chicken into small strips.
Roll then in a circle wrapped in bacon.
Layer one layer of chicken in bottom of crock-pot, then one layer of dried beef. Mix the soup and sour cream together in a large bowl.
Now a layer of the soup mixture and then layer again as before making sure you end up with the soup mixture on top.
Cook on low in the crock for 7 or 8 hours.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as package directs; drain.
Melt margarine in saucepan. Remove from heat. Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth. Gradually stir in milk and bring to a boil, stirring.

Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in 1 1/2 cups cheese and the macaroni. Pour into 2-quart casserole and sprinkle remaining cheese over top. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl. Beat until well blended. Add the flour, baking powder and salt. Work the ingredients together with a spoon until the dough is smooth. Pinch small pieces of dough and roll into 1-inch balls. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet 2-inches apart. Flatten cookie with the bottom of a glass lightly greased and dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar and half of the cold water in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Dissolve cornstarch in remaining cold water, and whisk gradually into syrup mix.
Cook over low heat until clear, whisking frequently.
Add salt, lemon juice and food color.
Pour over berries, stir lightly to coat, and let cool.
Add to baked pie shell.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: meat loaf
directions: Make into loaf.
Mix
cup brown sugar and ketchup to make a sauce.
Put
holes	in
meat
loaf and pour sauce over. Bake in moderate oven 1 hour or until done.

title: dan melvin's crisp corn bread
directions: Preheat an 8-inch iron skillet (hot).
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Pour batter into the iron skillet.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes or until done.

title: donna's dessert
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions until done with just enough water to cover them.
Do not drain off water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: In large 9 x 12-inch buttered baking dish, spread a layer of cracker crumbs, then oysters with juice and salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle nutmeg to season.
Place butter pat slices on top.
Cover with remaining cracker crumbs.
Pour whipping cream over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to bake, add a little half and half, if needed.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: italian lentils
directions: Place lentils
in saucepan with enough boiling water to cover. Lightly boil 30 minutes, adding more water, if needed. Add remaining
ingredients
and simmer 30 minutes more.
Serve over rice.
Especially nice with MAZIDRA.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: southern burgers
directions: Brown beef and onion in hot fat.
Drain.
Stir in catsup, mustard and soup.
Simmer until mixture thickens (to desired) about 15 to 20 minutes.
Spoon over toasted split buns.
(May be made early and refrigerated, then heated.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix filling ingredients, then pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.
Can substitute chocolate pie crust.

title: popovers
directions: Mix ingredients just until moistened.
Pour batter into well greased jumbo muffin tins.
Only fill each 1/2 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 450 degrees.
Reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake for an additional 20 minutes.
Serve hot!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soups and milk; put into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix stuffing mix with some broth from chicken, until thick enough to spread.
Spread evenly over chicken mixture and bake at 350° until bubbly on top and brown.

title: honey drops
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with hot water.
Add vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon, bake in moderate oven.
Ice with powdered sugar icing. Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli until tender and drain.
Mix eggs, salt, butter and flour.
Fold in broccoli and creamed corn and cheese. Put in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. (May make the night before and then pop into oven the next day.) Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone.
Mix sour cream, mushroom soup, diluted with 1/2 can of milk and stir in chicken.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix the small package of stuffing mix with the melted oleo and then add the hot water.
Crumble or sprinkle the stuffing mix over the chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May be made ahead of time and refrigerated until ready to bake.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: frozen lemon squares
directions: Combine butter, crumbs and sugar.
Press in bottom of 9-inch pan.

title: refrigerator yeast dough
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in lukewarm water.
Combine hot potato water or	milk
with
shortening, sugar and salt.
Stir until shortening is
melted and sugar and salt are dissolved.
Cool and
add well beaten eggs and dissolved yeast; mix thoroughly. Add about 1/2 of the flour and beat mixture well.
Add remaining
flour
and
mix thoroughly	but do not knead.
Brush the inside
of
a large bowl with shortening.
Put dough into this bowl, brush dough with shortening, cover and put in refrigerator.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Toss together all ingredients, except almonds and lettuce leaves.
Spoon individual portions onto lettuce leaves.
Garnish with 1 chopped almond per serving.

title: ham and potatoes
directions: Cut ham in inch pieces.
Make gravy with butter and flour, but do not brown.
Add 1/2 milk and water to make gravy.
Put ham in gravy and cook on low heat for 45 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat oil in a skillet.
Saute onion, garlic and green pepper until softened.
Stir in flour, tomatoes, chicken broth and wine until thickened.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces and add to onions along with mushrooms, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: barbecue beef hash
directions: Cook stew beef until tender.
Drain and save broth.
Mince beef. Add all ingredients and 1 cup broth.
Cook slowly on low heat for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
If hash gets dry, add more broth.

title: ratatouille(mediterranean vegetable stew)
directions: Cook and stir all ingredients until heated through.
Cover and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pat's prune cake
directions: Cream together oil, eggs, sugar, flour and buttermilk.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until blended.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in a Bundt pan.
Leave cake in pan and add topping.

title: vegetable-lentil chowder
directions: Combine lentils, water and salt in large saucepan.
Cook, covered, over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Cook onion and pepper in butter until tender.
Combine all ingredients; simmer, covered, 30 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Coat roast with flour.
In nonstick Dutch oven, brown roast in oil; remove.
Add water, vinegar, and broth mix to pot and cook 1 minute stirring.
Return roast to pot; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place vegetables around roast. Cover.
Bake 2 3/4 hours or until tender, turning once.
Remove roast and slice.
Return beef to pan and simmer 5 minutes.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix Tang, evaporated milk and sour cream.
Add Cool Whip. Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Top with pecans.
Refrigerate for an hour or more.
Can eat one and freeze the other for later use.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spread Tater Tots in 9 x 12 x 2-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle ham and mushrooms evenly over entire top, covering all Tots.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Serves 10 or more.
For easy clean up, first line cake pan with foil.

title: creamy sautéed cucumbers with dill
directions: In large skillet, cook garlic in oil over low heat, stirring until it begins to color. Add cukes; cook over moderate heat, stirring until cukes are tender and wilted. Stir in the vinegar and cream. Cook for 3 minutes, stirring until it thickens slightly. Remove from heat; stir in the dill and salt and pepper to taste.

title: ginger cookies(mom's gingerbread men)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Combine shortening, sugar, molasses and egg yolk and beat.
Add to dry ingredients, mix well. Chill overnight.
Roll out and cut.
Dough will be crumbly, but gets moist as you work it.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Decorate it desired.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in salt water until clear.
Mix mayonnaise, eggs, green pepper and onion.
Drain zucchini; add to mixture. Fold in Parmesan cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Cut chicken into medium pieces and spread into 13 x 9-inch cooking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together and stir in with chicken.
Crumble crackers on top and sprinkle poppy seeds on top.
Pour melted butter over top and bake for 35 minutes at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt butter, soup and sour cream.
Pour thawed potatoes in to coat well.
Add cheese.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 to 45 minutes, until brown and crispy.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Mix all other ingredients; add spinach.
Make 1-inch balls, place on cookie sheet and let stand 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 9 x 13 egg casserole
directions: Make night before.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check with toothpick.

title: brussels sprouts au gratin
directions: Place hot cooked Brussels sprouts in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with cheese spread.
Set aside.
Place butter in a 1 cup measure.
Microwave on High until butter melts.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Toss to coat.
Scatter crumb mixture over Brussels sprouts.
Microwave 30 seconds to 1 minute on High, or until cheese melts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix everything together except soup and water.
Make balls at least 2 inches in diameter.
Place in baking dish.
Pour soup and water over it.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate cereal treats
directions: Microwave margarine in 4-quart microwavable bowl on High 45 seconds or until melted.
Add marshmallows.
Mix to coat. Microwave 1 1/2 minutes or until marshmallows are smooth when stirred, stirring after 45 seconds.
Add cereal.
Mix to coat well.
Press firmly into lightly greased foil lined 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool.
Turn onto cutting surface.
Peel off foil.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut into bite-size pieces. Cook rice according to package instructions. Add all other ingredients into chicken and rice mixture and put into deep casserole dish to allow room for stirring. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until hot and bubbly. Stir once or twice during baking.

title: cheese pie
directions: Blend cheese and milk; blend with mixer until smooth.
Blend in lemon juice and vanilla; add to graham cracker crust. Refrigerate for one hour.
Serve with berries.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Coat meat with seasoned flour.
Brown in oil.
Add barbecue sauce, vinegar and water.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Add green pepper strips and marmalade during last 15 minutes.
Serve over boiled rice.

title: arroz con black-eyed peas(rice with black-eyed peas)
directions: Cook 1st four items on simmer.
Add rice, liquids and seasonings; stir well and bring to boil.
Add peas.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.

title: swiss and onion vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can of French fried onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.

title: crab camembert bread
directions: Drain crab and flake.
Remove cheese rind and cut into chunks. Melt butter in a saucepan; add cheese, parsley, garlic and basil, on medium heat until blended; stir constantly.
Fold in crab.
Cut bread in half lengthwise and dig out small ditch in center of bread.
Spread in crab/cheese mixture (mushrooms are optional). Place on a baking sheet.
Brown 5 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Slice in 1/2-inch pieces and serve immediately.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: In separate bowl, mix together flour and sugar. Cut butter into dry ingredients until crumbly. Pour fruit into 9 x 9 baking dish. Sprinkle with dry mixture. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: brown bread
directions: Combine and cover with plate 45 minutes.

title: spicy burrito bake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. Mix flour, milk, eggs and baking powder together and spread into pan.
Saute onion in margarine.
Mix onion, meat, beans, taco seasonings and salsa.
Pour over batter in pan and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until cheese is browned. Makes 8 servings.
Low-fat.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on until done, approximately 20 minutes.
Peel off potato skin, if desired, while still warm. Bring eggs to a boil, remove from heat and let stand in hot water 20 minutes.
Peel eggs under cold water.
Mix cut up potatoes, eggs, onion and celery.
For dressing, mix vinegar Miracle Whip, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix with potato mixture. Refrigerate.
Let mixture blend for several hours before serving. (1 potato = approx. 2 servings.
Adjust amount as needed.)

title: low-fat tiramisu
directions: *Do not use yogurt that contains gelatin; it does not allow the whey to drip from the yogurt.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and spices.
Add plums, oil and beaten egg.
Add nuts.
Just mix this cake.
Don't beat.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour in greased and floured tube pan.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a large microwavable bowl; cook on High for 8 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla and cook for 90 seconds.
Quickly add soda and pour into buttered jelly roll pan. Let cool and break into pieces.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt. Bring to a boil. Add raw peanuts and cook until small amount dropped in cold water forms a hard ball. Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir.
Pour into a buttered pan or platter.

title: adobo-filipino chicken
directions: In a large roasting pan (don't use an aluminum pan), place cut up chicken. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir so all the chicken gets coated with liquid.
Bake in covered roaster for 3 hours in a 275° oven. Turn occasionally so chicken is done evenly. Serve with rice and broccoli.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Chop tomato and onion finely.
Mash avocados and add to onion and tomato.
Add garlic salt to taste.
Serve with fresh vegetables or tortilla chips.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Steam carrots to desired doneness.
Add remaining ingredients; serve.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, butter, milk and egg.
Beat on low speed until very stiff dough forms.
Mix in chips and coconut or nuts. Drop by teaspoonful 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet or first drop into powdered sugar and turn with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: lima bean chowder
directions: Dice bacon and cook until crisp.
Drain. Cook onions in bacon fat until lightly browned.
Add bacon, potatoes, carrots, lima beans and salt.
Cover with boiling water.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add white sauce. Heat and serve.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a baking dish.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: cajun herb mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour into jar, seal tightly and store in cool, dark place.
This mix is delicious in all Cajun foods from sauces to seafood dishes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter, add milk and brown sugar and cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring the mixture until it comes to a boil. Remove from heat and cool.
Add confectioners sugar until it's the right consistency to spread.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in molasses.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, soda, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with hot water. Turn into well-greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
