directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs well.
Add Karo, sugar and vanilla.
Beat well; add melted oleo.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Middle should not be set as firm as outside of pie.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; set aside.
Meanwhile, drain and flake tuna; set aside.
Melt margarine, then toss with bread crumbs and set aside.

title: crab and shrimp salad
directions: Combine bread, onion and eggs.
Mix and cover.
Refrigerate overnight. Four hours before serving, add rest of ingredients. Refrigerate.
Makes a large salad. Serves 12.

title: pecan pralines
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine brown sugar, granulated sugar, syrup, butter and salt.
Add boiling water.
Place over heat immediately.
When mixture begins to boil, reduce heat to medium and cook for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and chopped pecans.
Beat until slightly thick.
Drop from tablespoon onto waxed paper.

title: chili
directions: Brown the beef, then add to all the other ingredients in large pot.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: dirt
directions: You will need a large flowerpot and plastic flower.

title: chewies
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa; add egg whites one at a time. Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350°.
When cool, place in freezer for 1 hour.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Remove shells from eggs and halve eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks and place in small bowl.
Mash yolks with fork and add remaining ingredients, except paprika. Mix until fluffy.
Spoon or pipe mixture into egg white halves.
Sprinkle with paprika or garnish with parsley.
Yields 12 servings.

title: braised seasoned pork chops
directions: Note:
This is a good recipe to be sure your pork chops are tender, not tough.

title: raspberry streusel muffins
directions: Grease 12 (3-inch) muffin pan cups.
Heat oven to 400°.
In medium size bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
In small bowl, combine milk, sour cream and vanilla.
In large bowl, with electric mixer, cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg.
Beat until well blended.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk mixture, beating until batter is just combined.
Gently fold in raspberries.

title: indiana style corn dogs
directions: In bowl mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, milk, egg, paprika, mustard and pepper.
Pour mixture into tall glass. Skewer hot dogs with wooden skewers; dip in mixture.
Deep fry at 375° until golden brown.

title: pita-n-brats
directions: Remove casings from brats and brown with onion; drain.
Add Tater Tots and brown until Tater Tots are cooked and crumbled. Serve with 1/2 pita.
Sprinkle with cheese and dab of sour cream.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Add buttermilk. Mix dry ingredients which have been sifted together and blended with shortening.
Knead and roll out or knead and put in bowl in icebox.
Use as needed.

title: kraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate. Will keep well 10 days.

title: batter for fish fillets
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add enough water to make batter thick enough to cling to fillets.
After fish is fried, pour mixture of lemon juice, melted butter and parsley over fish.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl.
Heat 1 cup oil and pour over crackers and seasoning.
Stir well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Stir every 7 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together at room temperature the butter, Crisco and cream cheese.
Add sugar gradually to mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time, then vanilla.
Add cake flour gradually.
Bake at 275° to 300° until done.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, and then refrigerate.
Pour into punch bowl to serve.

title: mexican hot pepper cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: skor cake
directions: Cook cake according to package directions. Bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
When cake is done, immediately punch holes with fork in top and pour Eagle Brand milk over top; next pour caramel sauce over cake.
Let cool and then frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle crushed candy bars over top.
Store cake in refrigerator.

title: crisco chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening. Beat in eggs and vanilla, then add dry ingredients. Fold in chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: applesauce jello
directions: Mix all but nutmeg together.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: bit-of-brie appetizer
directions: Spread pecans in a 9-inch pie plate.
Microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes until toasted. Add Kahlua and sugar. Stir well.
Remove rind from top of Brie.
Discard rind. Place Brie on a microwave-safe serving plate. Spoon pecan mixture over top of Brie.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until Brie softens to desired consistency, giving dish a half turn after 1 minute.
Makes 12 servings.

title: sauce for meatballs
directions: Uncooked meatballs may be easily frozen until ready to cook.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour into baking dish.

title: swiss deer steak
directions: Put oil in pan on high heat.
Flour tenderized deer and brown fast on both sides. Put in casserole dish.

title: berry nice corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin cups.
Combine dry ingredients well.
Combine wet ingredients, except rind and berries.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients; pour in the wet ingredients.
When partially blended, add berries and rind. Mix sparingly; don't overmix.
Fill 12 muffin cups.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage and crumble; drain and cool.
Add eggs, parsley, oregano and cheese.
Mix together.
When bread is thawed,
mash out long way on cookie sheet as flat as possible.
Spread sausage mix down the middle and pinch top together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir sherbet into hot gelatin.
Chill 45 minutes, or until partially set.
Add fruits and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill until firm. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss broccoli, bacon, raisins, onion and seed with Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar.
Chill and serve.
Best if made early on the day you plan to serve it.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder to taste.
Layer a cake pan with tortillas, layer of meat mixture, cover with another layer of tortillas and top with grated cheese.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Blend margarine, peanut butter and sugar together.
Mix in cereal.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls.
Set aside.
In double boiler, melt chocolate and paraffin.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture.
Put on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix well with pastry blender.
Put 1 egg in one cup measure and add enough water to fill.
Mix all together with blender. Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: very strawberry pie
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cubes and stir until melted.
Prepare pie filling mix with 3/4 cup milk as directed on package for pie crust.
Let stand about 2 minutes.

title: carolyn's fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine in warm oven. Mix sugars, milk, Karo syrup and salt and bring to a boil for 11 minutes. Add melted chips and margarine. Add vanilla. Beat until it begins to thicken. Pour onto buttered foil or brown paper.

title: buttermilk pecans
directions: Boil sugar and buttermilk until forms a soft ball.
Add soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in pecans until coated.
Pour on wax paper and spread pecans out.

title: birthday cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavoring and salt.
Mix flour and baking powder.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Add boiling water last.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Top with chocolate chip frosting.

title: chicken soup
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook until chicken is well done.

title: bethany cookies
directions: Blend butter and salad oil. Cream in the sugars.

Beat in the egg and vanilla. Sift together the flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar. Add to the mixture. Work in the oatmeal, coconut, Rice Krispies, chips x 2 and chopped pecans. Drop onto baking sheets (by teaspoons). Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together in a 13 x 9 baking dish.
Top with 2 cups corn flake crumbs and 1/2 cup melted margarine.	Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Place butter in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish or 9-inch round cake dish.
Microwave on High 45 to 60 seconds or until melted. Spread evenly over bottom of dish.
Sprinkle with sugar. Drizzle with honey.
Top with pineapple rings, cutting to fit as necessary. Place cherries in center of rings. Arrange pecan halves around rings. Place dish on inverted saucer.
Microwave on High 3 minutes. Blend cake mix, reserved juice and egg in medium mixing bowl on low speed of electric mixer. Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Spoon batter evenly over fruit.
Place dish on inverted saucer. Reduce power to 50% (Medium).
Microwave 5 minutes rotating 1/4 turn twice during cooking time.
Increase power to High.
Microwave 2 to 5 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool directly on countertop 5 minutes. Loosen edges well and turn out onto plate.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello completely in boiling water.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan and chill.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf.
Garnish with maraschino cherries if desired.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Boil raisins, dates, apples and water for 3 minutes.
Add shortening to melt; cool.
Add remaining ingredients, with nuts last; mix well.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes; cool.
Place in airtight container.
Keep in fridge; can freeze.

title: pinwheels
directions: Cut up meat into small pieces and mix into cream cheese.
Add cheese and onion. Stir together.
Add tabasco.
You can also add sliced olives.
Take your tortilla and put the mixture in the center and spread.
Roll it up and continue filling the tortillas until the mixture is gone.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice them up and serve with picante or guacamole.

title: swiss cheese potatoes
directions: Melt 2 Tbsp. butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Stir in potatoes.
Turn the mixture into a 10x6x2 inch baking dish.
Cover and bake for 35 minutes at 350°F.
Mix crumbs and remaining butter, and sprinkle around edges.
Bake uncovered 10-15 minutes.
For a breakfast casserole or supper casserole, add smokie links, chunked smoked sausage, or diced ham before baking.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: In a large bowl, combine biscuit and cornbread crumbs, onion, celery and butter; mix well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add sage (rub spice gently between fingers to enhance flavor).
Add chicken or turkey broth and eggs; mix lightly.
Use mixture for stuffing poultry or a crown roast, or bake in a lightly greased baking pan, covered, at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: lime chiffon salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add reserved juice.
Cool until slightly thickened (like thick syrup).
Beat until frothy (use egg beater).
Fold in pineapple, cottage cheese, mayonnaise and nuts.
Place in 13 x 9-inch or mold or square pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oyster cracker munchies
directions: Mix oil, dressing mix and spices together.
Pour over crackers and stir.
Can be put in a large, brown paper bag on a cookie sheet and shaken several times over 30 to 45 minutes.
Store in a tightly covered container.

title: caramel corn
directions: Fill a large roasting pan with 5 to 6 quarts of popped corn. Using another cooking pan, prepare sugar, margarine and corn syrup.
Boil 5 minutes; remove from heat.
Add vanilla, salt and soda.
Blend and pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Place in 250° oven for 40 minutes.
Stir often from the bottom.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and egg together and mix well.
Add spices, soda and salt; add flour and molasses.
The hot water goes in last.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for one hour.

title: banana spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly. Add vanilla and beaten eggs. Sift all dry ingredients together and add alternately with mashed bananas and milk. Bake in a square or oblong Pyrex dish for 30 minutes.

title: meatballs in mushroom sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup, mixing well.
Divide mixture into thirds, making 10 meatballs from each section (30 in all).
Place in shallow baking dish and bake uncovered 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; drain.
Combine mushroom soup and 1/2 cup water.
Pour over the meatballs and return to oven for 20 minutes.
Serve over buttered noodles.

title: eggplant-squash casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Salt and let sit for 20 to 30 minutes. Put eggplant in a large strainer and rinse with cold water.
Steam eggplant and squash until barely done.
Don't overcook.
Saute onion and green pepper in defatted chicken broth.
Add tomatoes, basil, oregano and thyme.
Heat to a simmer.
Toss all ingredients together.
Put in a large casserole dish (lightly greased).
Put Mozzarella cheese on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, salt, pepper and onion flakes.
Press beef in 2-quart casserole dish. Combine soups and spread over beef. Stand Tater Tots on end on top of soup layer.
Bake at 375°
for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar, eggs, bananas, lemon juice and milk.
Add pecans alternately with dry ingredients and cream mixture.
Pour into 2 loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: southern hush puppies
directions: Heat 2 to 3 inches Crisco oil in deep fryer or large saucepan to 375°.
Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop batter by tablespoons into hot oil.
Fry a few at a time, 3 to 4 minutes. Drain on paper towels.
Repeat with remaining batter.
Serve immediately or keep warm in 175° oven.
Makes about 1 dozen hush puppies.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes.
Pour half into a large shallow baking dish.
Add potatoes.
Top with remaining syrup.
Bake at 350°, basting often, for 20 minutes.
Do not cover.

title: tex-mex soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook turkey or beef, onion and garlic until meat is browned; drain off fat.
Add tomatoes, corn, chillies, water, broth, chili powder and bay leaf.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes. Add zucchini; simmer 5 to 10 minutes more or until zucchini are tender-crisp.
Makes 6 (1 3/4 cup) main-dish servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger. Drain. Mix all 3 ingredients well, then microwave for 5 minutes. Keep warm in crock-pot. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Mix spaghetti sauce and hamburger together.
Set aside.
Mix rest of ingredients to make filling.
Stuff shells with filling. Put 1/4 of sauce mixture in two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Place filled shells in pan and pour rest of sauce over shells.
Sprinkle with more Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pans.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Pour 1/2 cup cooking oil in bottom of rectangular cake pan. Dump 1 package yellow cake mix over top of oil and add eggs, coconut and pineapple with juice and water.
Stir until ingredients are mixed well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (test with toothpick for doneness).
Remove from oven and poke holes in cake with handle of wooden spoon.
Make package of instant pudding as directed on package.
When slightly set, pour over cake so that pudding goes in holes. The rest over the cake.
Before serving, top with Cool Whip and generously sprinkle with coconut.

title: pepper steak
directions: In large skillet, heat shortening and brown meat, turning frequently.
Stir in the soup mix and 2 cups water.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in pepper and simmer for 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with 1/2 cup water and add to skillet mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix lemon juice in peaches as they are peeled and mashed. Sweeten fruit to taste.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl and chill.
Pour into can of ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: pizza dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream together.
Add spices and red pepper.
Layer that on bottom of ceramic casserole dish (preferably round).
Add pizza sauce, then pepperoni.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Put a layer of Doritos, layer of hamburger, layer of mixture and layer of cheese.
Repeat until all are gone, ending with cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine and press in bottom of large pan. Mix Dream Whip in another bowl with cream cheese and sugar.
Put 1/2 of mixture in pan.
Add the cherries, add remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle top with a few crumbs, chill overnight or 2 to 3 hours in freezer.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Place cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Chill before serving.
Serve with sliced apples.

title: margarita pie
directions: Combine gelatin, 1/2 cup sugar and salt in saucepan.
Beat egg yolks and lime juice until foamy.
Stir into gelatin mixture.
Cook over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in tequila, liqueur and lime peel.
Chill until thick, but not set.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine margarine, butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Beat well. Add salt, vanilla and eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour; mix well.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Place pan in cold oven; bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours, or until done.
Cool in pan.

title: prize winning crab
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Blend in flour and soup, stirring until thick.
Add crab meat and seasonings. Turn into greased casserole and top with dry bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake in 375° oven until brown.
May be served in ramekins.

title: cabbage pineapple slaw
directions: Drain 3 tablespoons juice from pineapple.
Combine cabbage, apples, celery and raisins.
Mix mayonnaise and 3 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Pour over rest of the vegetables.
Cover and chill.
Let set at least 6 to 8 hours to let the flavors blend. The longer you keep this salad the better it gets.

title: mocked cabbage rolls
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
In crock-pot, put in layers the chopped cabbage, ground beef, onion and rice, then the jar of sauce.
Put 1 cup water in jar and shake.
Pour on top. Cover with lid and cook on low overnight or cook on high for 5 to 6 hours. You can also bake in oven, but you steam the cabbage in 1/2 cup water and use 3 cups cooked rice.
Place in layers in a large casserole.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven. You can also use ground turkey in both ways.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Mix and pat onto cookie sheet 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in small squares before baking at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crabmeat-broccoli casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread; cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes. Combine
bread
cubes,
milk and mayonnaise; stir well.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Remove mixture from refrigerator; stir in	eggs,
crabmeat,
onion
and parsley.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well.	Arrange broccoli in a
lightly greased
x
9	x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon crabmeat
mixture evenly
over broccoli.
Bake, uncovered, at 325°
for
40 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: easy turtle cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
While still warm, poke holes in cake. Pour caramel topping and Eagle Brand over cake. Let cool. Top with Cool Whip and crushed Heath bars. Yields 15 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Mix and bring to boil chicken broth and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Next combine flour, margarine and buttermilk to form a batter.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain pineapple; add juice and chill mixture until slightly thickened.
Beat until frothy. Fold in the cheese, pineapple, horseradish, nuts and mayonnaise or cream.
Spoon into mold and chill until set.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix in blender or processor.
Chill and serve.

title: dress-em-up carrots
directions: Place carrots, onions and soup in a casserole; pour 1/2 cup water over.
Top with cheese, butter and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, peanut butter and butter together thoroughly in a saucepan.
Cook until mixture reaches boil.
Boil one minute.
Remove from heat and add oats and cocoa, which have been mixed together in a mixing bowl.
Stir until oats are moistened. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, onion, pimento, eggs, mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and salt in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle topping over casserole.
Chill for several hours to overnight.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Yield:
8 servings.

title: house's egg nog(low fat version)
directions: Mix ingredients in food processor.
Garnish with nutmeg and cinnamon.

title: christmas pumpkin bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, 1/3 cup water and pumpkin.
Sift next 6 ingredients.
Beat together and add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done by testing.

title: date balls
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar and dates.
Boil 3 minutes.
In another bowl, add date mixture.
While warm, roll in coconut or powdered sugar or both.

title: old fashion fudge(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt in a 3 1/2-quart mixing bowl or casserole (will boil over if vessel is too small).
Stir in milk and syrup thoroughly!
Add butter; cover.
Microwave on High 5 minutes; mix well.
Microwave 10 to 14 minutes.
Test for soft ball.
Cook without stirring.
Let set to lukewarm. After 10 minutes add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Pour into buttered plate.

title: breakfast or brunch casserole
directions: Remove
crusts
from
bread
(optional);
butter bread. Place in a
x
x
2-inch baking dish.
Crumble and cook sausage until browned.
Drain well.
Spoon over bread slices. Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, half and half and cheese; mix well and
pour
over
cheese.
May be covered and chilled overnight. Remove for 15 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for about
45 minutes uncovered.
Very nice dish to take to a friend in need.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In Dutch oven, cook ground beef.
Add tomatoes and tomato juice.
Bring to boil and add onion.
Shred cabbage and carrots; add to pot.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer about 30 minutes. Freezes well.

title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: *Can use Jell-O vanilla flavor sugar-free instant pudding and pie filling and Cool Whip Lite topping.

title: date bran muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a 6-quart mixing bowl, mixing well.
Add dry ingredients, stirring just enough to moisten.
Store in covered container in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika in a paper
bag.
Put
shortening and butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish
and melt in oven.
Shake 3 or 4 pieces of chicken in the flour at a time.
Place the floured chicken in hot oil. Bake 30 minutes; turn and bake 30 minutes more.

title: four bean salad
directions: Place beans in shallow baking dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except onion rings.
Pour over beans.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Just before serving, add onion rings.
Toss lightly, drain.
Transfer to large lettuce-lined salad bowl.
Makes 12 servings.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Put all together and simmer 45 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Put water, corn meal and butter on stove to thicken.
Thin sugar, salt, baking powder, eggs and flour with evaporated milk. Add all together.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Turn down to 400° for 40 minutes.

title: strombelli
directions: Let bread dough defrost and rise.
Directions are on package. Beat egg and set aside.
When bread has risen, flatten into greased cookie sheet.
Spread dough with a little of the beaten egg, then put on cheese and sliced pepperoni.
Roll up, jelly roll fashion.
Secure ends.
Brush again with beaten egg.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices and serve hot.

title: betty's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in pan of choice.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Halfway through cooking, cover with tomato ketchup and pour some into drippings.

title: preserving old newspaper clippings
directions: Dissolve a Milk of Magnesia tablet in a quart of club soda and let set overnight.
Pour into a pan large enough to contain the flattened clipping.
Let soak 1 hour.
Carefully lift out. Spread on flat absorbent surface and pat dry.
Do not disturb until completely dry.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; spray dish with Pam.
Add ingredients to dish; cover with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° to 400° oven until it bubbles around edges.

title: quick beef soup
directions: Cook ground chuck in large nonstick skillet over medium heat until browned, stirring until meat crumbles.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Wipe pan dripping from skillet with paper towel.
Return meat to skillet; add carrot, onion, tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Stir in water.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 to 35 minutes or until carrot is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serving:
1/2 cup.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: When dough is ready to be made into rolls, roll out on lightly floured surface until 1/2 to 1-inch thick rectangle.
Spread with softened oleo, sprinkle on cinnamon sugar, nuts and raisins.
Roll up jelly-roll fashion.
Slice 1 to 2 inches thick and place in greased baking pan, 2 to 3 inches deep.
Let rise until double in size and bake 15 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: fresh lemon meringue pie
directions: Grate 1 teaspoon peel from lemon and squeeze out 1/2 cup juice.
Set aside.
Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan thoroughly and blend in lemon juice, cold water and beaten egg yolks until completely smooth.
Add the butter and stir in the boiling water gradually.
Bring to a boil and cook for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in the grated peel and cool.

title: impossible custard pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Put in 10-inch pie plate.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough, otherwise just scrub and rinse them.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through (use a handle of a spoon laid in front of the potato as you cut, to prevent knife from cutting all the way).
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Fan them slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake potatoes at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake potatoes for another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned, cheese is melted and potatoes are soft inside.
Serves 4.

title: swedish potato sausage
directions: Cut up the potatoes and onions; run through a meat grinder or chop up in a blender.
Put all the ingredients (except for the casing) and work/mix together by hand.
Soak casings in warm water.
When the meat mixture is mixed to satisfaction, put into a sausage stuffer and fill the casings.
These sausages can be frozen in freezer bags.

title: oysters ala gino
directions: Open oysters, letting oysters remain in door half of shell. Place oysters on a shallow baking pan.
Remove cartilage from crabmeat and put in medium bowl.
In a small bowl mix together Newburg sauce, sherry, chopped bacon, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour sauce over crabmeat and mix gently, being careful not to break crab lumps.
Fill each oyster with approximately 1 tablespoon crab mixture.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces; roll in seasoned flour and brown in hot oil.
Remove from skillet.
Cook onion, garlic and green pepper in remaining oil until onion is golden.
Add pimento and rice; stir over low heat 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to boil.
Pour into
2-quart casserole.
Arrange chicken on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Fry hamburger and drain well.
Put in slow cooker.
Add soups, sauce and cheese.
Cook in slow cooker until cheese is melted. Serve with chips.

title: chocolate chip ice cream pie
directions: Coat bottom and sides of an 8-inch pie plate lightly with margarine.
Combine chocolate syrup and chocolate chips in a microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave until hot (about 45 seconds).
Take out 1/4 cup of mixture and set aside.
Combine remaining chocolate mixture and Rice Krispies until Krispies are well coated.
Press mixture over bottom and up sides of pie plate.
Freeze about 15 minutes, until firm.

title: chewy chocolate chews
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first five ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes; stir in chocolate chips.
On baking sheet coated with cooking spray, drop rounded tablespoons of goo 2-inches apart.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on wire rack and store in an airtight container. Makes 60 cookies.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Slightly cook broccoli. Using a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, layer broccoli, chicken, broccoli, chicken.

title: shirley's crazy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine dry ingredients, then by hand, mix in wet ingredients.
Pour into pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes or until finger tapped in center does not leave an imprint (usually the cake leaves the sides of the pan).
Do not overbake. Let cool in pan for at least 1 hour before frosting in the pan.

title: charlie cole slaw
directions: Mix slaw and dressing separately, then combine with a fork. Serves 5.

title: green bean and cheese casserole
directions: Cook beans 9 minutes on High in the microwave.
Add mushroom soup and cheese to beans and mix.
Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Cook 5 minutes on High.
Stir and top with onion rings.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Cut bacon and fry in Dutch oven.
Remove bacon and saute sirloin (previously cut in 1/4 x 4-inch strips) until brown.
Add garlic and mushrooms.
Heat through and add seasonings.
Add bacon and stir thoroughly and remove from heat.
I use a separate stew pan and make a roux with butter and flour.
Cook, stirring constantly, until light tan in color.
Add liquid, stir and cook until slightly thickened.
Add to beef and mushroom mixture. Cover and simmer until beef is tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add additional seasoning as desired.

title: bratwurst with potatoes
directions: Place bratwurst, potatoes and water or beef broth into wide skillet or saute pan and simmer until water or beef broth evaporates and the potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Add apples into pan.
Push bratwurst and apples to one side and sprinkle sugar over a portion of the skillet.
Stir over high heat until sugar melts or caramelizes.
Add butter and stir with the potatoes and apples until evenly seasoned.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Keep warm until ready to serve.

title: bread pudding
directions: Arrange slices of bread in overlapping rows in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Drizzle melted butter over bread.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and raisins.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Add onion, green pepper and celery. Simmer on range top until tender.
Pour into 4-quart baking dish. Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and rice.
Blend well.
Garnish top with chopped parsley.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: string beans supreme
directions: Bake 1/2 hour or until tender at 325°.
Last 5 minutes, add onion rings on top.

title: mini german chocolate banana loaves
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mash bananas with mixer (30 seconds). Add cake mix, milk, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Blend on low for 1 minute, scrape down sides of bowl and beat 2 minutes on medium. Add chocolate chips.
Pour into 6 (6-inch) loaf pans that have been sprayed and floured.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Brown ground beef in microwave or stove, then place in crock-pot.
Drain and wash beans; place in pot.
Chop up carrots, zucchini and mushrooms.
Place all other ingredients in pot; stir well.
Put on high approximately 6 hours.

title: sausage potato dinner
directions: Grease a 3-quart baking dish.
In a large saucepan, heat soup and water over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Prepare cheese, peppers and pimientos.
Slice sausage.
Add above to soup mixture. Continue to heat.
Slice potatoes and layer on bottom of dish. Pour soup mixture over potatoes and bake at 400° for 1 1/4 hours. Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs gradually, sugar and oil.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Alternately to egg mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Flour and grease 2 loaf pans.
Separate mixture equally in pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Freezes very well.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl.
Mix thoroughly by hand, 50 strokes or more.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spicy apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spread apple pie filling in an 8-inch square pan or dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well. Spread over apples.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Serve plain or top with vanilla ice cream.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy and quick chocolate muffins
directions: Mix 2 ingredients together. Pour into muffin cups and bake.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Boil until soft.
Spread in baking dish after drained.
Cover with butter.
Mix soup and milk.
Whisk until smooth.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over potatoes. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: big cookies
directions: Mix eggs and butter until creamy. Add both sugars and mix. After this step and as you add the next ingredients, your mixer will not be able to handle the volume.

It is best to mix with your hands and you will need a large bowl. After you have it all mixed, use an ice cream scoop to drop the dough on a cookie sheet. You will only be able to bake 4 to 6 cookies per sheet. As you drop the dough with the ice cream scoop, flatten the dough with the back of the scoop.
Dough will spread while baking.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave chili
directions: Crumble ground beef in a 2-quart glass casserole.
Stir in onion and green pepper.
Cover.
Microwave 6 to 8 minutes on High or until beef is browned.
Drain and stir in remaining ingredients.
Re-cover and microwave 20 to 25 minutes on medium or until hot. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 5 to 7 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with liquids to the cream mixture until smooth.
Bake in a tube pan that has been greased.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
Don't open oven while cooking.

title: sopa
directions: In a 2-quart heavy pan, fry pasta in oil until lightly browned. Stir constantly.
Add onion and garlic until browned. Add tomato sauce, broth and seasonings.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and steam 20 to 25 minutes. Do not stir. Serve and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Serves 3 to 4. Temperature: Medium heat.

title: hash brown cheese casserole
directions: Place potatoes in colander.
Let stand until completely thawed and excess moisture is drained off.
Combine sour cream, soup and butter.
Mix well.
Add salt, onion and cheese.
Mix well.
Blend in potatoes.
Place mixture in shallow 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle buttered corn flakes on top.
Bake uncovered in oven preheated to 350° for about 50 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.
Best when assembled not more than 2 hours before it goes into the oven. Makes 8 servings.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter; add flour and cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; whisk in half and half.
Add mushrooms and seasonings.
Return to heat; bring to a boil, lower heat and cook until thick.
Really good base for crab soup, too (without mushrooms and some Old Bay). Serves 4.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Chill and serve on crackers.

title: caramel nut rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm water in beater bowl; stir in sugar, salt, margarine, egg and 2 cups of flour and beat until smooth. Gradually work in enough of remaining flour until dough is easy to handle.
On board, make into smooth ball.
Place in greased bowl, turn over to grease top, cover tightly and place in refrigerator until needed.

title: corn fritters *
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat egg, melted shortening and milk together.
Add corn to dry ingredients, then add to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Drop spoonfuls into hot oil and fry until golden brown.
Drain.
Makes about 12 fritters.

title: coconut lemon pie
directions: Combine egg yolks and lemon juice; set aside.
In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat; bring to a boil. Turn heat down to low; cook, stirring, for 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rind, butter and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.

title: walnut cookies
directions: Work flour and butter with hands.
Add sugar and mix.
Add walnuts and mix well.
Add egg yolks and mix until stiff dough. Add more flour if dough is too soft but don't get dough too dry or it will crumble.
Take large pieces of dough and roll out on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters and place on greased cookie sheet.
Beat egg whites until stiff and place a dab on center of each cookie.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook noodles.
Cook broccoli and onion in oil until tender. Remove from heat; stir in Parmesan cheese, Ricotta cheese, salt and 4 eggs.

title: vodka cooler(this drink is for adults only.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate in a pitcher until ready to drink.
Pour a glass 1/4 full with this mixture, add ice cubes and finish filling glass with strawberry soda, cream soda, or whatever kind of soda you desire.

title: easy boiled custard, i
directions: Beat yolks, sugar and flour.
Add 1 cup of the hot milk and mix well.
Add the remaining milk and stir constantly over medium heat until thickened.
Refrigerate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: big chocolate chip cookie
directions: Mix by hand.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Put dough on two pizza pans.
Decorate if desired.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour and set aside.
Mix butter, oil, cocoa and water in pan and boil rapidly for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour boiling mixture into flour and sugar; mix well.
Then add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Five minutes before cake is done, mix glaze (follows).

title: cottage cheese patties
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Brown in nonstick pan.
Make gravy or cover with mushroom soup mixed with 1 can milk.
Pour sauce over patties and bake until nearly all of the gravy has simmered into patties.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In large bowl combine and beat the peanut butter, butter, brown sugar and sugar until creamy. Gradually beat in the eggs and vanilla.
Set aside.

title: potato and kielbasa casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients but potatoes, kielbasa and cheese in microwave pan.
Cook 3 minutes on High.
Stir and continue cooking on Medium heat until thick.
Add potatoes and continue cooking until potatoes are almost done.
Add kielbasa and cook an additional 5 minutes.
Top with cheese and serve.

title: cabbage salad
directions: In a small bowl, beat egg and add slightly diluted vinegar and stir well.
In a saucepan, put sugar and cornstarch and mix.
Add egg and vinegar mixture slowly.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute. Add margarine and let melt.
Add cayenne pepper.
Cool.
I then mix the dressing with some Miracle Whip about 50-50.
Mix with cabbage.

title: cottage cheese jello salad
directions: Put cottage cheese in large bowl in Mixmaster; add dry Jell-O, mix well, add drained pineapple and mix.
Last add 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Mix well, let set for 3 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a large skillet, saute celery and onion in
butter until done.
Add broccoli, cream of mushroom soup and grated cheese. Stir in Minute rice.
Pour into greased baking dish. Top with cracker crumbs. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: french fried rattlesnake
directions: Dip pieces of snake meat in beaten egg to which garlic has been added.
Combine cracker crumbs, flour, salt and pepper in a paper bag.
Drop egg-coated pieces, one at a time, into the bag. Remove and fry until golden brown in the hot oil.

title: sweet hot pickle crisps
directions: Mix sugar, red pepper and garlic.
Alternate layers of pickles and sugar mixture inside large glass jar.
Set aside one day. Next day, turn jar upside down.
Third day, turn right side up. Fourth day, eat!

title: tracie's famous homemade pancakes
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together with a whisk.	Pour onto hot griddle with a ladle.
Turn when bubbled up on the first side and serve when golden brown on the other.
Enjoy!

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix the Jell-O with cottage cheese. Stir together. Add rest of ingredients and whip together. (Simple.)

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
(Optional: Sprinkle with chopped nuts.)
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple, including juice, into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour cherry pie filling on top of pineapple.	Dump dry cake mix on top of cherries.
Slice pats of butter and put on top of cake mix.
Bake according to cake mix directions or until knife comes out clean.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients several times.
Add sugar to the oil and mix well.
Mix dry ingredients into oil/sugar mixture. Add eggs, pumpkin and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans (2) and bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: lime pickles
directions: Pour over cucumbers and let stand overnight.
The next day simmer for 35 minutes and seal in hot jars.

title: peruvian chicken
directions: Mix together marinade.
Marinate chicken for 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes if boneless, 45 minutes with bone.
Serve over rice or with potatoes.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Toss with cheese in bowl.
Separate rolls into triangles.
Place some chicken mixture in center of each triangle.
Roll up from wide end.
Place in 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Combine soup and milk in saucepan; mix well.
Bring to a boil, stirring until smooth.
Pour over chicken rolls.
Sprinkle with any remaining cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: king's ranch casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add 1/2 cup cheese.
Remove from heat as soon as cheese melts.
Mix soups, tomatoes, broth and seasoning in bowl, then add to cheese mixture.
Coat bottom of large casserole dish with Pam.
Place a thick layer of crushed chips in bottom of pan.
Place a layer of cheese mixture, a layer of chicken and the remaining cheese mixture.
Top with plenty of grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: elegant french toast with maple syrup
directions: Use 1 slice of rye or pumpernickel bread for each.
Set oven for broil.
Put slices on cookie sheet.
Add slice or two of ham. Spread coleslaw on top.
Add slice of Swiss or whatever cheese on top.
Put under broiler until a little brown and cheese bubbles.

title: mock babe ruth bars
directions: Mix together butter, brown sugar and Karo syrup. Then add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes in a 9 x 13 pan. Melt milk chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter, then add peanuts. Spread over oatmeal layer and let cool.

title: tamales
directions: Use
an
electric
mixer to combine all ingredients but masa together
until
creamy
and smooth.
Small portion at a time, add masa to shortening mixture until all masa is added. Set aside.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake supreme
directions: Combine crumbs and melted margarine; press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: toffee bars
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the first 3 ingredients and boil for exactly 3 minutes.
Put heavy foil on cookie sheet.
Place 40 saltine crackers or how many it takes to cover pan.
Pour syrup over crackers.
Bake in a 400° oven for 5 minutes.
When removed from oven, sprinkle with the chocolate chips.
Let them melt and smooth over crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Let cool to set.

title: chicken spectacular casserole
directions: Cook rice according to instructions.
Saute chicken breast until done.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
In large casserole dish, combine green beans, water chestnuts, pimentos and onions.
When rice is done, mix with chicken and add to bowl.
Mix together well. Top with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake a 350° for 30 - 45 minutes.

title: chicken squares
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Separate an 8 ounce can of rolls into 4 triangles.
Seal perforations.
Spoon 1/2 cup mixture onto center of each roll; pull the 4 corners of dough to center of mixture. Seal and brush tops with melted butter.
Sprinkle tops with crushed croutons.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Cook vegetables according to directions.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Makes about 8 side dish servings.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions with margarine in large skillet for 15 to 20 minutes over medium flame. Place half of onions in 13 x 19 x 2 inch baking dish. Top with half of crackers and half of parmesan cheese. Repeat with remaining ingredients. Bake, uncovered, in 325° gas oven for 30 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.
